output: Jennifer purchased 40 cans of milk at the store before meeting her classmate Mark, who was also buying milk. Jennifer bought 7.5 additional cans for every 5 cans Mark bought. If Mark purchased 50 cans, how many cans of milk did Jennifer bring home from the store?

Catriona has 8 goldfish in her aquarium. She has 4 more angelfish than goldfish. Additionally, she has three times as many guppies as angelfish. If she decides to add 5 more goldfish next month, how many fish will she have in her aquarium then?

Libby is constructing an igloo in her backyard using bricks of snow. The igloo is built in 10 rows, where the bottom half of the igloo has \( a \) bricks of snow in each row, and the top half has \( b \) bricks of snow in each row. How many bricks of snow did Libby use for her igloo if \( a = 12 \) and \( b = 8 \)?

Evelyn uses a pad of paper with 60 sheets every week at work. She takes Monday and Friday off, and if she has an important meeting, she uses 5 extra sheets that day. Assuming she has 10 important meetings in a year, how many sheets of paper does she use per day at work on average?

Melissa is repairing her shoes. She has 6 shoes that need their buckles replaced and 4 shoes that need their heels evened out. If it takes her 5 minutes to replace a buckle and 10 minutes to even out a heel, how many total minutes will Melissa spend on this project? Additionally, if she wants to complete the repairs in 2 hours, how many more shoes can she fix if each additional shoe requires 7 minutes of work?
Larry spends time each day walking and playing with his dog. He also spends some time feeding his dog. How many minutes does Larry spend on his dog each day?

Sarah contributes a fraction \( p \) of the cost of raising a child. The cost is $10,000 per year for the first 8 years, then doubles to $20,000 per year until the child is 18. University tuition costs $250,000. If Sarah pays for \( p \) of the total cost, how much does she pay in total?

Maria is saving up to buy a new bike that costs $750. She has already saved $150. Her grandmother gives her an additional $200, but she still needs more money. If Maria decides to earn the rest by selling handmade crafts, how much more does she need to earn to buy the bike?

Jean bought 4 packs of 15 cupcakes. If she wants to give one cupcake each to 100 children in the orphanage, and cupcakes are also sold in packs of 10, how many packs of 10 cupcakes should she buy to have exactly enough cupcakes for all the children?

Jasmine and her sister went to the store to buy shoes. Jasmine's shoes are size 7. If Alexa's shoes are twice as big as Jasmine's, and they decide to buy a second pair of shoes that are half the size of the first pair, what is the total size of all the shoes they buy?

Nelly is thrilled with the antique vase she won at the auction. She tells her daughter that she outbid her rival, Joe, by paying $2000 more than thrice his bid. Additionally, she plans to donate 10% of the vase’s purchase price to a local art museum. If Joe’s bid was $160,000, how much will Nelly donate to the museum?

Viviana has \( v \) vanilla chips and \( c + 5 \) chocolate chips, while Susana has \( \frac{3}{4}v \) vanilla chips and \( c \) chocolate chips. If Viviana has 20 vanilla chips and Susana has 25 chocolate chips, calculate the total number of chips they have together.

On Monday, Sam had some money in his bank account. He then received a payment, which was twice the amount he spent on groceries last week. On Tuesday, he withdrew an amount equal to half of what he had left after the payment was received. On Wednesday, he deposited a sum that was the same as the difference between his initial amount and the amount he withdrew on Tuesday. How much money does Sam have in his account now?

Irene earns $500 if she works for 40 hours a week and gets an extra $20 for every hour of overtime. If she worked 50 hours last week and her total income was $400, how many hours of overtime did she work?

Every day, Sara bakes \( x \) cakes and puts them in her refrigerator. She does this for \( y \) days. Carol then comes over and eats \( z \) of her cakes. If it takes \( w \) cans of frosting to frost a single cake, how many cans of frosting does Bob need to frost the remaining cakes?

Marco has a collection of paintings. He decides to sell some of them. First, he sells 1/3 of his collection. Then, he buys 5 more paintings. Next, he sells 1/4 of what he has left. How many paintings does Marco have now?
Five coaster vans are used to transport students for their field trip. Each van carries 30 students, and 70% of the total students are boys. How many girls are there?
On a USB drive with a capacity of \( c \) gigabytes, \( p\% \) is already used. How many gigabytes are still available?

Bobby is planning a winter drive. For every 4 degrees the temperature drops below 32 degrees, his risk of skidding on ice increases by 10%. If he skids, he has a 30% chance of regaining control. If the temperature is 12 degrees, what is the percentage chance of Bobby getting into a serious accident if he drives?

The owner of a Turkish restaurant wanted to prepare traditional dishes for an upcoming celebration. She ordered ground beef, in four-pound packages, from three different butchers. The following morning, the first butcher delivered 10 packages. A couple of hours later, 7 packages arrived from the second butcher. Finally, the third butcher’s delivery arrived at dusk. If all the ground beef delivered by the three butchers weighed 95 pounds, how many packages did the third butcher deliver?
If Stu has 9 books and Albert has 4 times as many books as Stu, but then Stu gives 3 books to Albert, how many books do they have in total now?
Ann, Bill, Cate, and Dale each buy personal pan pizzas cut into 6 pieces. If Bill and Dale eat 40% of their pizzas and Ann and Cate eat 80% of the pizzas, how many pizza pieces are left uneaten?

Zig and Flo wrote books, with Zig writing four times as many books as Flo. If the total number of books written by both is 75, how many books did Zig write? However, it is also known that Zig wrote 60 books in the first half of the year, and the rest in the second half. How many books did Flo write in the second half of the year?
Brendan can cut x yards of grass per day. After buying a lawnmower, his efficiency increases by y percent per day. How many yards will Brendan be able to cut in z weeks?

Over the past five years, the high temperature for July 4th in Washington, DC has been: 90 degrees in 2020, 90 degrees in 2019, 90 degrees in 2018, 79 degrees in 2017, and 71 degrees in 2016. If the temperature increases by 2 degrees every year starting from 2016, what would be the average temperature for July 4th over the next 5 years?

Janice's office is on the third floor, and she has to walk up 3 flights of stairs to get to her office. In a single day, she goes up the three flights of stairs 5 times, down the three flights of stairs 3 times, and uses the elevator the remainder of the time. However, she also claims that she walks a total of 20 flights of stairs in a day. How many flights of stairs does Janice walk (up and down) in a single day?

Coral is reading a book that is \( p \) pages long. She reads \( \frac{1}{2} \) of it in the first week, and \( 30\% \) of the remaining pages in the second week. How many pages must she read in the third week to finish the book in \( w \) weeks?
There are 12 crates that each contain 150.5 oranges. There are 16 boxes that each hold 30.25 nectarines. How many pieces of fruit are in the crates and the boxes in total?

One of Robi's new year's resolutions is to start saving. He began by saving $3 in January. Each subsequent month, he doubles his savings. If he continues this pattern, how much will he have saved by the end of 6 months?

Steve has 25 socks, including 4 pairs that match. He decides to donate all his mismatching socks to a charity. If the charity needs at least 10 mismatching socks to make a donation, how many more mismatching socks does Steve need to find or buy to meet the charity’s requirement?

Angie's Coffee Consumption Chart

Angie bought 3 lbs. of coffee at the store today. Each lb. of coffee will brew about 40 cups of coffee. The chart below shows Angie's daily coffee consumption over the next few weeks. How many days will this coffee last her? (No chart provided.)
Henry took 9 pills a day for 14 days. Of these 9 pills, 4 pills cost $1.50 each. How much did he spend in total on the pills?

Tom uses 10 weight plates each weighing 30 pounds on an exercise machine. The exercise machine uses special technology to adjust the perceived weight based on the angle of the seat. The diagram below shows the angle adjustments and the corresponding weight multipliers. If Tom adjusts the seat to an angle that makes the weights 20% heavier on the lowering portion, how heavy did the weights feel when being lowered? (No diagram provided.)

A group of friends visited Juju’s Juice Bar and each ordered a glass of fruit juice. They spent a total of $120. Some friends chose mango juice, priced at $5 a glass, while others opted for pineapple juice, priced at $6 a glass. If the amount spent on pineapple juice was twice that spent on mango juice, how many people were in the group?

Jame is trying to improve his card-tearing skills. He starts by tearing 30 cards at a time, but increases the number of cards he tears by 5 every month. He tears cards 3 times a week. If he buys 18 decks, each containing 55 cards including jokers and blank cards, how many weeks can he continue tearing cards before he runs out?

Baez has 25 marbles. She loses 20% of them one day. Then a friend sees her and gives her double the amount that Baez had before she lost any marbles. How many marbles does Baez end up with if she also finds 10 more marbles on the way home, but only if she had fewer than 30 marbles after her friend gave her the marbles?

Olivia earns $9 per hour. She worked 4 hours on Monday, 3 hours on Wednesday, and 6 hours on Friday. Her friend, Mia, also earns $9 per hour and worked the same number of hours as Olivia on each day. If they both received a bonus, how much money did Olivia and Mia make together this week?

John has a chart that shows his daily schedule for watching a show over 5 days. The show has 20 episodes, each 30 minutes long. The chart includes the times he can watch the show each day, but it is not provided here. How many hours does John need to watch each day to finish the show on time?

Henry took 9 pills a day for 14 days. Of these 9 pills, 4 pills cost $1.50 each, and the other pills each cost $5.50 more. However, the total cost of the pills per day was only $10. How much did he spend in total on the pills?

Hawkeye is driving to his aunt's place, which is 200 miles away. He charges his battery for $3.5 per charge. If he charged his battery four times during the trip and his battery charging budget was $20, how much money was he left with when he reached his aunt's place? Additionally, if he had to stop for a meal and spent some of his remaining budget, how much did he spend on the meal?

James watched 2 episodes of Jeopardy and 2 episodes of Wheel of Fortune. Jeopardy is 20 minutes and Wheel of Fortune is twice as long. However, each episode of Wheel of Fortune also includes a 10-minute time travel segment where the show pauses and the contestants travel 100 years into the future. How many hours did he effectively watch TV, considering the time travel segments?

Carl has a jar full of marbles. He takes out 15 marbles to play a game with, but he accidentally drops them and 2/3 of the marbles get lost. So Carl takes out 8 more marbles. While he is playing his game, his mother comes home with another bag of marbles for him, which has 18.5 marbles in it. If Carl can't find his lost marbles, then how many marbles is he going to put in the jar after he plays his game, from both his original marbles and the new ones?
A square has four sides of different lengths, and the perimeter is 20 cm. If one side is 5 cm, what is the length of the diagonal of this square?

Lana and her friends go to a theater on the weekend to watch a new play Joan told them was live. When they arrived, Lana saw 100 cars in the front parking lot. She saw two times more vehicles at the back than there were in the front parking lot. If the total number of cars at the end of the play was 700, how many more cars packed into the parking lot during the play, and did any of the initial cars leave?
Roselyn gives Mara three times as many books as she gives Rebecca and remains with 75 books. If Rebecca received 50 books, how many books did Roselyn have initially?

A cylinder of whole milk that normally has a volume of 1 gallon and costs $3 is now sold at $2. A parallelogram of cereal was sold at a discount of $1. How much will you save via discounts if you buy 3 cylinders of whole milk and 5 parallelograms of cereal?

Nancy, the librarian, is shelving books from the cart. She shelved 12 history books, 8 romance books, and 4 poetry books from the top section of the cart. Half the books on the bottom section of the cart were mystery books, which she quickly put back into place. Then, she shelved the remaining books from the bottom of the cart, including 5.5 Western novels and 6.5 biographies. How many books did she have on the book cart when she started?

Kate bought 7 packs of red bouncy balls and 6 packs of yellow bouncy balls. Each pack contained 18 bouncy balls. If she decides to give away 25% of the red bouncy balls and 10% of the yellow bouncy balls, how many more red bouncy balls than yellow bouncy balls does she have left?

Mark plans to visit the theater at least once a week. Each performance lasts \( t \) hours, and the ticket price is \( p \) dollars per hour. If Mark decides to spend \( h \) hours at the theater each week, how much will he spend on theater visits over \( w \) weeks?

Jenny bought some books and spent half of her savings. She then earned some money by selling old toys and now has $20. How much did she originally have, and how much did she earn from selling the toys?

Sansa is a famous artist who can draw portraits that shrink over time. She sells an 8-inch portrait for $5, and a 16-inch portrait for twice the price of the 8-inch portrait. If the 8-inch portraits shrink to 4 inches by the end of the day and the 16-inch portraits shrink to 8 inches, and she sells three 8-inch portraits and five 16-inch portraits per day, how much does she earn every 3 days from selling these shrinking portraits?

TreShawn's mom needs to order pizza for a party that lasts for 3 hours. TreShawn starts by eating 1/2 a pizza in the first hour and increases his consumption by 1/6 of a pizza each subsequent hour. Michael eats 1/3 of a pizza in the first hour and decreases his consumption by 1/12 of a pizza each hour. LaMar consistently eats 1/6 of a pizza every hour. How many pizzas does she need to order for the entire party?

Joy is winding balls of yarn for her cat to play with. The first ball is half the size of the second ball. The third ball is three times as large as the first ball. She used 27 feet of yarn for the third ball. However, the second ball is also twice the size of the third ball. How many feet of yarn did she use for the second ball?
Stu has 9 books, and Albert has 4.5 times as many books as Stu. How many books do Stu and Albert have in total?

Flora has been advised by Dr. Juan to drink 105 gallons of milk over 3 weeks to strengthen her bones. If Flora decides to drink 4 gallons of milk daily, how many additional gallons must she drink each day to meet Dr. Juan’s requirement?

Alex decides to invest in a series of lotteries. He buys a total of 200 tickets, each costing $2. Among these, a certain percentage are winners. Of the winning tickets, 80% win a smaller prize, while the rest win larger prizes. One of the tickets is the grand prize, worth $5,000. The remaining winning tickets win an average of $10. How much profit did Alex make?
A store sells chairs and tables. A chair costs 1/7 of the cost of a table. If you buy a table and some chairs, the total cost is $200. How many chairs did you buy, and what is the cost of one table?

Dale and Andrew had breakfast at a cafe. A slice of toast costs £1, and eggs cost £3 each. Dale had 2 slices of toast and 2 eggs. Andrew had 1 slice of toast and 2 eggs. The cafe offers a discount of 150% on the total bill. How much did their breakfast cost?

Riku has 25 times more stickers than Kristoff. If Kristoff has 85 stickers, and each sticker weighs 100 kilograms, how many stickers does Riku have, and what is the total weight of Riku's stickers in metric tons?

Lennon is a sales rep who receives mileage reimbursement at a rate of $0.36 per mile. In the first week, he drove 18 miles on Monday, 26 miles on Tuesday, 20 miles each on Wednesday and Thursday, and 16 miles on Friday. Each subsequent week, he increases his total weekly mileage by 10 miles. How much money will he be reimbursed over the first four weeks?
If children 6–11 years old watch television for \( t \) minutes each day, and they are allowed to watch television \( d \) days a week, how many hours do they watch television in \( w \) weeks?

Jackson is redesigning a rectangular courtyard that measures 12 feet by 30 feet. He plans to use a mix of tiles, requiring 5 tiles per square foot. If 35% of the tiles are blue marble costing $4 each, and the remaining tiles are yellow, costing $2 each, how much will Jackson spend in total on the tiles?

Alice decides to buy books and pens for her classes. She buys 5 books and several pens. Each book costs $20, and each pen costs $2. If she spends a total of $120, how many pens did Alice buy? However, it is not clear whether the total cost includes a 10% discount on the books or if the discount applies to the entire purchase.

Marvin and Tina were selling candy bars to help fund their class trip. The candy bars cost $2 each. Marvin sold 35 candy bars total. Tina sold three times the number of candy bars as Marvin, but she only made $10 more than Marvin. How much more money did Tina make for the class trip selling candy bars compared to Marvin?

A cable company has a roll of cable and decides to cut it into various lengths. The lengths and the number of sections for each length are shown in the chart below. After distributing some sections to different clients, the company needs to determine how many 25-foot sections remain. How many 25-foot sections are left after the distribution? (No chart provided.)

To make 3 liters of ketchup, Ashley needs 69 kg of tomatoes. If Ashley decides to make 5 liters of ketchup every month but doubles her production in the summer months (June, July, and August), how many kilograms of tomatoes does she need in a year?

Karen had a giant box of crayons, containing twice as many crayons as were in Beatrice's box. Beatrice's box contained three times as many crayons as were in Gilbert's box. Gilbert had twice as many crayons as were in Judah's box. If Karen's box contained 216 crayons, how many crayons were in Judah's box?

A survey conducted by the school showed that only 20% of the 800 parents agree to a tuition fee increase. If the school decides to send a follow-up letter to each parent who disagrees, and each letter is 4 pages long, how many pages will the school write in total to the parents who disagree?

Samson ate 3 sandwiches at lunch and twice as many at dinner on Monday. The next morning, he felt sick and only ate 1 sandwich for breakfast. If Samson eats x sandwiches at lunch, 2x sandwiches at dinner, and y sandwiches for breakfast the next day, how many more sandwiches did he eat on Monday than on Tuesday?

Mrs. Johnson plans to purchase items totaling $600. She arrives at the store with $600, but discovers she needs an additional one-third of her amount to cover the costs. If the store offers a 20% discount, how much more money will she need to complete her purchase?

A cleaning company produces two sanitizer sprays. One spray kills 50% of germs, and another spray kills 25% of germs. The effectiveness of these sprays against different types of germs is shown in the chart below. However, 5% of the germs they kill are the same ones. What percentage of germs would be left after using both sanitizer sprays together? (No chart provided.)

Joy is winding balls of yarn for her cat to play with. The first ball is a perfect cube with a side length of 3 feet. The second ball is a sphere with a diameter equal to the side length of the first ball. The third ball is a flat circle with a circumference equal to the perimeter of the first ball. She used 27 feet of yarn for the third ball. How many cubic feet of yarn did she use for the second ball?
Tom and Tim both brought 4 six-sided dice to school, but Tim decided to add 2 more dice each month. How many total sides are there on all the dice they have combined at the end of 6 months?

The price of a home is $98 per square foot (sq ft). The house is 2,400 sq ft and the barn out back is 1,000 sq ft. The property also includes a garden and a pool, the areas of which are shown in the diagram below. Calculate the total cost of the property, including the garden and the pool. (No diagram provided.)

Dale owns 4 sports cars. The speed of the red car is twice that of the green car, which in turn is 8 times the speed of the blue car. The yellow car is out of service and cannot move. If the speed of the blue car is \( b \) miles per hour, express the speed of the red car in terms of \( b \).

Colbert is building a treehouse that requires 240 wooden planks in total. A third of these planks come from Colbert’s storage, 40 planks come from Colbert’s friends, and he buys the rest from the store. Additionally, for every 10 planks he buys, he receives 2 planks as a bonus from the store. How many planks of wood does he need to buy from the store to finish his treehouse, considering the bonus planks?

Marcy is a makeup artist preparing for a large wedding. She has 8 tubs of lip gloss, each containing 3 tubes, and each tube can serve 4 people. If she decides to bring an additional 2 tubs as a backup, and this is exactly what she needs to cover everyone, how many people is Marcy applying makeup to?

John volunteers at a shelter and his schedule varies each month. The shelter has a chart that shows the number of hours John volunteers each month. According to the chart, how many hours does John volunteer in a year? (No chart provided.)

Max enjoys collecting model trains. For each of his birthdays, he receives 2 trains, and for each Christmas, he receives 3 trains. This continues for 4 years. At the end of the 4 years, his grandparents decide to give him an additional 50% of the number of trains he already owns. How many trains does Max have now?

Sandy bought 1 million Safe Moon tokens. She has 4 siblings. She wants to keep half of them to herself and divide the remaining tokens among her siblings. However, she also decides to give each sibling an additional 10% of what she keeps for herself. After splitting it up, how many more tokens will she have than any of her siblings?

Ittymangnark and Kingnook are an Eskimo couple living in the most northern region of the Alaskan wilderness with their child, Oomyapeck. Every day, Ittymangnark catches enough fish for the three of them to eat. They split the fish equally among themselves. After splitting the fish, they give all the eyes to Oomyapeck, who gives two of the eyes to his dog and eats the rest himself. If Oomyapeck eats 22 eyes in a day and there are 5 extra fish caught on weekends, how many fish does each person get to eat on a weekend day?

Carrie works for $8 an hour and 35 hours a week at her job. It’s been a month since she started working there. She has saved up all of her money because she wants to buy a bike for $400. After buying the bike, she plans to use the remaining money to buy a rectangular garden plot. The garden plot has a length of 10 feet and a width of 5 feet, but the area of the garden plot is 75 square feet. How much money will she have left over after she buys her bike and the garden plot?

Vaishali has a collection of hats, some of which have stripes and some do not. She mentions that she has 4 hats, each with three stripes. She also has three hats, but it’s not clear if these are additional hats or if they are the same ones mentioned before. Each of these three hats has four stripes. Additionally, she has six hats that are stripe-free, and another two hats, which may or may not be part of the previously mentioned hats, with five stripes each. What is the combined total number of stripes on all of Vaishali’s hats?

Alex is planning to create the longest possible jump rope for a school event. She gathers ropes of various lengths: a 10-foot rope, a 15-foot rope, four 3-foot ropes, and a 9-foot rope. Each knot she ties between the ropes results in a loss of 1.5 feet. How long will the jump rope be after she ties all the ropes together?

John has 2 hives of bees. One hive has 1,000 bees and produces 500 liters of honey. The second hive has 20% fewer bees, but each bee produces 40% more honey. Additionally, during the summer months (June, July, and August), each hive produces an extra 10% of honey due to favorable weather conditions. How much honey does John produce in a year?

Mille is planning snack packs for her kindergarten class. She has 64 pretzels, four times as many goldfish, and 32 suckers. If she divides these snacks equally among the 16 kids in her class, how many items will each child receive?

Andy harvests all the tomatoes from \( p \) plants that have \( t \) tomatoes each. If he dries half of the tomatoes and turns a third of the remaining tomatoes into marinara sauce, how many tomatoes are left in terms of \( p \) and \( t \)?

In a movie screening, there were 50 guests in total. Half of the guests were women, 15 were men, and the rest were children. During the movie, 1/5 of the men and 4 children left. If 10 more children joined the screening after the others left, how many people were in the screening at the end?

Larry has a time-traveling dog that requires him to spend negative 30 minutes each day walking and playing in the past, and he spends a quarter of an hour every day feeding his dog in the future. How many minutes does Larry spend on his dog each day in his normal timeline?

William read 6 books last month, and Brad read three times as many. This month, Brad read 8 books, but William, determined to catch up, read twice as many books as Brad. However, if there was a holiday, William read 2 additional books this month. Assuming there were 3 holidays, who has read more books over the two months, and by how much?

A family with two children, ages 6 and 10, visited an amusement park. The park offers different ticket prices based on age groups, and the ticket prices are listed in a chart. The family also bought some snacks, and the total cost of the snacks is shown in a separate chart. If the family gave the cashier $500, how much change will they receive? (No charts provided.)
Marvin and Tina were selling candy bars to help fund their class trip. Marvin sold 35 candy bars. Tina sold three times as many candy bars as Marvin. How much more did Tina make compared to Marvin?

Pam has some bags of apples. Each of her bags contains as many apples as 3 of Gerald's bags, which have 40 apples each. If Pam has a total of 1200 apples, and each of her bags can magically hold an infinite number of apples, how many bags does she need to contain all her apples?
At Sunshine Orchard, there are 15 more than twice the number of pumpkins at Moonglow Orchard. If Moonglow Orchard has 18 pumpkins, how many are there at Sunshine Orchard?

John plants a plot of trees in a rectangular arrangement. The plot is divided into sections, each containing a different type of tree. The number of trees in each section and the number of apples each type of tree produces are shown in the chart below. John sells each apple for $0.5. How much money does John make from selling all the apples? (No chart provided.)
Randy has 60 mango trees on his farm. He also has 10 more than a third as many coconut trees as mango trees. How many trees does Randy have in all on his farm?
Sally and Bob decide to save half of their earnings from babysitting for a trip. If Sally makes $6 per day and Bob makes $4 per day, how much money will they have saved for their trip?

Brandon can teleport geckos to different dimensions. Last year, he teleported 86 geckos to Dimension A. This year, he teleported twice as many geckos to Dimension B, but each teleportation to Dimension B takes 3 hours. How many hours did Brandon spend teleporting geckos to Dimension B this year?

A cleaning company produces two magical sanitizer sprays. One spray can kill 150% of germs, and another spray can kill 75% of germs. However, 20% of the germs they kill overlap. What percentage of germs would be left after using both sanitizer sprays together?

Brandon, a passionate herpetologist, sold 86 geckos last year. The geckos were a mix of leopard geckos and crested geckos, with leopard geckos making up 60% of the total. The year before, he sold twice as many geckos, and interestingly, the ratio of leopard geckos to crested geckos remained the same. Additionally, Brandon’s pet store is located in a small town with a population of 1,200 people, and he has a loyal customer base of about 150 regulars. How many geckos has Brandon sold in the last two years?

A family went to an amusement park. The regular ticket price and the discount for children were mentioned, but the ticket prices and the ages of the children were not provided. If they gave the cashier $500, how much change will they receive?

Reina has three times as many counters and four times as many marbles as Kevin. If Kevin has 40 counters and 50 marbles, and during the summer, Reina doubles her number of counters and triples her number of marbles, how many counters and marbles does Reina have by the end of the summer?

Three families shared a vacation rental for a week. Each day, everyone uses an oversized beach towel before getting a new one. How many loads of laundry will it take to wash all the oversized beach towels?

The price of a home is $98 per square foot (sq ft). The house is 2,400 sq ft and the barn out back is 1,000 sq ft. However, the barn is actually a portal to a parallel dimension where the price per square foot is negative $50. How much is this property?

Sara has a collection of stickers, and she decides to share them with her friends. She gives 15 stickers to each of her friends. If she has 10 friends and still has 20 stickers left, how many more stickers does she need to give to her friends so that each friend has twice as many stickers as they originally received, assuming she can get more stickers from her cousin who has an unknown number of stickers?

Lucy has been experimenting with baking and wants to ensure she always has enough flour for her recipes. At the start of the month, she had a 1000g bag of flour. She used 350g to make bread on the first week, and then spilled 1/3 of what was left while trying to transfer the flour to a new container. If Lucy wants to have at least 700g of flour in the cupboard by the end of the month, how much more flour does she need to buy, in grams?

Peter goes to the store to buy a soda. The soda costs $0.25 an ounce. He brought $2 with him and leaves with $1.50. However, the store has a policy that you can only buy sodas in multiples of 5 ounces. How many ounces of soda did he buy?

Basil's cookie consumption is tracked in a chart that shows her daily cookie intake over a month. The chart also includes the number of cookies she receives in the morning, during the day, and before bed. Using the chart, determine how many boxes of cookies Basil will need for 30 days, given that each box contains 45 cookies. (No chart provided.)

In my new house, there are 12 medium ceiling lights. The small ceiling lights require 1 bulb each, the medium ones require 2 bulbs each, and the large ones require 3 bulbs each. If my wife says she saw twice as many large ceiling lights as medium ceiling lights and ten more small ceiling lights than medium ones, and we also decide to add 3 more medium ceiling lights during a home renovation, how many bulbs should I buy in total?

Stephanie is planning to decorate \( n \) cupcakes for a birthday party. She currently has \( m \) candles. She wants to decorate \( \frac{n}{2} \) cupcakes with 1 candle each and the remaining \( \frac{n}{2} \) cupcakes with 2 candles each. How many additional candles does Stephanie need to complete the cupcakes if \( n = 24 \) and \( m = 30 \)?

Mary has 5 green crayons and 8 blue crayons of different shades. If she gives out 3 green crayons and 1 blue crayon to Becky, and then each crayon she has left starts multiplying at a rate of 2 crayons per minute, how many crayons will she have after 10 minutes?

However, if she signs up for the store’s loyalty program, she gets an additional 10% off the discounted price. What is the final cost of the dress if Stella signs up for the loyalty program?

Ella saves 35% of all the money she earns or receives in a year. This year, she made $800 from a part-time job, received $300 for her birthday, made $200 from selling some old clothes, and another $100 from tutoring. How much will she save?

Conor can chop 12 eggplants, 9 carrots, and 8 potatoes in a day. If he works 4 times a week, and each week he either doubles the number of vegetables he chops or doubles the number of days he works, how many vegetables can he chop in a month?

A library cabinet houses five ancient scrolls. The first scroll is 4080 years old. If each scroll is older than the last by half as many years as the last scroll’s age, and the fifth scroll can travel back in time at a rate of 100 years per year, how old will the fifth scroll be 10 years from now?

John buys a chair. He then buys a table that is 3 times the price of the chair. After that, he buys a couch that is 5 times the price of the table. If John paid $380 for all these items, and there was a 10% discount on the couch, what was the original price of the couch before the discount?
James writes a comic every other day for 4 years. If he misses writing a comic whenever there is a full moon (occurring 12 times a year), how many comics has he written in total?

Janet’s grades for her first semester of college were 90, 80, 70, and 100. If her semester 2 average was 82 percent, and her overall average for both semesters combined was 85 percent, how much higher was her semester 1 average compared to her semester 2 average, considering that the number of courses in each semester might not be the same?

A group of kids is playing near a park where 48 pigeons are resting on a fountain. Some kids start clapping, and a fraction of the pigeons fly away. Later, a few more kids join, and another fraction of the remaining pigeons decide to fly to a nearby tree. If the first group of kids scared away 1/6 of the pigeons and the second group scared away 1/4 of the remaining pigeons, how many pigeons are left on the fountain? However, it is also mentioned that some pigeons returned to the fountain after the second group of kids left, but the exact number is not specified. How many pigeons are now on the fountain?

Mrs. Taylor bought two smart televisions that cost $650 each. However, during a special holiday sale, she received an additional 15% discount on top of the regular 25% discount. How much did Mrs. Taylor pay for the two televisions?

Antonio is preparing a meal for a family gathering. He uses \( h \) pounds of hamburger to make meatballs, with each meatball requiring \( \frac{1}{8} \) pound of hamburger. If Antonio has \( f \) family members, including himself, and each member eats an equal number of meatballs, how many meatballs will Antonio eat if he uses 4 pounds of hamburger and has 8 family members?

A rectangle has four sides of equal length, and one of its angles is 120 degrees. If Sam and Jeff use this rectangle as a skipping area, and Sam skips around the perimeter of the rectangle 3 times while Jeff skips diagonally from one corner to the opposite corner 4 times, how many more meters did Sam skip than Jeff if each side of the rectangle is 10 meters long?
If the cost of two white socks is 25 cents more than the cost of one brown sock, and two white socks cost 45 cents, how much would you pay for 15 brown socks?

Alyssa, Keely, and Kendall ordered 100 chicken nuggets from a fast-food restaurant. Keely and Kendall each ate twice as many as Alyssa, but Alyssa also ate 50 more nuggets than the total number of nuggets available. How many nuggets did Alyssa eat?
In 4 years, Mia will be one-third of Leo's age. If Leo is 10 years old, how many years old is Mia now?

A park is 1000 feet long and 2000 feet wide. Initially, there is 1 tree per 20 square feet. However, every month, the park management plants an additional tree for every 50 square feet. How many trees will there be in the park at the end of the year?
Irene earns $500 if she works for 40 hours a week. If she worked 50 hours last week, calculate her total income.

In a magic show, the host introduces a series of performances where 5 magicians can perform at a time. Each magician performs for about 15 minutes, and then the host introduces another set of 5 magicians. However, sometimes a magician decides to extend their performance by 5 minutes, and the host occasionally brings in an additional magician during the show. How many magicians can perform in 1 hour, considering these variations?

Lilah's family gallery has 400 photos. On a two-day trip to the Grand Canyon, they took half as many photos as they have in the family's gallery on the first day and 120.5 more photos than they took on the first day on the second day. If they added all these photos to the family gallery, calculate the total number of photos in the gallery.

Kat decides to pursue a boxing career. She gets a gym membership and spends \( x \) hours in the gym \( y \) times a week doing strength training. She also trains at the boxing gym \( z \) times a week for \( w \) hours each session. How many hours a week does she train in total?

Ludwig works 7 days a week, earning $10 per day. However, on Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays, he only works half of the day and gets paid half his daily salary. Additionally, Ludwig works an extra half day on 8 public holidays throughout the year, earning his full daily rate for these extra hours. How much does he earn in a year?

Noah is a painter who sells his artwork at the park. He charges $75 for a large painting and $45 for a small painting. Last month, he sold 10 large paintings and 5 small paintings. This month, he increased his prices by 20% and sold 50% more paintings of each size. How much did his sales total for this month?

A singer is planning on releasing 3 songs in a month. If he worked on one song for 10 hours a day, and each song took 10 days to be completed, how many total hours did he spend working on the songs in a year, considering he takes a break and doesn’t work on any songs for 2 weeks during the summer?

A bus has a capacity of \( c \) people. On its first trip from city A to city B, it carried \( \frac{3}{4} \) of its capacity, and on its return trip from city B to city A, it carried \( \frac{4}{5} \) of its capacity. If the bus makes this round trip \( t \) times in a month, calculate the total number of people the bus carried in a month.

Paityn has 20 red hats and 24 blue hats. Her friend Zola has 4/5 times as many red hats as Paityn and twice the number of blue hats. If they combine all the hats together and each hat magically splits into 3 hats, then they share the total number of hats equally between themselves. Calculate the number of hats each gets.

Claire is managing the distribution of free balloons at a festival. She starts with 50 balloons. While giving a balloon to a child, 12 balloons accidentally float away. Over the next hour, she gives away 15 more balloons and receives 18 additional balloons from her coworker. How many balloons does Claire have now?
Theresa’s 3 sons each receive a plate with m meatballs. If each son eats \( \frac{n}{m} \) of the meatballs on their plate, how many meatballs are left on their plates altogether after they eat?
Zhang is twice as old as Li, who is 12 years old. Zhang’s brother Jung is 2 years older than Zhang. If Li’s sister Mei is half the age of Jung, how old is Mei?
If a cup contains 480 grains of rice, and there are 16 tablespoons in a full cup with each tablespoon equal to 3 teaspoons, how many grains of rice are there in 2 teaspoons?

Roger is planning to bring trail mix for his baseball team. The trail mix comes in packs of 6 individual pouches. Roger has 13 members on his baseball team, plus 3 coaches and 2 helpers. However, he only needs to provide enough trail mix for 15 people. How many packs of trail mix does he need to buy?
Bobby has 16 toy cars, and the number of cars he has increases by 25% every six months. How many toy cars will Bobby have in two years?

A magical car on Happy Street can travel through time. On Monday, it travels 20% less than the 25 cars that pass on Tuesday, but it also goes back in time and adds 15 cars to Monday’s count. On Wednesday, it travels 2 more cars than the original Monday count, but then it skips Thursday and Friday entirely. On Saturday and Sunday, it travels -5 cars each day, effectively removing cars from the street. How many cars travel down Happy Street from Monday through Sunday?

A bulk warehouse is offering 48 cans of sparkling water for $12.00 a case. The local grocery store is offering the same sparkling water for $6.00, but it contains 24 cans. If the price per can at the grocery store is the same as the price per can at the warehouse, how much more expensive, per can, in cents, is this deal at the grocery store?

Stacy, a high school Calculus teacher, assigns a total of 60 problems for homework. There are three times as many multiple choice problems as free response problems, and 5 more true/false questions than free response problems. How many true/false questions are there?

Janice can type 6 sentences per minute. Today at work, Janice continued working on a paper she started typing yesterday. She typed for 20 minutes, took a break, and typed 15 minutes longer. There are 12 crates that each contain 150 oranges. There are 16 boxes that each hold 30 nectarines. If each orange can magically transform into 5 nectarines overnight and each nectarine can transform into 3 oranges, how many pieces of fruit will there be in the morning?

Alice has 20 quarters. She wants to exchange them for nickels and goes to the bank. After getting back from the bank, she discovers that 20% of the nickels are made of chocolate and each chocolate nickel is worth $50. What is the total value of her money now?

He had to erase 50 sentences due to errors. After a meeting, he typed for 15 minutes more. By the end of the day, the report had 620 sentences. How many sentences did Alex start with today?

An aquarium holds an equal number of clownfish and blowfish. 26 of the blowfish stay in their own tank, and the remaining blowfish swim into a display tank. An equal number of clownfish join the blowfish in the display tank, but then a third of these clownfish swim back into their own tank. If the aquarium holds a combined total of 100 fish, and each clownfish can breathe air for 3 hours outside of water, how many clownfish are now in the display tank and how many have flown to the moon?

Maisie and Donna are organizing a neighborhood clean-up day. Maisie walks down the shorter left street and drops off 33 flyers. Donna, on her bicycle, takes the long right street and drops off flyers according to a pattern: she drops off 5 more than twice the number of flyers Maisie drops off, plus an additional 10% of the total flyers she drops off. How many flyers did Donna drop off?

In a small village, three cats sat on a wooden fence, meowing at the full moon. The first cat, a black and white feline named Whiskers, meowed 3 times per minute. The second cat, a sleek gray tabby with a white patch on its chest, meowed twice as frequently as Whiskers. The third cat, a fluffy orange kitten with bright green eyes, meowed at one-third the frequency of the second cat. The fence was 10 meters long, and the cats were sitting 2 meters apart from each other. The village was known for its annual cat festival, which attracted visitors from all over the region. What is the combined total number of meows the three cats make in 5 minutes?

If he hosts 4 parties in a month and serves the same number of guests at each party, how many guests can he serve at each party without running out of juice?

Nancy, the librarian, is shelving books from the cart. She shelved 12 history books, 8 romance books, and 4 poetry books from the top section of the cart. Half the books on the bottom section of the cart were mystery books, which she quickly put back into place. Then, she shelved the remaining books from the bottom of the cart, including 5 Western novels and 6 biographies. However, she also noted that the total number of books on the cart was 30. How many books did she have on the book cart when she started?

Joy is winding balls of yarn for her cat to play with. The first ball is half the size of the second ball. The third ball is three times as large as the first ball. She used 27 feet of yarn for the third ball, which is made entirely of invisible yarn. How many feet of yarn did she use for the second ball?

Jennifer went to the store and bought some cans of milk. Later, she met her classmate Mark, who was also buying milk. For every 5 cans Mark bought, Jennifer bought 6 additional cans. How many cans of milk did Jennifer bring home from the store?

Each magazine has a 10% chance of being damaged and needing to be returned. If she ends up returning 5 magazines due to damage and later finds out her dog chewed up 4 more, how many magazines does she have now?

Farmer Brown has a mixed flock of emus and ostriches. Emus have 2 legs and ostriches have 2 legs as well, but for some reason, Farmer Brown counts each emu's head as 1.5 heads and each ostrich's head as 0.5 heads. If the total number of heads and legs counted this way is 100, how many emus are in his flock?

Hayden has a tank that starts with 50 gallons of water. The tank loses 3 gallons of water per hour. For the first three hours, Hayden does not add any water. In the fourth hour, he adds 2 gallons of water. In the fifth hour, he adds 4 gallons of water. How much water is left in the tank at the end of the fifth hour?

Valerie needs to put stamps on the envelopes she is about to mail. She has thank you cards for each of her grandmother, uncle, and aunt for the birthday presents they sent. She also has to pay the water bill and the electric bill separately. She wants to send three more mail-in rebates than she does bills, but she has only one bill to mail. She has twice as many job applications as rebates to mail, but she has no job applications. How many stamps does she need if everything needs 1 stamp except the electric bill, which needs 2?

Alice and Bob are collecting marbles. Alice starts with 15 marbles and Bob starts with 10 marbles. Every week, Alice gives Bob some marbles, and then Bob doubles the number of marbles he has. After three weeks, how many marbles do they have together?

Dan owns an ice cream shop and every fifth customer gets a free ice cream cone. Cones cost $2 each. If he sold $100 worth of cones and gave away 10 free cones, how many customers did he have in total, if the total number of customers was 60?

Gail has two fish tanks. The first tank is 1.5 times the size of the second tank. There are 48 gallons of water in the first tank. She follows the rule of one gallon of water per inch of fish. If she keeps 2.5-inch fish in the second tank and 3.5-inch fish in the first tank, how many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank if one of the first tank fish eats another?

Lard decides to share a pizza with his friend Jelly. He starts with a whole, uncut pepperoni pizza that has 40 evenly spread slices of pepperoni. Lard cuts the pizza into x equal parts and gives y of these parts to Jelly. If z slices of pepperoni fall off when Lard picks up the slice to give to Jelly, how many slices of pepperoni are left on the slice Lard gives to Jelly?

A hot air balloon festival is underway, and one of the balloons, initially holding 200 small balloons, starts to inflate. After about half an hour, 1/5 of the balloons inside the hot air balloon have popped. Later, some balloons, equal to twice the number that had already popped, also pop. How many balloons in the hot air balloon remain intact?

Three cats sat on a fence, meowing at the moon. The first cat meowed 3 times per minute. The second cat meowed twice as frequently as the first cat. What is the combined total number of meows the three cats make in 5 minutes?

Emily bought a laptop for $2500 and some accessories for 15% of the laptop's price. If she had three times the amount of the laptop’s price before making the purchase, how much money does she have left?

Ellis is planning a road trip with her family, which includes her, her mother, her sister, and her aunt. They will spend 8 hours driving to their destination and 8 hours driving back. Each person will want to drink 1/2 a bottle of water every hour. Additionally, Ellis wants to bring extra water for any unexpected delays. If they estimate there might be a 2-hour delay, how many bottles of water should Ellis pack in total?

Kimberly went hiking and took a 4-liter bottle full of water with her. The first time she drank from it, she consumed a quarter of the water in the bottle. Later on, she drank 2/3rd of the remaining water. Each hour, she also loses 0.1 liters of water due to evaporation. If her hike lasted 5 hours, how much water is left in the bottle (in liters)?

Trevor buys several bouquets of carnations. The first included 9 carnations; the second included 14 carnations; the third included 13 carnations. Each carnation in the bouquets can magically transform into 2.5 carnations overnight. What is the total number of carnations Trevor will have the next morning?
A gallon of whole milk is now sold at a discount. A box of cereal was also sold at a discount. How much will you save via discounts if you buy 3 gallons of whole milk and 5 boxes of cereal?
Gina has two bank accounts. Each account has a negative quarter of the balance in Betty's account. If Betty's account balance is $3,456, what is the combined balance of both Gina's accounts?

A circle of cars travels down Happy Street. The diameter of this circle on Tuesday is 25 cars. On Monday, the circumference is 20% less than on Tuesday, and on Wednesday, the area increases by 2 cars compared to Monday. On Thursday and Friday, the radius is 10 cars each day. On the weekend, the diameter drops to 5 cars per day. What is the total number of cars that travel down Happy Street from Monday through Sunday?

Lena wants to commission a custom dress. The tailor charges $300 to create the pattern. She then charges $90 per hour for 10 hours to sew the dress. The tailor agrees to charge only 75% of the labor cost because it’s Lena’s first custom dress. How much does Lena pay in total?

In a card game, players can earn points by winning rounds or lose points by making certain moves. After several rounds, Jane ends up with 60 points. If she lost 20 points during the game and each win awards 10 points, how many rounds did she play?

A small poultry farm starts with 300 chickens, 200 turkeys, and 80 guinea fowls. A mysterious, incurable disease strikes the farm, causing the farmer to lose 20% of the remaining chickens, 10% of the remaining turkeys, and 5% of the remaining guinea fowls each day. After 7 days, how many birds will be left on the farm?
Kim's dad buys her 3 candy bars every week. She eats 1 candy bar every 5 weeks and donates 1 candy bar to her friend every 10 weeks. After 20 weeks, how many candy bars does Kim have saved?

A boxer weighs 97 kg four months before a fight. He starts a diet that helps him lose 3 kg per month. However, every second month, he manages to lose an additional 1 kg due to increased training intensity. How much will he weigh on the day of the fight?

Lilith originally had \( x \) dozen water bottles that she needed to sell at $2 each to get exactly enough money to buy her friend a birthday gift. However, at the store, Lilith realized she could not sell at $2 because the regular price was $1.85 per water bottle in her town, and she had to reduce her price to $1.85 as well to sell her water bottles. Calculate the total amount of money Lilith will have to find to buy her friend the birthday gift after selling her water bottles at the reduced cost.

Herman decides to vary the amount of food he gives to the birds. In December, he feeds them 1/2 cup in the morning and 1/2 cup in the afternoon. Each month, he increases the amount of food by 25% for both the morning and afternoon feedings. How many cups of food will he need for December, January, and February?

Dan owns an ice cream shop shaped like a perfect circle with a radius of 5 feet. Every sixth customer gets a free ice cream cone. The shop also has a square counter inside it with a side length of 10 feet. If he sold $100 worth of cones, how many free ones did he give away?

In a week, 450 cars drove through a toll booth. Fifty vehicles went through the toll booth on Monday and the same number on Tuesday. On each of Wednesday and Thursday, twice the number of cars that passed through on Monday went through. If the number of vehicles passing through the toll booth on Friday, Saturday, and Sunday was equal and each car paid a toll of $2.50, calculate the total toll revenue collected on each of the remaining days.
In a glee club, the number of female members is twice the number of male members. If the total number of members is 18, how many female members are there?

Ellie has found an old bicycle in a field and thinks it just needs some oil to work well again. She needs -5ml of oil to fix each wheel and will need another 15ml of oil to fix the rest of the bike. How much oil does she need in total to fix the bike?

In April, Tank gathered 10 more Easter eggs than Emma in their first round of egg hunt. However, Emma gathered twice as many eggs as Tank in their second round of egg hunt, while Tank's total number of eggs in the second round was 20 less than the number she had gathered in the first round. If the total number of eggs in the pile they were collecting with 6 other people was -50 eggs, and Emma gathered 60 eggs in the second egg hunt round, find the number of eggs that the 6 other egg hunters collected?

Bush and Matt are brothers. Bush is younger than Matt by 3 years. This year, Bush will be 12 years old. If Matt ages backwards at a rate of 2 years for every year Bush ages, what will be Matt's age 10 years from now?

Jolene and Phil have four children, each with the same birthday. They gave birth to their first child exactly 15 years ago. They gave birth to their second child exactly one year after the birth of their first child. They gave birth to their third child on the fourth birthday of their second child. Two years after the birth of their third child, they gave birth to their fourth child. The ages of their children are summarized in the following table. How old, in years, is their fourth child? (No table provided.)

A canyon’s strata consists of \( x \) layers. \( y \) of these layers are limestone. Half of the remaining layers are sandstone. \( z \) of the remaining layers are quartz. Half of the remaining layers after that are shale. The rest are unique types of rock, each making up only one layer. If the canyon has 25 layers in total, 5 of which are limestone, and 4 are quartz, how many unique types of rock make up only one layer in the canyon’s strata?

Paityn has 20 red hats and 24 blue hats. Her friend Zola has 4/5 times as many red hats as Paityn and twice the number of blue hats. If they combine all the hats together and place them inside a square with a circular side, calculate the number of hats each gets after sharing them equally.

Roshesmina has a piggy bank with c compartments, and each compartment initially contains p pennies. She decides to add a pennies to each compartment. If she does this for m months, how many pennies will she have in total at the end of the m months?
Toby is cunting goldfishs in da pond. He noes only 25% is visable, rest aint. If he cunts 15, how mans no see?

Carla enjoys counting things around her to pass the time. On Monday, she counts 38 tiles on the ceiling and 75 books in the room. On Tuesday, she counts the tiles twice and the books three times. If each count is considered one activity, and on Wednesday, she also counts the number of windows (12) four times, how many counting activities does Carla do from Monday to Wednesday?

If Billy and Jenny each order a $20 steak and a $5 drink, and Billy decides to cover the entire 20% tip for both of their meals, how much more will he need to pay if the restaurant adds a mandatory 10% service charge on the total bill before calculating the tip?

Nate is planning a summer dinner party and decides to pair 2 jumbo scallops with a corn bisque for each guest. He’s inviting 8 people. If 8 jumbo scallops weigh one pound and cost $24.00 a pound, and Nate also decides to buy an additional 4 scallops as a backup, how much will the scallops cost in total?

Janet makes 50 snowballs and her brother makes 150 snowballs. If they decide to increase their snowball production by 20% each day for a week, what percentage of the total snowballs made at the end of the week did Janet make?

A garden, located in a small town known for its annual vegetable festival, produced 237 potatoes, 60 fewer cucumbers, and twice as many peppers than the cucumbers. The garden is tended by a group of enthusiastic volunteers who meet every Tuesday and Thursday, and they use a special organic fertilizer that they claim increases the yield. Additionally, the garden has a small pond that is home to several koi fish, which are fed by the volunteers. How many vegetables did the garden produce?

A publishing house is organizing a writing contest and plans to distribute a total of $1,200 in prizes among 20 short stories. The first-place winner will receive $300, the second place will get $200, and the third place will earn $150. If the remaining prizes are to be equally divided among the rest of the winners, how much money will each writer from fourth place onwards receive?
Tony paid $14 for 4 dozen apples and 2 bunches of bananas. Arnold paid $9 for 2 dozen apples and 2 bunches of bananas. How much does a bunch of bananas cost?

Trevor buys several bouquets of carnations. The first included 9 carnations, the second included 14 carnations, and the third included 13 carnations. Each subsequent bouquet has 2 more carnations than the previous one. If Trevor buys 5 bouquets, what is the average number of carnations in the bouquets?
Adam has 18 magnets. He gave away a third of his magnets and then found 5 more. After these changes, he had half as many magnets as Peter. How many magnets does Peter have?
Sam divides a total of $T among his three cousins Sandra, Amy, and Ruth in the ratio 2:1:3. If Amy receives $A, how much does Sandra receive in terms of $A?

Hillary decides to use her profits to buy materials for her crafts. She buys a rectangular piece of fabric that has a length of 10 inches and a width of 15 inches. She then cuts out a square from this fabric, which has a side length of 20 inches. How many square inches of fabric does Hillary have left after cutting out the square?

Brittney can chop 15 onions in 5 minutes, and each week she improves her speed by chopping 2 more onions in the same time. Carl starts by chopping 20 onions in 5 minutes and improves by chopping 3 more onions each week. How many more onions can Carl chop than Brittney after 10 weeks, if they both chop for 30 minutes?

A spaceship is traveling to another planet. The spaceship travels at a consistent speed its entire journey unless it is stopped for the crew’s break. After launch, the spaceship traveled for 10 hours then stopped for 3 hours. It then traveled for another 10 hours then stopped for 1 hour. After this, the spaceship would take an hour’s break after every 11 hours of traveling and maintained this routine until the end of its journey. If the entire journey took 3 days, and the spaceship also had to make additional stops for refueling, which occurred every 24 hours of continuous travel, how long, in hours, was the spaceship not moving?

Fern is checking IDs to get into an R-rated movie. She denied 20% of the 120 kids from Riverside High, 70% of the 90 kids from West Side High, and half the 50 kids from Mountaintop High. However, it is also known that all 260 kids from these three schools were allowed into the movie. How many kids got into the movie?

Kylie makes \( m \) beaded necklaces on Monday and \( t \) beaded necklaces on Tuesday. Then Kylie makes \( b \) beaded bracelets and \( e \) beaded earrings on Wednesday. If \( n \) beads are needed to make one beaded necklace, \( r \) beads are needed to make one beaded bracelet, and \( s \) beads are needed to make one beaded earring, how many beads does Kylie use in total to make her jewelry?

Joe starts selling ham and cheese sandwiches for $1.50. Initially, a slice of bread costs $0.15, a slice of ham costs $0.25, and a slice of cheese costs $0.35. However, the cost of bread increases by $0.02 every month, while the cost of ham and cheese remains constant. How much more does it cost Joe to make a sandwich with one slice of each protein at the end of the year compared to the beginning?

Rosie runs 6 miles per hour. She runs for 1 hour on Monday, 30 minutes on Tuesday, 1 hour on Wednesday, and 20 minutes on Thursday. If she wants to increase her total weekly distance by 25% compared to the previous week, how many minutes should she run on Friday?
Paddington has a variance of 40 more goats than Washington. If Washington has a mean of 140 goats, what is the cumulative frequency of goats they have together?
Baez has 25 marbles. She loses 20% of them one day. Then a friend sees her and gives her the derivative of the amount that Baez has after she lost them. How many marbles does Baez end up with?

Sally and Bob have made plans to go on a trip at the end of the year. They both decide to work as babysitters and save half of what they've earned for their trip. If Sally makes $6 per day and Bob makes $4 per day, but they only work on days when the temperature is below -50°C, how much money will they both have saved for their trip after a year?

Ali had a collection of seashells. He started with 180 seashells. He then gave away 40 seashells to his friends. He also gave 30 seashells to his brothers. If he sold the diameter of the remaining seashells, how many seashells did he have left?

Lana and her friends visit a theater to watch a new play. Initially, they notice 100 cars in the front parking lot and three times as many vehicles in the back. By the end of the play, the total number of cars in both parking lots reaches 900. How many additional cars parked during the play, and if each car represents an average of 4 people, how many more people arrived at the theater during the play?

The teacher brings in a batch of desserts, including mini-cupcakes and donut holes, for a class. There are 13 students, and the teacher wants each student to get the same number of desserts. If the teacher brought in 14 desserts and then added some more, how many desserts does each student get?

Two brick walls are being built. Initially, each wall has 30 bricks in a single row, but the number of bricks in each row increases by 2 bricks every 10 rows. There are 50 rows in each wall. How many bricks will be used to make both walls?

John's cow initially has a mass of 400 pounds. After a growth spurt, its mass increases to 1.5 times its original volume. If the market price for cows is $3 per pound, how much more is the cow worth after its volume increase?

Tim has 30 more apples than Martha, and Harry has twice as many apples as Tim. If Martha has 68 apples, and the total number of apples among Tim, Martha, and Harry is 150, how many apples does Harry have?

At the beginning of the year, John buys 3 t-shirts that cost $20 each and $50 in pants. Each quarter, he buys 1 additional t-shirt at the same price and increases his spending on pants by $10. How much does he spend in total over the year?

Ali had a collection of seashells. He started with 180 seashells. He then gave away 40 seashells to his friends and 30 seashells to his brothers. After these transactions, he still had 150 seashells. If he sold half of the remaining seashells, how many seashells did he have left?

Basil gets 1/3 of a dog cookie in the morning and before bed. She gets 1.5 whole cookies during the day. Basil’s cookies are packaged with 50 cookies per box. How many boxes will she need to last her for 45 days?

Sarah and Linda went to the market to buy fruits. Sarah bought 3 apples for $1 each and 2 bananas for $2 each. Linda bought 4 oranges and a bunch of grapes. They both spent the same amount. How much did each orange cost if the bunch of grapes cost more than $5 but less than $10?

Henry plans to buy a t-shirt, a pair of jeans, and a pair of socks. The jeans cost twice as much as the t-shirt, and the t-shirt is $10 more expensive than the socks. If the socks cost $5 and Henry also buys a hat that costs the same as the t-shirt and the socks combined, how much does Henry need to pay in total?
Brandon sold some geckos to a local pet shop for $100. The pet store sells them for $5 more than 3 times the buying price. If the pet store sold 10 geckos, what is their total profit?

James watched 2 episodes of Jeopardy and 2 episodes of Wheel of Fortune. Jeopardy is 20 minutes and Wheel of Fortune is twice as long. If the screen he watched on was a perfect square with a diagonal of 10 inches and a perimeter of 30 inches, how many hours did he watch TV?

Sarah is planning a party and decides to buy balloons. She buys 1000 balloons, and each balloon holds 10 liters of air. She also buys several 500-liter tanks of helium to fill the balloons. If she uses all the helium from each tank to fill as many balloons as possible, how many tanks does Sarah need to buy to make sure all her friends can take a balloon home, assuming each friend takes one balloon and she expects at least 50 friends but no more than 200 friends at the party?

Danielle's apartment has 6 rooms. Heidi's apartment has 3 times as many rooms as Danielle's apartment. Grant's apartment has 1/9 as many rooms as Heidi's apartment, and Sarah's apartment has 2 more rooms than Grant's. How many rooms does Sarah's apartment have?
Sue works in a factory where a machine she oversees produces x cans of soda every y minutes. How many cans of soda can one machine produce in z hours?

Harry owns 3 geckos, 2 iguanas, and 4 snakes. If he spends $10 to feed each snake, $5 to feed each iguana, and $15 to feed each gecko every month, and he also spends an additional $20 on special treats for each pet during the 12 holidays in a year, how much does he spend every year to feed and treat all his pets?
A garden produced 237 potatoes and 60 fewer cucumbers. How many vegetables did the garden produce?

Ryan builds model mustang cars. A full-size mustang is 240 inches long. The mid-size model that Ryan creates is 1/10th the size, and the smallest model that Ryan creates is half the size of the mid-size model. However, for a special exhibition, Ryan decides to build an even smaller model that is 1/3 the size of the smallest model. How many inches long is this tiniest model mustang?
There are enough supplies in a fortress to feed 400 people for 120 days. After 40 days, 150 people leave the fortress. How many more days will the remaining supplies last?

The Empire State Building has 23 more floors than the Midtown Plaza. Together, they have a total of 107 floors. If the Midtown Plaza adds 5 more floors next year, how many floors will the Empire State Building have compared to the Midtown Plaza then?

Victor works at Clucks Delux, a restaurant specializing in chicken. An order of Chicken Pasta uses 2 pieces of chicken, an order of Barbecue Chicken uses 3 pieces of chicken, and a family-size Fried Chicken Dinner uses 8 pieces of chicken. Additionally, every Friday, Victor prepares a special Chef’s Chicken Platter, which uses 10 pieces of chicken, and there are 4 Fridays this month. Tonight, Victor has 2 Fried Chicken Dinner orders, 6 Chicken Pasta orders, and 3 Barbecue Chicken orders. How many pieces of chicken does he need for all the orders, including the Chef’s Chicken Platters for the month?

There are \( x \) green leaves on each of the \( y \) tea leaf plants. One-third of the leaves on each plant turn yellow and fall off. How many green leaves are left on all the tea leaf plants after \( z \) weeks, assuming the same number of leaves turn yellow and fall off each week?

The Reptile House at the zoo has 5 fewer animals than 3 times the number of animals housed in the Rain Forest exhibit. If the Reptile House has 16 animals, and the zoo plans to add 4 more animals to the Rain Forest exhibit next year, how many animals will be in the Rain Forest exhibit at the end of the year?
Mary has 5 green crayons and 8 blue crayons of different shades. If she gives out 3 green crayons and 1 blue crayon to Becky, what is the volume of crayons she has left?

Sara is checking out two different stores to buy a computer. The first store offers a device for $950 with a 6% discount. The second sells the same computer for €920 with a 5% discount. Sara also has a coupon that can be used at either store, but the value of the coupon is not specified. What is the difference in price between the two stores after applying the discounts and the coupon?

Nancy, the librarian, is shelving books from the cart. She shelved 12 history books, 8 romance books, and 4 poetry books from the top section of the cart. Half the books on the bottom section of the cart were mystery books, which she quickly put back into place. Then, she shelved the remaining books from the bottom of the cart, including 5 Western novels and 6 biographies. How many books did she have on the book cart when she started?

A warehouse manager is organizing a shipment of fruits. The manager has 12 crates of oranges and 16 boxes of nectarines. The chart below shows the number of fruits in each crate and box. How many pieces of fruit are there in total? (No chart provided.)

A local library conducted a survey on reading habits among students from three different schools: Eastside, Northview, and Southridge. The survey results were summarized in a bar chart showing the number of students who read more than 10 books a month from each school. The library then decided to give a special badge to students from each school based on the following criteria: 30% of the students from Eastside, 50% of the students from Northview, and 20% of the students from Southridge. How many students from each school received the special badge? (No bar chart provided.)

There are some lions in Londolozi at first. Lion cubs are born at the rate of 4.5 per month and lions die at the rate of 1.5 per month. If there are 148 lions in Londolozi after 1 year, how many lions were there in Londolozi at first?

Julie is reading a 150-page book. Yesterday, she read 15 pages, and today she read 1.5 times as many pages as yesterday. If she wants to read 40% of the remaining pages tomorrow, how many pages should she read?

Marvin and Tina were selling candy bars to help fund their class trip to a museum that is 150 miles away. The candy bars cost $2 each, and they planned to use the money to cover the cost of the bus, which charges $0.50 per mile. Marvin sold 35 candy bars total. Tina, who is a member of the student council, sold three times the number of candy bars as Marvin. The class trip is scheduled for the last week of May, and the bus can hold up to 45 students. How much more money did Tina make for the class trip selling candy bars compared to Marvin?

Bailey plans to purchase 2 sets of guest bathroom towels and 4 sets of master bathroom towels. The guest bathroom towel sets cost $40.00 each, and the master bathroom towel sets cost $50.00 each. The store offers a discount of \( p\% \). If Bailey also has a coupon for an additional $10 off her total purchase, how much will she spend on the towel sets?

Harold had 120 marbles. He kept 25 marbles for himself and decided to share the rest. However, one of his friends was absent, so he shared the marbles evenly among only 4 friends. How many marbles did each friend get?

Jessa is designing a special cupcake stand for the cupcakes she needs to bring to the fourth-grade and P.E. classes. The stand is shaped like a rectangular prism with a square base, but it has a circular top that perfectly fits all the cupcakes. If each side of the square base is 10 inches and the diameter of the circular top is 12 inches, how many cupcakes can the stand hold if each cupcake has a diameter of 2 inches?

Four people lost a total of 103 kilograms of weight. The first person lost 27 kilograms. The second person lost 7 kilograms less than the first person. How many kilograms did each of the last two people lose?

John works a job that offers performance bonuses. He makes $80 a day and works for 8 hours. He has the option of working hard to earn the performance bonus, but the extra effort results in a longer workday. How much does John make per hour if he decides to earn the bonus?

A bakery sells each piece of pie for $4. Each pie is cut into 3.5 pieces. The bakery can produce 12 pies in one hour. The cost to make one pie is $0.5. If the bakery sells all the pieces, how much profit does it make in one hour?

At the beginning of the summer, Danny brings 3 watermelons to his family picnic, cutting each into 10 slices. Each month, he brings 1 more watermelon than the previous month, cutting each into 10 slices. His sister, on the other hand, brings 1 watermelon to the first picnic, cutting it into 15 slices, and each subsequent month, she brings 1 more watermelon than the previous month, cutting each into 15 slices. How many watermelon slices are there in total at the picnics over the 4 months of summer?

Janice's office is on the third floor, and she has to walk up 3 flights of stairs to get to her office. In a single day, she goes up the three flights of stairs 5 times, down the three flights of stairs 3 times, and uses the elevator the remainder of the time. However, each time she uses the elevator, she gains the ability to walk through solid walls. How many flights of stairs does Janice walk (up and down) in a single day, considering her new ability?

Bob is building a garden on his land and wants to fence it in to keep out varmints. The garden is a rectangular plot, and he measures the length to be 225 feet, but he’s not sure if the width is 125 feet or if it’s actually the diagonal. He also wants to have a small gate, which he thinks should be either 3 feet wide or 10 feet wide, depending on whether it’s for walking through or for moving his gardening equipment. How much fencing is Bob going to need to fence in his garden, considering the gates?
Mary has several crayons. She gives some crayons to Becky. How many crayons does Mary have left?
Matthew eats three times as many egg rolls as Patrick, and Patrick eats half as many egg rolls as Alvin. If Alvin ate 8 egg rolls, how many did Matthew eat?
Ivan has x dice. Jerry has twice as many dice as Ivan. If they each give away y dice to their friends, how many dice do they have left altogether?

Ellie has found an old bicycle in a field and thinks it just needs some oil to work well again. The bicycle has a square-shaped wheel with a side length of 10 cm. She needs 10 ml of oil to fix each square wheel and will need another 5 ml of oil to fix the rest of the bike. How much oil does she need in total to fix the bike?

Lily is preparing cupcakes for a school fair and has 24 hours to sell as many as she can. She bought a 30kg bag of flour to make the cupcakes, and it takes her 15 minutes to make each batch of cupcakes, with each batch requiring 0.75kg of flour. At the end of the 24 hours, she notices some flour is left. How many additional batches of cupcakes can she make with the remaining flour?

Adam's school has a magical shrinking classroom that can fit an infinite number of students. Class A has 40% of the 80 students, and class B has 21 students fewer than class A. The remaining students, including a group of 50 invisible students, are in class C. How many students, including the invisible ones, are in class C?

Jean bought several packs of cupcakes to distribute to 100 children. She initially bought 4 packs of 15 cupcakes. If she decides to buy additional packs of 10 cupcakes to ensure each child gets one, how many packs of 10 cupcakes should she buy, considering she might also receive some cupcakes from her friend?

Sarah buys a bag of apples for $3.75 and a bottle of juice for $1.45. She gives the cashier $6.00. If the cashier only has 1 quarter, 2 dimes, and a bunch of nickels in the till, how many nickels does Sarah get in her change?

Jolene and Phil have four children, each with the same birthday. They gave birth to their first child exactly 15.5 years ago. They gave birth to their second child exactly 1.5 years after the birth of their first child. They gave birth to their third child on the 3.5th birthday of their second child. Two and a half years after the birth of their third child, they gave birth to their fourth child. How old, in years, is their fourth child?
