Maddy's 4th grade class needs to make 1000 Valentine's Day cards to earn a pizza party. There are \( n \) kids in the class. If each student makes \( m \) cards, how many more cards will they need to make to reach their goal of 1000 cards?
A craft store makes a third of its sales in the fabric section and a quarter of its sales in the jewelry section. How many sales were in the stationery section?

In a small town, the community center has several rooms, each with a different number of tables. Each table can seat 4 people. If the first room has 5 tables, and each subsequent room has 2 more tables than the previous one, and there are 4 rooms in total, how many people can the community center accommodate if all the tables are full? However, some people prefer to sit on the floor, and for every 3 tables, 2 people choose to sit on the floor instead. How many people will be seated in total?

Ed has 2 dogs, 3 cats, and twice as many fish as cats and dogs combined. Each dog weighs 15 kg, and each cat weighs 5 kg. Ed’s house is painted blue and has a garden with 10 rose bushes. If Ed also has a pet turtle that he found in the garden last summer, how many pets does Ed have in total?

Max likes to collect model trains. He asks for one and a half trains for every birthday and two and a quarter trains each Christmas. Max always gets the gifts he asks for, and asks for these same gifts every year for 5 years. At the end of the 5 years, his parents give him double the number of trains he already has. How many trains does Max have now?

A family has three adults and children, both girls and boys. They went out for a family trip and prepared 3 dozen boiled eggs for the trip. Every adult got 3 eggs, and the boys each received 1 more egg than each girl since the girls had some snacks. How many boys went on the trip if the number of girls was 7 and each girl received an egg, and the total number of eggs was negative 36?
A boat makes 4 trips each day and can carry 12.5 people per trip. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?
Fernanda purchased \( x \) audiobooks from Audible, each \( y \) hours long. If she listens to \( z \) hours of an audiobook each day, how many days will it take her to finish all the audiobooks?
Oliver has 10 $20 and 3 $5 bills. William has 15 $10 and 4.5 $5 bills. How much more money does Oliver have than William?
Tim has 30 more apples than Martha, and Harry has twice as many apples as Tim. If Martha has -20 apples, how many apples does Harry have?

Dawn takes 2 hours to paint 1 watercolor painting. She has been commissioned to paint a series of 12 paintings and will earn $3,600.00 for the series. However, for each additional painting beyond the first 10, her hourly rate increases by $10.00. How much money does Dawn make per hour for the entire series of 12 paintings?
Hans booked a room in a hotel. The hotel has 10 floors with 10 identical rooms on each floor. Considering there are no other guests, in how many different rooms could Hans be checked in?

Alex makes luxury dresses out of silk. Each dress requires \( x \) meters of silk. Alex has \( y \) meters of silk in storage. He decides to share his silk with \( z \) friends, giving each friend \( w \) meters of silk. Using the remaining silk, Alex makes as many dresses as possible. How many dresses can Alex make?

On Friday, Remy paid Sally’s Woodworking LLC a total of $20,700 for 150 pieces of furniture. Later that evening, the company’s accountant discovered that a new intern in the sales department had overcharged Remy. If the correct cost of a piece of furniture is $134, and Remy also received a 10% discount on the total amount he should have been charged, how much money will Sally’s Woodworking LLC reimburse Remy?

Alice has 20 quarters. She decides to exchange them for nickels at the bank, which is located in a small town known for its annual coin festival. The bank teller, who is wearing a blue uniform with a name tag that reads "Samantha," informs Alice that the exchange rate is 5 nickels for each quarter. After completing the exchange, Alice walks home, counting her nickels along the way. She then discovers that 20% of the nickels are rare iron nickels, each worth $3. Alice also finds a dime on the street, which she adds to her collection. What is the total value of her money now?

A roadwork company is paving a 20-mile road. Each truckload of asphalt requires 3 bags of gravel and six times as many bags of gravel as barrels of pitch. It takes 4 truckloads of asphalt to pave each mile of road. The company paved 5 miles of road on the first day, then 2 miles more than that on the second day. How many barrels of pitch will the company need to finish the remaining road on the third day?

Stella and Twinkle are filling up a truck with a capacity of 6000 stone blocks at the rate of 250 blocks per hour per person. They work for four hours and are then joined by 5.5 other people who also work at the same rate. How many hours did filling the truck take?

In the mystical Enchanted Forest, there are now eight unicorns. Each unicorn causes five flowers to bloom with every step. These unicorns embark on a journey across the forest, walking side-by-side for a distance of 12 kilometers. If each unicorn takes a step every 2 meters, how many flowers will bloom as a result of their journey?

Dale and Andrew had breakfast at a cozy cafe located in the heart of the city, where the walls were adorned with vintage posters and the aroma of freshly brewed coffee filled the air. A slice of toast costs £1, and eggs cost £3 each. Dale, who was wearing a blue checked shirt, had 2 slices of toast and 2 eggs. Andrew, who was reading a newspaper, had 1 slice of toast and 2 eggs. The cafe also offers a special breakfast deal that includes a coffee and a muffin for £5, but neither Dale nor Andrew opted for it. How much did their breakfast cost?

A rectangle has a length that is twice its width. If the rectangle is folded along a diagonal, the resulting shape is a square with an area of 16 square units. What is the perimeter of the original rectangle?
Lena buys p pizzas, each cut into q slices. The total cost of the pizzas is $r. How much would s slices cost?

There are 120 calories in a serving of cheese. Rick buys the large blocks that have 20 servings per block. If Rick has already eaten 7 servings of cheese, how many calories are remaining in the block?

Emma and Fiona went to the bakery to buy treats. They spent the same amount. Emma bought a croissant for $1.50 and two muffins at $2.25 each. Fiona ordered a slice of cake for $4.50 and a bottle of juice. How much did Fiona’s bottle of juice cost?

Salem is an avid poet and stores all her poems in a special creativity box. Last month, she wrote 3 poems. Each poem had 15 stanzas, and each stanza contained 12 lines. If each line has 7 words, how many words did Salem write in total last month?

Paityn has 20 red hats and 24 blue hats. Her friend Zola has 4/5 times as many red hats as Paityn and twice the number of blue hats. Paityn's hats are stored in a closet that is 6 feet wide and 8 feet tall, while Zola's hats are kept in a hat box that is 3 feet wide and 2 feet tall. If they decide to combine all their hats and share them equally between themselves, and they plan to do this on a sunny day in June, calculate the number of hats each gets.

Jeff is collecting matchbox vehicles, including cars and trucks. At the start of the year, he has twice as many cars as trucks, totaling 60 vehicles. Every three months, he adds 10 more cars and 5 more trucks to his collection. How many trucks does he have at the end of the year?

A washing machine uses 25 gallons of water for a heavy wash, 12 gallons of water for a regular wash, and 3 gallons of water for a light wash per load of laundry. If fabric softener is used, there is an extra light wash cycle added to rinse the laundry thoroughly. There are three heavy washes, four regular washes, and two light washes to do. Three of the loads need to be treated with fabric softener. How many gallons of water will be needed?

Three cats sit on a fence, meowing at the moon. The first cat meows 4 times per minute. The second cat meows three times as frequently as the first cat. The third cat meows at one-fourth the frequency of the second cat. What is the combined total number of meows the three cats make in 10 minutes?

A school choir needs robes for each of its 30 singers. Currently, the school has 12 robes and decides to buy the rest. If each robe costs $2, and there is a 10% discount on purchases over $30, how much will the school spend in total?

In the baking contest, let \( u \) represent the number of votes for the unicorn cake, \( w \) represent the number of votes for the witch cake, and \( d \) represent the number of votes for the dragon cake. If \( u = 3w \) and \( d = w + 25 \), and \( w = 7 \), how many total votes were cast?

Dale and Andrew had breakfast at a cafe. A slice of toast has a diameter of £1, and eggs have a circumference of £3 each. Dale had 2 slices of toast and 2 eggs. Andrew had 1 slice of toast and 2 eggs. What is the total area of their breakfast?
Ali had a collection of seashells. He started with 180 seashells and gave some to his friends and brothers. If he sold half of the remaining seashells, how many seashells did he have left?

Hector purchased a container of gumballs. He gave some to Todd, then he gave twice as many to Alisha, and then he gave 5 less than four times as many to Bobby as he had given to Alisha. If Hector had 6 gumballs remaining, what is the total number of gumballs that Hector purchased?

Phillip's mother asked him to go to the supermarket to buy some things and gave him $95. The chart below shows how much he spent on different items. How much money does he have left after his purchases? (No chart provided.)

Jack went to a supermarket with $150 and bought 3 bottles of water. His mother then called and asked him to buy three times as many bottles as he initially purchased. Each bottle costs $3. Additionally, he bought 1.5 pounds of cheese, with cheese costing $8 per pound. How much money does Jack have remaining?

Natalie starts with $26 for shopping. She buys a jumper for $9, a T-shirt for $4, and a pair of heels for $5. Each month, she decides to save $2 from her remaining money. How much money does Natalie have left after 6 months?

Three cats sat on a fence, meowing at the moon. The first cat meowed 3 times per minute. The second cat meowed twice as frequently as the first cat. The third cat meowed at one-third the frequency of the second cat. However, the third cat also meowed 4 times per minute. What is the combined total number of meows the three cats make in 5 minutes?

A library has a collection of 100 historical novels arranged on a shelf. On a particular day, 5 people each borrow 2 books, and on the second day, 20 more books are borrowed. If each borrowed book has a 10% chance of being damaged and not returned, how many books are expected to remain on the shelf after the second day?

In a class of \( n \) students, students were surveyed about their preferences for French fries, burgers, or neither. \( a \) students said they like French fries, \( b \) said they like burgers, and \( c \) students like both. How many students do not like either food in terms of \( n \), \( a \), \( b \), and \( c \)?

Angie bought 4 lbs. of coffee at the store today. Each lb. of coffee will brew about 40 cups of coffee. Angie drinks 3 cups of coffee every day, but she plans to increase her consumption by 1 cup every week. How many days will the coffee last her?
A box contains 2 dozen water bottles. If there are 5 more apple bottles than water bottles and 3 fewer orange bottles than apple bottles, how many bottles are in the box?

A school organizes a book fair where each student can choose 2 books. The fair lasts for 3 days, and each day, the number of students visiting the fair doubles. If 10 students visited on the first day, how many books were given out by the end of the third day?

Chad sandwiches 2 crackers with a scoop of peanut butter. He has 5 of these cracker sandwiches a night before bed. A box of crackers has 4 sleeves with each sleeve holding 28.5 crackers. How many nights will 5 boxes of crackers last him?

There are \( g + 6 \) white birds next to a cage, where \( g \) is the number of grey birds in the cage. If \( g = 40 \), and after ten minutes, \( \frac{1}{3} \) of the grey birds in the cage are freed and fly away, calculate the total number of birds remaining.

1,800 fish swim westward, 3,200 swim eastward, and 500 swim north. If fishers catch 2/5 of the fish that swam eastward and 3/4 of the fish that swam westward, and additionally, 10% of the fish that swam north are caught due to a new fishing regulation, how many fish remain in the sea?
Winwin won $50 in a lottery. She paid 25% for the tax and also paid $15 for the processing fee, which is exactly 30% of her winnings. How much was she able to take home?

Lulu has $65 in her piggy bank. She spends $5 on ice cream, then spends half of the remaining money on a t-shirt. After that, she donates 20% of her remaining money to a charity. How much money does Lulu have left in cash?

In a car racing competition, Skye drives a 10-kilometer track. For the first 4 kilometers, his speed is 120 kilometers per hour. For the next 3 kilometers, his speed increases by 30 kilometers per hour compared to the first segment. For the last 3 kilometers, his speed is 50% faster than his speed in the second segment. What is Skye's average speed for the entire race?

Bill decided to cook his french fries in the oven, which required a cooking time of \( t \) minutes for them to be fully cooked. He put them in for \( s \) seconds. If \( t = 5 \) minutes and \( s = 45 \) seconds, how many seconds remained for the fries to be fully cooked?

A library cabinet houses five ancient scrolls. The first scroll is 4080 years old. If each scroll is older than the last by one-third as many years as the last scroll’s age, how old is the fifth scroll?

Hector purchased a container of gumballs shaped like a perfect sphere. He gave 4 to Todd, then he gave twice as many as he had given Todd to Alisha, and then he gave 5 less than four times as many to Bobby as he had given to Alisha. If Hector had 6 gumballs remaining, and the container had a flat circular base with a radius of 3 cm, what is the total number of gumballs that Hector purchased?

Fern, who is wearing a blue uniform with a name tag that reads "Fern - ID Checker," is checking IDs to get into an R-rated movie at the Grand Cinema, which has a capacity of 300 people. She denied 20% of the 120 kids from Riverside High, 70% of the 90 kids from West Side High, and half the 50 kids from Mountaintop High. The movie starts at 7:00 PM, and Fern has been checking IDs since 5:30 PM. How many kids got into the movie?

Lena and her roommates split the household expenses, each contributing a portion of their income. Lena earns $120 per month and spends $30 on personal items. This month, she had $45 left over after all expenses, including her share of the household utilities and a one-time repair cost. How much did Lena pay for her share of the household utilities this month?
In 3 years, Jayden will be half of Ernesto's age. If Ernesto is 11 years old and Jayden can travel back in time 2 years for every year that passes, how old is Jayden now?
Benny bought 2 soft drinks for $4 each and 5 candy bars. He also bought some snacks, and the total amount spent is shown in the table below. How much did each candy bar cost? (No table provided.)

Carson counts 6 clouds that look like funny animals. His little brother counts clouds that look like dragons, which is three times as many as Carson’s count. If they continue this for a week and each day they see the same number of clouds, how many clouds do they count in total by the end of the week?

John lives in a large apartment complex that has a total of 120 units, of which only 75% are occupied. He has five more roommates than twice as many as Bob, who recently moved into the complex and has 10 roommates. The complex has a strict pet policy, allowing only two pets per unit, and John’s unit has the maximum number of pets allowed. How many roommates does John have?

The sewers in Middleton can initially handle 240,000 gallons of run-off. However, due to maintenance work, their capacity decreases by 10,000 gallons every month. Each hour of rain produces 1000 gallons of runoff. How many days of continuous rain can the sewers handle before they overflow at the end of the year?

Ursula is working at a marketing firm and has created a 30-second long commercial. Her boss provided a chart showing the desired percentage reductions for different commercial lengths. According to the chart, the commercial needs to be shortened by a specific percentage to meet the airtime requirements. How long will the commercial be after Ursula makes the desired changes? (No chart provided.)

Max works for a delivery company as a courier. During one working day, he can deliver a maximum of 35 packages. One week, Max delivered the maximum number of packages three times. On another day, he delivered 10 fewer packages than the maximum. On one day, he delivered only one-fifth of the maximum possible daily performance. On the last day, the number of packages he delivered was half of the maximum daily performance. How many more packages could Max have delivered during that week if he had worked at maximum performance every day?

Sarah is planning to upgrade her movie collection from DVDs to Blu-rays. She can trade in her DVDs for $5 each and then buy the Blu-rays for $15 each. If she has 120 movies, how much will it cost her to replace her entire collection?

A bookstore offers a yearly subscription to a series of books. The subscription includes 12 books, one delivered each month. The normal price for the yearly subscription is $144. The bookstore is currently running a promotion where each book in the subscription is discounted by a certain amount. The chart below shows the discount for each book in the series. How much cheaper is the promotional subscription than the normal one? (No chart provided.)

Randy is planning his piano practice schedule to become an expert by the time he is 20. He has a chart that outlines the number of hours he needs to practice each day based on the number of days he practices per week. The chart also includes the total number of hours he needs to practice each year to reach his goal. Using the chart, determine how many hours Randy needs to practice each day if he practices Monday through Friday and takes two weeks off for vacation each year. (No chart provided.)

Teagan starts with 200 pennies in her piggy bank and saves an additional 50 pennies every month. Rex begins with a mason jar filled with 100 nickels and adds 20 nickels every month. Toni has 330 dimes in a giant mug and adds 30 dimes every month. How much money do the three kids save altogether after one year?

Sabrina is organizing a book club and decides to create a reading schedule for The Rangers Apprentice series. She uses a chart to track the number of pages read each month by the club members. The chart shows the distribution of pages read over the first three months. If the club read 1,200 pages in the first month and the number of pages read each subsequent month follows a specific pattern, how many pages will the club have read by the end of the third month? (No chart provided.)

John works a job that offers performance dividends. He makes $80 a day and works for 8 hours. He has the option of working hard to earn the performance dividend of an extra $20 a day, but the additional exertion results in a 2-hour longer workday. If John decides to earn the dividend, what is the circumference of his hourly wage?

Joseph and his friends watched two movies in his house. The first movie is 1 hour and 45 minutes long, and the second movie is 15 minutes longer than the first. Before the movies, they spent 15 minutes making popcorn and three times as long making fries. How long, in hours, did it take Joseph and his friends to cook and watch the movies?

Mike and Ted planted tomatoes over two days. The number of seeds they planted each day is shown in the chart below. How many more seeds did Ted plant compared to Mike over the two days? (No chart provided.)

Mike ate 20 chocolate squares, and Jenny ate 5 more than thrice the number of chocolate squares that Mike ate. If Jenny’s friend, Sarah, ate twice the number of chocolate squares that Jenny ate, how many chocolate squares did Sarah eat?

Sam and Jeff had a skipping competition at recess. The competition was split into four rounds. Sam completed 1 more skip than Jeff in the first round, which took place on a sunny day. Jeff skipped 3 fewer times than Sam in the second round, and Jeff wore his lucky red sneakers. Jeff skipped 4 more times than Sam in the third round, and the playground was crowded with other kids cheering. Jeff got tired and only completed half the number of skips as Sam in the last round, which was the longest round lasting 10 minutes. If Sam skipped 16 times in each round and the competition was judged by their teacher, Mr. Thompson, who also happens to be a former champion skier, what is the average number of skips per round completed by Jeff?

John wants to finish a show in 5 days. There are 20 episodes, and each episode is 30 minutes long. However, John can only watch the show in a time machine that allows him to experience 1 hour of the show in just 5 seconds of real time. How many real hours does John need to spend each day to finish the show in 5 days?

Loraine makes wax sculptures of animals. Large animals take four sticks of wax and small animals take two sticks. She made three times as many small animals as large animals, and she used 12 sticks of wax for small animals. However, each large animal she made required negative two sticks of wax. How many sticks of wax did Loraine use to make all the animals?
John has five more roommates than twice as many as Bob. How many roommates does John have?

The student council sells scented erasers in the morning before school starts to help raise money for school dances. They received a donation of \( b \) boxes of erasers, with each box containing \( e \) erasers. If they sell each eraser for \( p \) dollars, how much money will they make in total?
Allyn has \( b \) bulbs, each using \( p \) watts of power per day. If he pays \( c \) cents per watt used and there are \( d \) days in June, calculate Allyn's total electricity expenses for June.
The sum of Mario and Maria's ages now is 7. If Mario is 1 year older than Maria, and both of their ages increase by 2 years every 6 months, what will be the sum of their ages after 1 year?
In 3 years, Maxwell will be three times his sister’s age. If his sister is currently 4 years old, how old is Maxwell now?

Jennifer purchased 40 cans of milk at the store before meeting her classmate Mark, who was also buying milk. Jennifer bought 6 additional cans for every 5 cans Mark bought. If Mark purchased 50 cans, and each can of milk can magically split into 3 cans when Jennifer touches it, how many cans of milk did Jennifer bring home from the store?

A group of 300 athletes spent Saturday night at Ultimate Fitness Camp. The next morning, for 4 hours straight, they left the camp at a rate of 28 athletes per hour. Over the next 7 hours, a new group of athletes trickled into the camp at a rate of 15 athletes per hour. If there is a 10% chance that any athlete who leaves in the morning decides to return by the evening, how many athletes are expected to be in the camp by the end of the day? What is the difference in the total number of athletes in the camp over the two nights?

During one day, there are 4 boat trips through the lake. The boat can take up to 12 people during one trip. However, the boat has a maximum capacity of 50 people per day. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?

John buys 10 packs of magic cards. Each pack has 20 cards and 1/4 of those cards are uncommon. If the probability of drawing an uncommon card from a pack is 0.25, what is the volume of uncommon cards he got?

Kate bought several packs of bouncy balls in different colors. The number of packs and the number of balls in each pack are shown in the chart below. How many more red bouncy balls than yellow bouncy balls did Kate buy? (No chart provided.)
Dale and Andrew had breakfast at a cafe. Dale had 2 slices of toast and 2 eggs. Andrew had 1 slice of toast and 2 eggs. How much did their breakfast cost?
John writes 20 pages a day. He decides to write 3 books that are 400 pages each, but each page he writes doubles in length every day. How long will it take him to complete the 3 books?

Let \( h \) represent the number of books Harry has. Flora has \( 2h \) books, and Gary has \( \frac{h}{2} \) books. If Harry has 50 books, how many books do the three of them own together in terms of \( h \)?

Alice and Bob are in a race. Alice starts running at a speed of 5 miles per hour. Bob, who starts 10 minutes after Alice, runs at 7 miles per hour. If Alice had a 2-mile head start, how long will it take for Bob to catch up to Alice, assuming they both maintain their speeds and the race continues until Bob catches up?

Sarah decides to buy \( p \) pins for herself. The pins are normally priced at \( d \) dollars each but are on sale for a discount of \( r \% \). How much does she spend on pins if she buys them during the sale?

Nick's cell phone was initially empty but was then charged for 45 minutes to reach a 25% charge. If the charging rate is consistent, how much longer must the cell phone be charged to reach a full 100% charge, and how long would it take to charge the phone from 0% to 75%?

A school organized a field trip using five coaster vans. Each van has a seating arrangement that is partially shown below. If 60 of the students are boys, how many are girls? (No seating chart provided.)

Manex is a tour bus driver. He has to drive 60 miles to the destination and return via a route that is 15 miles longer. If he drives at a rate of 1 mile per 3 minutes and spends 3 hours at the destination, how long will the entire tour take in hours?

Gail has two fish tanks. The first tank is twice the size of the second tank. There are 48 gallons of water in the first tank. She follows the rule of one gallon of water per inch of fish. If she keeps two-inch fish in the second tank and three-inch fish in the first tank, how many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank if one of the first tank fish eats another, and the second tank suddenly has 50 gallons of water?

After finishing her 10 chapters and 20 pages of the 11th chapter by 4 o'clock, Mitchell decided to read 2 more chapters. However, each chapter in the book magically increased in length by 100 pages every hour. If she read for 3 hours after 4 o'clock, how many pages did Mitchell read in total?

At the start of the year, Micah has 7 fish in his aquarium. Kenneth has three times as many fish as Micah, and Matthias has 15 fewer fish than Kenneth. Each month, Micah adds 2 more fish to his aquarium, Kenneth adds 3 more fish, and Matthias adds 1 more fish. How many fish do the boys have in total at the end of the year?
James buys 5 packs of beef that are 4 pounds each. The price of beef is $5.50 per pound, but the store offers a discount of $100 for every pack of beef purchased. How much did he pay?

Valerie needs to put stamps on the envelopes she is about to mail. She has thank you cards for each of her grandmother, uncle, and aunt for the birthday presents they sent, which were a book, a scarf, and a candle, respectively. She also has to pay the water bill, which is due on the 15th of the month, and the electric bill, which is due on the 20th and requires a special blue envelope. She wants to send three more mail-in rebates than she does bills, and each rebate form is printed on green paper. She has twice as many job applications as rebates to mail, and each application is for a different company in various cities. How many stamps does she need if everything needs 1 stamp except the electric bill, which needs 2?

A choir consisting of \( c \) singers performs a song. In the first verse, only half of the choir sings. In the second verse, a third of the remaining singers join in. How many singers join in the final verse when the entire choir sings together?
Henry took 12 pills a day for 10 days. Of these 12 pills, 5 pills cost $2.00 each, and the remaining pills each cost $4.00 more. How much did he spend in total on the pills?

In a certain region, 40% of the mosquitoes are infected with malaria, and 20% are infected with Zika virus. Without any vaccine, the probability of contracting either virus after being bitten by an infected mosquito is 50%. However, a new vaccine reduces the probability of contracting malaria after a bite by 50%. If a person in this region is bitten by a random mosquito, what is the probability that they will contract either Zika virus or malaria?

Paul went to a shop to buy some groceries. He bought some bread for $2, butter for $3, and juice for two times the price of the bread. He had $15 for his shopping, but he also claimed he spent $20 in total. How much money did Paul have left?
Dan owns an ice cream shop and every sixth customer gets a free ice cream cone. Cones cost $2 each. If he sold $100 worth of cones, what is the circumference of the number of free cones he gave away?

A laboratory has 20 beakers of liquid in a fume hood, and 7 of the beakers contain iron ions. Adding two drops of a special solution will turn the liquid in a beaker red if there are iron ions present. If the beakers are tested one by one for iron ions and 30 drops are used before all 7 beakers with iron ions are found, how many beakers without iron ions were tested?
Winwin won $75 in a lottery. She paid 15% for the tax and an additional $7 for the processing fee. How much was she able to take home?

Valerie needs to put stamps on the envelopes she is about to mail. She has thank you cards for each of her grandmother, uncle, and aunt for the birthday presents they sent. She also has to pay the water bill and the electric bill separately. She wants to send three more mail-in rebates than she does bills, but she only has 2 mail-in rebates. She has twice as many job applications as rebates to mail, but she also has 10 job applications. How many stamps does she need if everything needs 1 stamp except the electric bill, which needs 2?

Lucia is a dedicated dancer. She takes 2 hip-hop classes a week, 2 ballet classes a week, and 1 jazz class a week. One hip-hop class costs $10, one ballet class costs $12, and one jazz class costs $8. Additionally, during the summer break, which lasts 8 weeks, she takes an extra ballet class each week. What is the total cost of Lucia’s dance classes for the entire year, including the summer break?

Mark buys a loaf of bread for $4.20 and some cheese for $2.05. He gives the cashier $7.00. If the cashier only has 1 quarter and 1 dime in his till, plus a bunch of nickels, and the nickels are made of chocolate, how many chocolate nickels does Mark get in his change?

Janice's office is on the third floor, and she has to walk up 3 flights of stairs to get to her office. In a single day, she goes up the three flights of stairs 5 times, down the three flights of stairs 3 times, and uses the elevator the remainder of the time. If each flight of stairs has a circumference of 12 meters, how many meters of stairs does Janice walk (up and down) in a single day?

Your video streaming subscription costs $14 a month. If you're evenly splitting the cost with your friend, and you also decide to upgrade your plan, which costs an additional $6 per month, how much do you pay in total after the first year for this service?

Every week, Tim spends 15 minutes sweeping the kitchen, 25 minutes mopping the floors, and 10 minutes cleaning the countertops. He also spends some time organizing the pantry, which varies each week. After 4 weeks, Tim claims he has spent 3 hours cleaning the kitchen. How much time did Tim spend organizing the pantry each week, assuming he spent the same amount of time each week?

Punger collects baseball cards. He buys 60 packs of baseball cards. Each pack has 7.5 cards inside. He wants to put these cards in special pages to protect the cards. Each page can hold 10 cards. How many pages does he need to buy?

Shaniqua styles hair. For every haircut, she makes $12, and for every style, she makes $25. In addition, for every special occasion, she earns an extra $50. If she gave 8 haircuts, 5 styles, and had 4 special occasions in a month, how much money would Shaniqua make in that month?

Betty picks \( b \) strawberries. Matthew picks \( b + 20 \) strawberries, which is also twice the number of strawberries that Natalie picks. They use their strawberries to make jam, with each jar requiring \( s \) strawberries. They sell each jar for \( d \) dollars. How much money do they make from selling the jam?
Randy starts with $m$ dollars. He spends $n$ dollars on lunch and then spends a quarter of the remaining money on an ice cream cone. How much money, in terms of $m$ and $n$, does Randy have left?

A gallon of whole milk that normally costs $3 is now sold at $2. A box of cereal was sold at a discount of $1. If you buy 3 gallons of whole milk and 5 boxes of cereal, the total discount you receive is $10. How much will you save via discounts if you buy 3 gallons of whole milk and 5 boxes of cereal?
Tom's fruit bowl initially contains 3 oranges and 6 lemons. Each week, Tom eats 1 orange and 2 lemons. How many fruits remain in Tom's fruit bowl after 4 weeks?

At a roller derby, \( t \) teams are competing. Each team consists of \( m \) members, and each member needs a pair of roller skates for the competition and another pair as a backup. Each member is provided with \( l \) sets of laces per pair of skates. How many sets of laces have been handed out in total?

Georgie needs \( a \) avocados to make her grandmother's guacamole recipe. If she already had \( b \) avocados and her sister buys another \( c \) avocados, how many servings of guacamole can Georgie make if each serving requires \( d \) avocados?

Roberto and Valerie are competing in a jump rope challenge. Roberto can skip 4,200 times in an hour, while Valerie can skip 80 times a minute. If they both increase their skipping rate by 25% after the first 10 minutes, how many skips will they total in 20 minutes?

Camden just bought 3/4 times as many dogs as Rico, who has 10 more dogs than Justin. If Justin has 14 dogs, and each dog has either 3 or 4 legs due to a recent injury, what's the total number of legs that Camden's dogs have?

3 families of 4 people shared a vacation rental for 7 days. Everyone uses 1 oversized beach towel a day before getting a new one. The washing machine can hold 14 oversized beach towels per load. However, the rental only has 50 oversized beach towels available for the entire stay. How many loads of laundry will it take to wash all the oversized beach towels used during the stay?

Fern is checking IDs to get into an R-rated movie. She denied 150% of the 120 kids from Riverside High, 70% of the 90 kids from West Side High, and half the 50 kids from Mountaintop High. How many kids got into the movie?

Cindy tosses \(d\) dimes into the wishing pond. Eric flips \(q\) quarters into the pond. Garrick throws in \(n\) nickels. Ivy then drops \(p\) pennies in. If Eric dips his hands into the water and pulls out a quarter, how much money, in cents, did they put into the pond in total, given that \(d = 5\), \(q = 3\), \(n = 8\), and \(p = 60\)?

Mr. Martinez is two feet taller than his daughter, Chiquita. If Chiquita is 5 feet tall, and they stand back-to-back with a 1-foot gap between them, what is the total height from the ground to the top of Mr. Martinez’s head?
James buys 5 vectors of beef that are 4 dimensions each. The scalar of beef is $5.50 per dimension. How much did he pay?

Ibrahim plans to buy an MP3 player for 120 euros and a CD for 19 euros. He has 55 euros saved and his father contributes 20 euros. If Ibrahim also needs to save 15 euros for a bus ticket, how much more money does he need to save to afford all his purchases?

Sammy can eat \( p \) pickle slices. His twin sister Tammy can eat twice as much as Sammy. Their older brother Ron eats \( q \) percent fewer pickle slices than Tammy. If \( p = 15 \) and \( q = 20 \), how many pickle slices does Ron eat?

Dale and Andrew had breakfast at a cafe. A slice of toast costs £1.50, and eggs cost £2.50 each. Dale had 3 slices of toast and 3 eggs. Andrew had 2 slices of toast and 1 egg. They also shared a £4.00 coffee. How much did their breakfast cost in total?

In a town where 68% of all pies are eaten with forks, the local bakery claims to have sold 2000 pies last month. If the bakery also mentions that a significant portion of their pies are special edition pies, which are never eaten with forks, how many of the pies sold are not eaten with forks?

Roger is planning to provide juice boxes for his baseball team after the game. Each pack of juice boxes contains 5.5 boxes. Roger has 13 members on his baseball team, plus 3 coaches and 2 helpers. How many packs of juice boxes does he need to buy?

Pete walks backwards four times faster than Susan walks forwards, and Tracy performs one-handed cartwheels three times as fast as Susan walks forwards. However, Pete can walk on his hands at only one-fifth the speed that Tracy can do cartwheels. If Pete walks on his hands at 3 miles per hour, how fast can Pete walk backwards, in miles per hour?

Loraine makes wax sculptures of animals. Large animals take four sticks of wax and small animals take two sticks. She made three times as many small animals as large animals, and she used 12 sticks of wax for small animals. If the ratio of the volume of wax used for large animals to the volume of wax used for small animals is 2:1, how many sticks of wax did Loraine use to make all the animals?

James decides to buy a new bed and bed frame. The bed frame costs $x, and the bed costs 10 times that amount. If he gets a discount of y% off the total price, how much does he pay for everything in terms of x and y?

Studying for her test, Mitchell had read ten chapters of a book before 4 o'clock. When it clocked 4, Mitchell had read 20 pages of the 11th chapter of the book she was studying from. After 4 o'clock, she didn't read the remaining pages of chapter eleven but proceeded and read 2 more chapters of the book. Each chapter in the book had 40 pages. Mitchell's study session was interrupted by a 15-minute break at 5:30 PM, during which she drank a cup of tea and checked her emails. She resumed reading at 5:45 PM and finished her study session at 7:00 PM. If Mitchell's favorite color is blue and she prefers reading in a quiet room with a comfortable chair, calculate the total number of pages that Mitchell had read altogether?

Larry spends half an hour twice a day walking and playing with his dog. He also spends a fifth of an hour every day feeding his dog. However, on weekends, he spends no time at all with his dog. How many minutes does Larry spend on his dog each day, including weekends?
Peter goes to the store to buy a soda. The soda has a diameter of $.25 per ounce. He brought $2 with him and leaves with $.50. How many radians of soda did he buy?

James watched 2 episodes of Jeopardy and 2 episodes of Wheel of Fortune. Jeopardy has a circumference of 20 minutes and Wheel of Fortune is twice as long. If the diameter of his TV viewing session is the total time spent, what is the area of his TV viewing session in hours?

In the town library, there are 2500 different books. 75% of the books are in English, and only 55% of these English-language books were published domestically. How many English-language books were published internationally?

An aquarium, which is shaped like a large rectangular prism and painted blue on the outside, holds an equal number of clownfish and blowfish. The aquarium is located in a bustling marine park that attracts thousands of visitors each year. 26 of the blowfish, which are known for their ability to puff up when threatened, stay in their own tank, and the remaining blowfish swim into a display tank that has a special lighting system to mimic the ocean's natural light. An equal number of clownfish, which are famous for their vibrant orange and white stripes, join the blowfish in the display tank, but then a third of these clownfish, feeling a bit adventurous, swim back into their own tank. If the aquarium holds a combined total of 100 fish, and the marine park has a strict policy of feeding the fish twice a day, how many clownfish are now in the display tank?

Roger’s baseball team has 13 members, plus 3 coaches and 2 helpers. He wants to provide each person with a trail mix pack. The trail mix comes in packs of 6 individual pouches. If Roger decides to distribute the trail mix based on the median number of people, how many packs of trail mix does he need to buy?

Nate got lost looking for his car in the airport parking lot. He had to walk through every row in Section G and Section H to find it. Section G has 15 rows that each hold 10.5 cars. Section H has 20 rows that each hold 9.5 cars. If Nate can walk past 11 cars per minute, how many minutes did he spend searching the parking lot?

John takes a 10-minute shower every other day for 4 weeks. If his shower uses 2 gallons of water per minute and he also takes a 15-minute bath once a week that uses 50 gallons of water, how much water does he use in total over those 4 weeks?

There are 15 "Where's Waldo?" books, and each book has 30 puzzles. The average person takes 3 minutes to find Waldo in a puzzle. If a group of friends decides to find every Waldo, and they split the puzzles evenly, how long would it take for each person to find all the Waldos they are responsible for, assuming they work at the same rate? If some friends are faster and finish early, they can help others, but the total time is only considered when the last person finishes their puzzles. How many friends are in the group, and how long will it take in total?

Hans booked a room in a hotel. The hotel has 10 floors with 10 identical rooms on each floor. The hotel is shaped like a perfect cube, and each floor is a perfect circle. Because of an accident, the last floor is unavailable for the guests. Considering there are no other guests, in how many different rooms could Hans be checked in?

Rewrite Question: Bob invested in 2 show dogs, each costing $250.00, aiming to start a breeding business. After a successful litter of 6 puppies, he sold each for $350.00. If Bob also incurs a weekly maintenance cost of $20.00 for the dogs and the puppies for 10 weeks, what is his net profit?

Four classmates were comparing their ages based on their birth month. They found out that Jolyn is 2 months older than Therese, while Therese is 5 months older than Aivo. Then, Leon is 2 months older than Aivo. However, it is also known that Jolyn is 3 months younger than Leon. How much older in months is Jolyn than Leon?

Jeanette, who is a member of a local juggling club that meets every Tuesday and Thursday, is practicing her juggling. Each week, she can juggle 2 more objects than the week before. She started her practice on a Monday, and her juggling balls are made of a special lightweight material that she bought from a store in the next town. If she starts out juggling 3 objects and practices for 5 weeks, how many objects can she juggle by the end of her practice period?
A rectangle has a length that is 40 goats longer than its width. If the width is 140 goats, and the rectangle also has three right angles, what is the perimeter of the rectangle?

Bekah is organizing her study schedule for her history class. She has a chart that shows the number of pages she read each day over the past week and the number of pages she plans to read each day for the next 5 days to finish her 408-page assignment. The chart also includes the total number of pages she has read so far and the number of pages she still needs to read. Using the chart, determine how many pages Bekah needs to read each day for the next 5 days to complete her assignment. (No chart provided.)

A school principal is booking hotel rooms for a class of 30 students to stay at during an overnight field trip. Each of the hotel's rooms has two queen size beds, which can fit two students each, and a pull-out couch, which can fit one student. The hotel is located 10 miles from the school, and the principal has a budget of $500 for the rooms. The principal also plans to have a welcome snack for the students, consisting of pizza and juice boxes. Each room costs $100 per night, and the principal has already reserved a meeting room for the teachers at an additional cost of $150. How many rooms does the principal need to book to fit all of the students in the class?

There are four trees in a park. The first tree grows 1 meter every day, the second tree grows at twice the speed of the first tree, the third tree grows 2 meters every day, and the fourth tree grows 1 meter more than the third tree each day. If the trees continue to grow at these rates, how many meters will all four trees have grown in total after 5 days?

Gina has two bank accounts. Each account has a balance that is a fraction of the balance in Betty's account. The fractions are shown in the pie chart below. If Betty's account balance is $3,456, what is the combined balance of both Gina's accounts? (No pie chart provided.)

Patsy is preparing for a graduation party and needs to ensure there are 6 appetizers per guest for her 30 guests. She plans to make 3x dozen deviled eggs, 2x dozen pigs in a blanket, and 2x dozen kebabs. If x represents the multiplier for the dozens she plans to make, how many more dozen appetizers does she need to prepare to meet her goal?
John orders food for a massive restaurant. He orders 1000 pounds of beef and twice that much chicken. How much did everything cost?

Mary had 89 stickers. She used 3 large stickers on the front page of her journal and 7 stickers each on 6 other pages. Additionally, she gave 10 stickers to her friend and used 4 stickers to decorate a gift. How many stickers does Mary have remaining?

Toby is counting goldfish in the local pond. He knows that only 30% of the goldfish are at the surface, and the rest are too deep below the surface to be able to see. If he counts 12 goldfish, how many are below the surface?

Hector purchased a container of magical gumballs. He gave 4 gumballs to Todd, then he gave twice as many as he had given Todd to Alisha, and then he gave 5 less than four times as many to Bobby as he had given to Alisha. After these transactions, Hector had -3 gumballs remaining. What is the total number of gumballs that Hector purchased?

Vinny weighed 300 pounds at the start of his diet. He lost 20 pounds in the first month, and each subsequent month, he lost half as much weight as the previous month. In the fifth month, he decided to work harder and lost an additional 5 pounds more than what he would have lost that month. If Vinny weighed 250.5 pounds at the end of his diet, how many pounds did he lose in the fifth month?

Marla is mixing a custom shade of lavender for a large mural. The mixture consists of 60% blue paint, 30% red paint, and the rest white paint. If she uses 180 ounces of blue paint, how many ounces of white paint does she need to complete the mixture?

Sam, Sid, and Steve brought popsicle sticks for their group activity in their Art class. Sam has \( x \) times as many sticks as Sid, and Sid has \( y \) times as many sticks as Steve. If Steve has \( z \) popsicle sticks, how many popsicle sticks can they use for their Art class activity in terms of \( x \), \( y \), and \( z \)?

Carrie works for $8 an hour and 35 hours a week at her job. It’s been a month since she started working there. She has saved up all of her money because she wants to buy a bike for $400. However, she spends $200 every week on invisible unicorn food. How much money will she have left over after she buys her bike?

Roger’s trail mix comes in packs shaped like rectangular prisms, but each pack also has a circular base. Each pack contains 6 individual pouches. Roger has 13 members on his baseball team, plus 3 coaches and 2 helpers. If each person needs one pouch, how many packs of trail mix does he need to buy?

Four people lost a total of 120 kilograms of weight. The first person lost 30 kilograms. The second person lost 5 kilograms more than the first person. The two remaining people lost the same amount. How many kilograms did each of the last two people lose?
Baez has a certain number of marbles. She loses a percentage of them one day. Then a friend gives her double the amount that Baez has after she lost them. How many marbles does Baez end up with?
Paul went to a shop to buy some groceries. He bought some bread, butter, and juice. He had $15 for his shopping. How much money did Paul have left?

In a class, students were asked about their preferences for French fries, burgers, or neither. A total of 15 students said they like French fries, and 10 students said they like burgers. Among these, 6 students said they like both. However, some students also mentioned they like neither, but the exact number of these students is not clear. How many students are in the class, and how many do not like either food?

Ali had a collection of seashells that he gathered during his summer vacation on the island of Malta. He started with 180 seashells, which he kept in a large, ornate wooden box that his grandmother gave him for his 12th birthday. He then decided to share his collection with his friends, giving away 40 seashells to his best friend, Sam, and another 30 seashells to his two brothers, who are twins and love collecting seashells as much as he does. After giving away the seashells, Ali felt that his collection was still too large, so he decided to sell half of the remaining seashells at the local market, where he met a curious tourist who bought them all. How many seashells did Ali have left?

Mia is buying Christmas gifts for her family. She starts by spending $30 on each of her 3 siblings. She then decides to increase her spending by $10 each month for her parents' gifts. If Mia spent a total of $210 on Christmas gifts by the end of the year and each of her parents received gifts of equal value, how much money, in dollars, did she spend on each parent’s gift in December?
A rectangle has a length that is twice its width. If the diagonal of the rectangle is 10 units and the rectangle is also a square, what is the area of the rectangle?

Erin works in the school cafeteria serving soup. Each bowl of soup has 10 ounces, and Erin can serve 5 bowls per minute. If the pot of soup has 8 gallons of soup and Erin takes a 5-minute break every 20 minutes, how long will it take her to serve all the soup, rounded to the nearest minute? (There are 128 ounces to a gallon.)
In a zoo, the number of cats is 20% less than the number of dogs, and the number of frogs is twice the number of dogs. If there are 160 frogs, how many animals are there in total in the zoo?

On Tuesday, Liza had $800 in her checking account. On Wednesday, she paid her rent, $450. On Thursday, she deposited her $1500 paycheck. On Friday, she paid her electricity and internet bills, which were $117 and $100, respectively. Additionally, she decided to make a one-time donation of $200 to a charity. Then on Saturday, she paid her phone bill, $70. How much money is left in Liza's account?

Hector purchased a container of gumballs. He gave 4 to Todd, then he gave twice as many as he had given Todd to Alisha, and then he gave 5 less than four times as many to Bobby as he had given to Alisha. If Hector had 6 gumballs remaining and he originally had 50 gumballs, how many gumballs did he give to Bobby?

Madeline needs to cover her monthly expenses which include $1200 for rent, $400 for groceries, $200 for medical expenses, and $60 for utilities. She also wants to save $200 for emergencies and plans to donate $100 to a charity. If she receives a 10% raise next month and currently makes $15 per hour, how many hours will she need to work this month and next month to meet her financial goals?

Alden's family invited their relatives for a family reunion on Christmas eve. Initially, there were 50 more female adults than male adults, but for every 10 male adults, 2 additional female adults joined the gathering. Children were twice the total number of adults. If there were 100 male adults, how many people attended the family reunion?
James buys 5 packs of beef that are 4 pounds each. The price of beef is $5.50 per pound, but he only pays $100 in total. How many packs of beef did he actually buy?

Herman likes to feed the birds in December, January, and February. He feeds them 1/2 cup of bird food in the morning and 1/2 cup in the afternoon. However, the birds can only consume a total of 1 cup of food per day, and any excess food turns into 1 additional bird every day. How many birds will there be by the end of February if Herman starts with 1 bird in December?

3 families of 4 people shared a vacation rental for 7.5 days. Everyone uses 1 oversized beach towel a day before getting a new one. The washing machine can hold 14 oversized beach towels per load. How many loads of laundry will it take to wash all the oversized beach towels?

Jay and Gloria are hosting a 4th of July party and have invited a total of 60 people. They want to ensure that each guest, as well as themselves, receives a small American flag. The craft store is offering a deal of 5 flags for $1.00. If they also decide to buy an extra 10 flags as backups, how much will they spend at the craft store?

Mary and Mike are sharing a jar of paint. Mary paints a dragon using 3 square feet of paint. Mike paints a castle using 2 square feet more paint than Mary used on her dragon. They then decide to paint a series of smaller suns, each using 1 square foot less paint than the previous one, starting with a sun that uses 4 square feet of paint. If there was originally enough paint in the jar to cover 13 square feet, how many suns can they paint before running out of paint?

The card shop has two boxes of cards. The first box contains cards that cost $1.25 each. The second box contains cards that cost $1.75 each. A girl then comes in and buys 5.5 cards from each box. What was the total cost, in dollars, of the cards she bought?

John orders food for a massive restaurant. He orders 1000 kilograms of beef at a density of $8 per cubic meter. He also orders twice that volume of chicken at a density of $3 per cubic meter. How much did everything cost?

A rectangle has a length that is twice its width. The perimeter of the rectangle is 36 meters. If the rectangle is cut into two equal squares, what is the area of each square? Additionally, if one of these squares is then folded into a regular pentagon with all sides equal to the side of the square, what is the area of the pentagon?

Josh has $300 in his wallet and $2000 invested in a business. If the business's stock price first rises by 30% and then drops by 20% before he sells all of his stocks, how much money will he have in his wallet after selling the stocks?

Sydney sends 5 texts each to Allison and Brittney on Monday, and 15 texts to each of them on Tuesday. If each text costs $0.10 and Sydney has a budget of $5, how many days can she continue this texting pattern?

A garden produced 237 potatoes, 60 fewer cucumbers, and twice as many peppers as the cucumbers. However, each pepper plant produced -15 peppers due to a magical curse. How many vegetables did the garden produce?

Cary is an engineer in charge of designing an irrigation system for three farmers. Farmer Bob grows 4 acres of corn, 10 acres of cotton, and 15 acres of beans. Farmer Brenda grows 7 acres of corn, 8 acres of cotton, and 16 acres of beans. Farmer Bernie grows 3 acres of corn and 14 acres of cotton. If corn takes 25 gallons of water an acre, cotton takes 75 gallons of water an acre, and beans take 1.5 times as much water as corn, what percentage of the total water used will go to Farmer Bob's farm?

Anne is 2 times as tall as her sister while Bella is 3 times as tall as Anne. If Anne is 80cm tall, and her sister can shrink at a rate of 10cm per second, how long will it take for her sister to become 0cm tall, and what will Bella's height be at that moment?

Scarlet saved $80 to spend on jewelry. She bought a pair of earrings that cost $23, a necklace that cost $48, and plans to buy a bracelet. If the bracelet costs $b dollars, how much will she have left after the purchase?
Alyssa, Keely, and Kendall ordered chicken nuggets from a fast-food restaurant. Keely and Kendall each ate twice as many as Alyssa. How many chicken nuggets did Alyssa eat?
In 3 year, Jayden wil be halv of Ernesto age. If Ernesto 11 year old now, how many year old Jayden is now?

The teacher brings in 28 mini-cupcakes and 24 donut holes for the class. There are 26 students in the class. If each student gets the exact same amount, how many desserts does each student get? Additionally, if the teacher decides to bring an extra 10 desserts for special occasions throughout the year, how many desserts does each student get on those days?

Arthur has set a goal to read 1000 pages over the summer. He has already read 75% of a 400-page book and 1/4 of a 1200-page book. Additionally, he plans to increase his reading by 50 pages every month. How many more pages does he need to read by the end of the summer to meet his goal, considering he has 3 months left?

Ivan has a bird feeder that holds \( b \) cups of birdseed. Every week, he refills the feeder, which is emptied by birds and a squirrel. Each cup of birdseed can feed 14 birds, and a squirrel steals \( s \) cups of birdseed from the feeder every week. How many birds does Ivan’s bird feeder feed in \( w \) weeks?

There is very little car traffic on Happy Street. During the week, most cars pass it on Tuesday - 25. On Monday, 25% less than on Tuesday, and on Wednesday, 1.5 more cars than on Monday. On Thursday and Friday, it is about 10 cars each day. On the weekend, traffic drops to 5.5 cars per day. How many cars travel down Happy Street from Monday through Sunday?

The gummy bear factory manufactures 300 gummy bears a minute. Each packet of gummy bears has 50 gummy bears inside. The factory needs to fill an order for 240 packets. However, the factory also has a special order that requires an additional 100 gummy bears per packet. How long would it take for the factory to manufacture enough gummy bears to fill both the regular and special orders, in minutes?

Paddington has 40 more goats than Washington. Washington, who lives on a large farm that also houses 50 sheep and 30 cows, has 140 goats. Paddington, on the other hand, recently won a local farming competition and decided to celebrate by buying a new tractor, which he uses to manage his farm that is located 10 miles away from Washington's farm. How many goats do they have in total?

The owner of a Turkish restaurant, known for its vibrant decor and traditional music, wanted to prepare a variety of traditional dishes for an upcoming celebration. She ordered ground beef, in four-pound packages, from three different butchers located in various parts of the city. The first butcher, who has been supplying the restaurant for over 15 years, delivered 10 packages early in the morning. A couple of hours later, 7 packages arrived from the second butcher, who is famous for using only organic meat. Finally, the third butcher, whose delivery truck is painted with colorful murals, arrived at dusk. If all the ground beef delivered by the three butchers weighed 100 pounds, how many packages did the third butcher deliver?

Question: Studying for her test, Mitchell had integrated ten chapters of a book before 4 o'clock. When it clocked 4, Mitchell had differentiated 20 pages of the 11th chapter of the book she was studying from. After 4 o'clock, she didn't integrate the remaining pages of chapter eleven but proceeded and differentiated 2 more chapters of the book. If each chapter in the book had 40 pages, calculate the total number of pages that Mitchell had integrated altogether?

Cameron is printing her thesis in the school library and starts with 400 A4 pieces of paper. If 40% of the papers do not print to her satisfaction and she discards them, but then she decides to reprint the discarded papers using a higher quality setting, which uses an additional sheet of paper per document, how many total sheets of paper does she use if 30% of the reprints also fail to meet her standards?

Kennedy's house is 600 square feet larger than 4 times Benedict's house. If Kennedy's house is 10000 square feet and Benedict's house is 2500 square feet, how many square feet larger is Kennedy's house than Benedict's house?

Carolyn is planning her final essay, which needs to be 5000 words in total. The introduction is 450 words, and the conclusion is triple the length of the introduction. She decides to add an additional section to her essay, making it five body sections in total, each of the same length. How long is each body section now?

Janice can type 6 sentences per minute. Today at work, Janice continued working on a paper she started typing yesterday. She typed for 20 minutes, took a break, and typed 15 minutes longer. She then had to erase some sentences she had typed incorrectly. After a meeting, she typed for 18 minutes more. In all, the paper had 536 sentences by the end of today. How many sentences did she start with today?
Jim collects model cars, and he has 301 models in total. Jim has 4.5 times as many Buicks as Fords, and 2.5 times as many Fords as Chevys. How many Buicks does Jim have?

In a small town with a population of 5,000 people, 2,000 are males. The number of females increases by 10% every year. If 30% of the female population wears glasses, how many females will be wearing glasses after 2 years?

Alex has a magical water bottle that refills at a mysterious rate. One day, Alex notices that after drinking from the bottle, it refills to 25% of its capacity in 45 minutes. If Alex drinks the same amount of water again, how much longer will it take for the bottle to reach 100% full? Assume the rate of refilling remains constant.

In a neighborhood, some families own pets. 15 families have 2 dogs, 20 families have 1 dog, and the rest of the families have 2 cats each. If there are 50 families in total, how many pets are there in the neighborhood, considering that some families might also have an additional pet that is neither a dog nor a cat?

An Italian restaurant earns $600 every weekday and increases its earnings by 25% on the weekend. If the restaurant also donates 10% of its total monthly earnings to a local charity, how much money does it earn by the end of the month after the donation?

When the strawberries at Fruity Farm are ready for harvest, Miguel charges each interested picker $5 to access the strawberry fields. Once there, people pick as many strawberries as they wish, and then take them to Miguel for weighing and pricing. This year, the standard price of a pound of strawberries is $25. Miguel is a very generous man. He deducts the entrance charge from the cost of the harvest. Sally, Jenny, and Moses have just finished their strawberry picking and are headed home. They paid $150 for their harvest. How many pounds of strawberries did they pick?

Edmonton is 220 kilometers north of Red Deer. Calgary is 110 kilometers south of Red Deer. If a car starts from Edmonton and increases its speed by 10 kilometers per hour every hour, starting at 100 kilometers per hour, how long will it take to reach Calgary?

Tom was driving on a highway and was pulled over for speeding. The base fine for speeding is $50, and the fine increases by $2 for every mile per hour over the speed limit. Tom was driving 70 miles per hour, but the police officer mentioned that the speed limit was either 40 miles per hour or 50 miles per hour, depending on the time of day. The fine is also doubled if Tom was in a construction zone, but it's unclear whether he was in one. Additionally, Tom has to pay $200 in court costs and his lawyer $100 per hour for two to three hours of work. How much does Tom owe in total?

At the start of the year, Caroline has 40 pairs of socks. Each month, she loses 2 pairs of socks at the laundromat and donates one-third of her remaining pairs to the thrift store. Every three months, she buys 5 new pairs of socks and receives 2 new pairs as gifts. How many pairs of socks does Caroline have at the end of the year?

John buys 10 packs of magic cards from a specialty store that is known for its vast collection of rare and unique items. Each pack contains 20 cards, and the store offers a special discount of 15% on bulk purchases. Interestingly, 1/4 of the cards in each pack are uncommon, and the store's mascot, a dragon named Zephyr, is often seen roaming the aisles. How many uncommon cards did John get?
Paddington has 40 more goats than Washington. If Washington has 140.5 goats, how many goats do they have in total?
Mary hav 5 gren crayon an 8 blue crayon, diffrent shdes. She giv 3 gren crayon an 1 blue crayon too Becky, how many crayon she hav lefft?

Marla has a grid of squares that has 12 rows and 20 squares in each row. She colors 5 rows of 8 squares in the middle of the grid with red. She colors all squares on the first 3 and last 3 rows with blue. Then she colors the rest with green. How many squares does Marla color green?

In a class of 300 students, 40% are smokers. Each quarter, 10% of the smoking students quit, and 5% of the non-smoking students start smoking. By the end of the year, 70% of the smoking students are hospitalized due to smoking-related complications. How many students who were smoking at the beginning of the year have not been hospitalized by the end of the year?
Ed has 2.5 dogs, 3.5 cats, and twice as many fish as the number of cats and dogs combined. How many pets does Ed have in total?

Jeanne wants to ride the Ferris wheel, the roller coaster, and the bumper cars. The Ferris wheel costs 5 tickets, the roller coaster costs 4 tickets, and the bumper cars also cost 4 tickets. Jeanne has 5 tickets and her friend gives her some more. How many more tickets should Jeanne buy if she wants to ride all the attractions, and how many tickets did her friend give her?

Hadley wore his cowboy boots everywhere. He walked \(a\) miles to the grocery store, \(b\) miles to the pet store, and \(c\) miles back home. If \(a = 2\), \(b = a - 1\), and \(c = 4 - 1\), how far, in miles, did Hadley walk in his boots?

A café has a few orders to cook and also needs to make sandwiches for a group of customers that arrived. 4 local offices have each ordered 12 bacon sandwiches, and 60% of the group that has arrived have asked for 5 bacon sandwiches each. If the café makes a total of 78 bacon sandwiches, how many customers are in the group that arrived?

Jean has 3 grandchildren. She buys each grandchild 2 cards a year and puts $80 in each card. Additionally, during the summer, she gives each grandchild a gift of $100. How much money does she give away to her grandchildren in a year?

Marcy is a makeup artist preparing for a friend's wedding. She has 6 tubs of lip gloss, each holding 2 tubes, and each tube is enough for 3 people's makeup. However, Marcy realizes she has only brought 5 tubs of lip gloss, and each tub now holds 3 tubes. Despite this, she still claims she has the exact amount of lip gloss needed for 36 people's makeup. How many people is Marcy painting with makeup?

On a road map, 1/3 inch represents 10 miles of actual road distance. The towns of Maplewood and Oakville are represented by points 4 1/2 inches apart on the map. What is the actual distance, in miles, between the towns?
John orders food for a massive restaurant. He orders 1200 pounds of beef for $7.50 per pound. He also orders three times that much chicken at $2.50 per pound. How much did everything cost?

Lilah's family gallery, which is located in their spacious living room next to a large, ornate fireplace, has 400 photos. On a two-day trip to the Grand Canyon, they took half as many photos as they have in the family's gallery on the first day. On the second day, they took 120 more photos than they took on the first day, despite the fact that it rained heavily in the afternoon, forcing them to seek shelter in a nearby visitor center where they spent an hour browsing through a collection of Native American artifacts. If they added all these photos to the family gallery, which is organized in a custom-built wooden frame with glass panes, calculate the total number of photos in the gallery.

Ann is baking cookies and has organized her baking schedule into a chart that shows the number of dozens of each type of cookie she bakes and gives away. Using the chart, determine how many total cookies Ann keeps. (No chart provided.)

Fern is checking IDs to get into an R-rated movie. She denied 25% of the 120 kids from Riverside High, 60% of the 90 kids from West Side High, and 45% of the 50 kids from Mountaintop High. How many kids got into the movie?

A cheetah and a gazelle start running in the same direction. The cheetah runs at a top speed of 60 mph, while the gazelle runs at 40 mph. If one mile per hour is about 1.5 feet per second, and they are initially 210 feet apart, how long will it take for the cheetah to catch up to the gazelle, assuming the cheetah starts running 10 seconds after the gazelle begins? Consider the time the cheetah takes to reach its top speed and the gazelle's initial head start.

Kylie has 5 daisies. Her sister gave her another 9 daisies. After receiving the daisies, Kylie decides to give 1/3 of her total daisies to her mother and then 2 daisies to her friend. How many daisies does Kylie have left?

Henry took 9 pills a day for 14 days. Of these 9 pills, 4 pills cost $1.50 each, and the other pills each cost $5.50 more. However, the total cost of all the pills per day is $20. How much did he spend in total on the pills?

In a certain state, there are 40 Judges. If 10% of the Judges are under 30 years old, 60% are between 30-50 years old, and the rest are over 50 years old, how many Judges are over 50 years old? Additionally, if the number of Judges under 30 years old increases by 5% next year while the number of Judges over 50 decreases by 10%, how many Judges will be over 50 years old next year?
Tim buys x dozen eggs, and each egg costs $y. How much does he pay for the eggs in z weeks if he buys them every week?

Janice's office is located in a building with a circular staircase that spirals around a cylindrical core. Each floor is connected by a single flight of stairs that wraps around the core exactly once, making a full 360-degree turn. In a single day, Janice goes up the three flights of stairs 5 times, down the three flights of stairs 3 times, and uses the elevator the remainder of the time. If each flight of stairs is 10 meters long and the staircase has a radius of 2 meters, how many meters does Janice walk (up and down) in a single day, considering that the staircase also has a straight section that is 5 meters long and runs parallel to the cylindrical core?
Tom swims for \( t \) hours at a speed of \( s \) miles per hour. He then runs for \( \frac{t}{2} \) hours at a speed of \( 4s \) miles per hour. How many miles does he cover in total?

James has a rainwater collection barrel. For each inch of rain, he collects 15 gallons. On Monday, it rained 4 inches, and on Tuesday, it rained 3 inches. He decides to use 25% of the collected water for his garden and sells the rest at $1.20 per gallon. How much money did he make from selling the water?
John writes 20.5 pages a day. How long will it take him to write 3 books that are 400 pages each?

There were chocolates on the table. Jack came and took half of all the chocolates and 5 more chocolates. Then Paul came and took the remaining 8 chocolates. How many chocolates were on the table at first?

A couple with two children, ages 6 and 10 years old, decided to go to an amusement park. The regular ticket costs $109, but children below 12 years old have a $5 discount. If the family's total expenditure is represented by the hypotenuse of a right triangle with legs measuring $350 and $150, how much change will they receive if they gave the cashier $500?

Valerie is designing a special envelope for her thank you cards. She decides to make the envelope in the shape of a rectangle with a circular base. The rectangle is 10 inches long and 5 inches wide, and the circular base has a diameter of 6 inches. If she needs to cover the entire surface area of the envelope with decorative paper, how many square inches of paper does she need? Additionally, if each thank you card requires 1 stamp and she has 3 thank you cards, how many stamps does she need in total?

Oliver and William are comparing their collections of bills. The amounts and types of bills they have are summarized in a chart. Using the chart, determine how much more money Oliver has than William. (No chart provided.)

Sam and Jeff had a skipping competition at recess. The competition was split into four rounds. Sam completed 1 more skip than Jeff in the first round. Jeff skipped 3 fewer times than Sam in the second round. Jeff skipped 4 more times than Sam in the third round. Jeff got tired and only completed half the number of skips as Sam in the last round. If Sam skipped 16 times in each round, and Jeff could skip backwards in time, how many skips did Jeff complete in total?

Jessa needs to make cupcakes for 3 fourth-grade classes that each have 30 students and a P.E. class with 50 students. However, she only has enough ingredients to make 100 cupcakes. How many cupcakes does she need to make to ensure each student gets one, and how many students will not receive a cupcake?

Five coaster vans are used to transport students for their field trip. Each van carries 28 students, and the total number of students is 150, including 60 boys. If each boy weighs 50 kg and each girl weighs -30 kg, what is the total weight of all the girls?

Jason is climbing a telephone pole next to a tree that his friend Matt is climbing. If Matt climbs at a rate of \( m \) feet per minute and Jason climbs at a rate of \( j \) feet per minute, how much higher will Jason be than Matt after \( t \) minutes?

A Turkish restaurant owner ordered ground beef in four-pound packages from three different butchers. The first butcher delivered 10 packages, and the second butcher delivered 7 packages. The third butcher delivered the remaining packages in a rectangular prism-shaped box that had a square base with sides of 2 feet and a height of 3 feet, but the box was only 1 foot tall. If all the ground beef delivered by the three butchers weighed 100 pounds, how many packages did the third butcher deliver?

Gail has two fish tanks. The first tank is twice the size of the second tank. There are 48 gallons of water in the first tank. She follows the rule of one gallon of water per inch of fish. If she keeps two-inch fish in the second tank and three-inch fish in the first tank, how many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank?

In a factory that initially employed 852 people, 25% more workers were hired in the first quarter, and then an additional 15% more workers were hired in the third quarter. How many employees are there now in the factory?

Kamil decides to renovate his kitchen and hires two professionals. Each professional works 6 hours a day for 7 days. If one professional is paid $15 per hour, and Kamil also provides a bonus of $50 for each professional for completing the work on time, what is the total cost for hiring the professionals including the bonuses?

Olga has three stripes on the side of each of her tennis shoes. Rick has one less stripe per shoe than Olga. Hortense, however, has double the number of stripes on her tennis shoes as Olga. If each of them also has a pair of casual shoes with half the number of stripes as their tennis shoes, what is the total number of stripes on all of their pairs of tennis shoes and casual shoes combined?

Hawkeye is driving to his aunt and needs to charge his battery multiple times. If each charge costs $3.5 and he charges his battery x times, with a battery charging budget of $20, how much money is left when he reaches his aunt's place?

Jeanette is practicing her juggling. Each week she can juggle 2 more objects than the week before. If she starts out juggling 3 objects and practices for 5 weeks, what is the circumference of the number of objects she can juggle?

A farmer hires small trucks to transport his lemons to the markets. The load on a truck may not exceed 900 kilograms. If the farmer starts with 100 bags of lemons, each weighing 8 kilograms, and plans to add 10 more bags each month, how many additional kilograms can be loaded into the truck at the end of 6 months?

Nate is planning his route through the airport parking lot to find his car. He has a map that shows the layout of Section G and Section H, including the number of rows and the number of cars in each row. The map also indicates the starting point and the direction he should walk. Using the map, Nate wants to determine the most efficient path to cover all rows in both sections. If Nate can walk past 11 cars per minute, how many minutes will it take him to search the entire parking lot? (No map provided.)

In a wildlife reserve, the age of a lioness is twice the age of a hyena. The lioness is 12 years old. If the babies of the two animals are half the age of their mothers, and each mother has more than one baby, calculate the sum of the age of the babies in five years. Assume each baby ages at the same rate as their mother.

Betty is 60 years old, the oldest in her family. Her daughter is 40% younger than Betty, and her granddaughter is one-third her mother’s age. If Betty’s grandson is 5 years younger than her granddaughter, how old is the grandson?

Sarah starts buying snacks from the vending machine at work. She buys a snack for $1.00 on the first day. Each subsequent day, she buys a snack that costs either $0.50 more or $0.50 less than the previous day's snack. After 10 days, how much money has Sarah spent on snacks?

James buys a rectangular prism-shaped block of beef that measures 4 feet in length, 3 feet in width, and 2 feet in height. The block is somehow flattened into a circle with a diameter of 1 foot. If the price of beef is $5.50 per pound and the density of beef is 0.5 pounds per cubic foot, how much did James pay for the beef?

A jar contains a large number of jelly beans. Three fourths of the jelly beans are red, and one quarter of the red jelly beans are coconut flavored. If 750 jelly beans are coconut flavored, how many jelly beans are there in the jar? The jar is cylindrical with a height of 20 cm and a diameter of 10 cm, and it is filled to 80% of its capacity with jelly beans. The jar was purchased from a local store on a Tuesday, and the store offers a 10% discount on all purchases over $50.
