Sarah receives a performance bonus that is the same percentage each year. Last year, she earned $120,000 and received a $12,000 bonus. This year, her earnings increased to $240,000. What is her total income, including the bonus, this year?

Samantha needed to make several trips with her car and had only 15 gallons of gasoline. She drives to a bookstore 7 miles away and then drives back home. Then she heads to her office which is 9 miles away. Three miles into the journey, she realizes she forgot her laptop and drives back home to get it, then continues to her office. If she now has exactly 3 gallons of gasoline left, at what rate in miles per gallon has her car been consuming gasoline?

A rectangular garden has a length that is 3 times its width. The garden produced 237 potatoes, 60 fewer cucumbers, and twice as many peppers as the cucumbers. If the perimeter of the garden is 100 meters and the area is 150 square meters, how many vegetables did the garden produce?

Nancy is filling an aquarium for her fish. She fills it halfway and goes to answer the door. While she's gone, her cat knocks the aquarium over and spills half the water in it. Then Nancy comes back and triples the amount of water in the aquarium. If the aquarium is 4 feet long, 6 feet wide, and 3 feet high, and the aquarium is shaped like a perfect sphere, how many cubic feet of water are in the aquarium?

Janeth bought 5 bags of round balloons with 20 balloons in each bag and 4 bags of long balloons with 30 balloons in each bag. She decided to give 10 round balloons and 15 long balloons to her friend. While blowing up the remaining balloons, 5 round balloons and 3 long balloons burst. How many balloons are left?

On the first day of the journey, the Skipper sailed his ship halfway to the destination by traveling due east for 24 hours at a speed of 25 kilometers per hour, and then turned the ship's engines off to let them cool down. But while the engines were off, a wind storm blew his vessel backward in a westward direction. After the storm, the Skipper used his GPS device to determine the new location of the ship, and he discovered that he was only one-fourth of the way to his destination. How many kilometers had the ship been blown in a westward direction by the storm?
There are 30 tables in a hall. One-third of the tables have 2.5 chairs each, 6 have 3.2 chairs each, and the rest have 4.1 chairs each. How many chairs in total are in the hall?

Agatha has a budget to spend on a new bike. She spends $15 on the frame, $25 on the front wheel, and $10 on a helmet. If she has $20 left to spend on a seat and handlebar tape, how much money, in dollars, did she have initially?

Sarah is planning a series of baking days to make blueberry pies. She needs 200 blueberries to make a pint of blueberry jam and then uses a quart of blueberry jam to make a blueberry pie. If she plans to make 6 pies, and she has already made 3 pints of jam, how many more blueberries does she need to pick? However, she also decides to double her jam production for each subsequent baking day. How many blueberries does Sarah need to pick in total?

Sharon is inspired by Angela's kitchen and decides to buy kitchen supplies for her own. Angela has 20 pots, 6 more than three times as many plates as the pots, and half as many pieces of cutlery as the plates. Sharon plans to buy half as many pots as Angela, 20 fewer than three times as many plates as Angela, and twice as much cutlery as Angela. Additionally, Sharon decides to buy 5 extra pieces of cutlery for each family member, and she has 4 family members. How many kitchen supplies in total does Sharon want to buy?
Trent caught \( t \) tadpoles and then released \( p\% \) of them. How many tadpoles did he keep in terms of \( t \) and \( p \)?

Sarah buys a batch of fruits for $50 to make smoothies. She makes 25 smoothies and decides to sell them. Initially, she sets the price at $4 per smoothie. By midday, she sells some smoothies and then decides to increase the price to $5 per smoothie. By the end of the day, she sells the rest of the smoothies. How much profit does Sarah make?
A basketball team played 40 games and won 70% of the games. They still have 10 games left to play. If they want to end the season with a 65% win rate, how many of the remaining games must they win?

Nancy, the librarian, is shelving books from the cart. She shelved 12 history books, 8 romance books, and 4 poetry books from the top section of the cart. The bottom section of the cart contained a circumference of mystery books, which she quickly put back into place. Then, she shelved the remaining books from the bottom of the cart, including 5 Western novels and 6 biographies. What is the diameter of books she had on the book cart when she started?

Tom decides to expand his theater business by adding a second theater. The new theater will have 700 seats, and the cost per square foot of space remains $5. He still needs 12 square feet for every seat. Construction costs are twice as much as the land. Tom’s partner agrees to cover 40% of the total cost this time as well. How much does Tom spend on the new theater?

There are 40 students in a class. If 1/10 are absent, 3/4 of the students who are present are in the classroom, and the rest are in the canteen. If the classroom has a diameter of 10 meters, how many students are in the canteen?

Sam and Jeff had a skipping competition at recess. The competition was split into four rounds. Sam completed 1.5 more skips than Jeff in the first round. Jeff skipped 2.5 fewer times than Sam in the second round. Jeff skipped 3.5 more times than Sam in the third round. Jeff got tired and only completed 0.75 the number of skips as Sam in the last round. If Sam skipped 16 times in each round, what is the average number of skips per round completed by Jeff?

An aquarium holds an equal number of clownfish and blowfish. 26 of the blowfish stay in their own tank, and the remaining blowfish swim into a display tank. An equal number of clownfish join the blowfish in the display tank, but then a third of these clownfish swim back into their own tank. If the aquarium holds a combined total of 100 fish, and the number of clownfish in the display tank is now 15 more than the number of blowfish in the display tank, how many clownfish are now in the display tank?

John's Gym Schedule is divided into different activities, and the time spent on each activity is represented in a pie chart. The pie chart shows the following activities: Weightlifting, Warming Up, Cardio, and Resting. John goes to the gym 3 times a week and spends a total of 4 hours at the gym each week. What fraction of his total gym time is spent on Warming Up and Cardio combined? (No pie chart provided.)

Sarah is designing a custom rectangular rug for her living room. The rug measures \(a\) feet by \(b\) feet, and the cost to make the rug is \(c\) dollars per square foot. If Sarah decides to increase the length by 2 feet and the width by 3 feet, how much more will the rug cost?

Amber worked for \( a \) hours last weekend. Armand worked \( \frac{1}{3} \) of Amber's hours, and Ella worked twice as long as Amber. If they each worked for \( w \) weekends, how many hours did they work in total over \( w \) weekends?

At a certain school, 2/3 of the population are females. One-fifth of the males are foreign students, and the number of foreign male students increases by 2 each semester. If the school has 300 students and there are 2 semesters in a year, how many non-foreign male students are there at the end of the year?

Alice and Bob decide to split the cost of a new sofa and coffee table. The sofa costs $600, and the coffee table costs half as much as the sofa. They agree that Alice will pay 60% of the total cost, and Bob will pay the rest. However, they also decide to use a discount coupon, but they can't agree on whether the discount should be applied to the sofa only or to the total cost of both items. If the discount is 15%, how much does each person end up paying?

Jessica has a magical piggy bank that doubles the amount of money she puts in every month. Last year, she put $1000 for rent, $200 for food, and $100 for car insurance each month into the piggy bank. This year, her rent goes up by 30%, food costs increase by 50%, and the cost of her car insurance triples because she was at fault in an accident. How much money will the piggy bank have at the end of this year if it continues to double the amount she puts in each month?

In Professor Plum's biology class, there are 40 students. Of those students, 80 percent have puppies. Of the students who have puppies, 25% also have parrots. Additionally, 10% of the students who have parrots also have fish. How many students have puppies, parrots, and fish?

Gina had $400. She gave 1/4 of her money to her mom, used 1/8 of her money to buy clothes, gave 1/5 of her money to a charity, and then decided to save 1/3 of the remaining money for a rainy day. How much money did Gina save for a rainy day?

Mia starts with 4 times as many shells as David, who has 15 shells. Each month, Mia’s collection grows by 5 shells, while Ava has 20 more shells than Mia at any given time. Alice always has half the number of shells Ava has. After 6 months, what is the total number of conch shells they all have?
Noemi plays at the casino, losing $x on roulette and $y on blackjack. If she ends up with $z in her purse, how much money did she start with if she played for w weeks?

Marcy is a makeup artist and has agreed to do some makeup for her friend's wedding, which is being held at a luxurious venue with a capacity of 200 guests. The wedding is scheduled to start at 3 PM, and Marcy arrives at 9 AM to set up her station, which includes a variety of makeup products. The only makeup she has limited stock of is lip gloss, so she counts how many tubes she needs. Each tube of lip gloss will hold enough lip gloss for 3 people's makeup. Marcy decides to bring 6 tubs of lip gloss, each of which holds 2 tubes of lip gloss, and this will be the exact amount she needs for everyone's makeup. Additionally, Marcy has a helper who will assist her, and they plan to take a 15-minute break every hour. How many people is Marcy painting with makeup?

A fruit and vegetable merchant installed \( a \) kg of carrots, \( b \) kg of zucchini, and \( c \) kg of broccoli. He sold only a fraction \( f \) of them. What mass of vegetables did he sell in \( g \) days, if he sells the same amount each day?

Percius has a collection of 100 marbles. 40% of them are clear, 20% are black, and the rest are a mix of other colors. If his friend randomly picks 10 marbles, how many marbles of other colors can his friend expect to get on average?

Then, he divided the remaining dandelion puffs equally among his 3 friends, but each friend received -2 dandelion puffs. How many dandelion puffs did Caleb originally pick?

Janice can type 6 sentences per minute. Today at work, Janice continued working on a paper she started typing yesterday. She typed for 20 minutes, took a break, and typed 15 minutes longer. If the paper had a circumference of 500 sentences at the start of today, how many sentences did she start with today?

An aquarium holds an equal number of clownfish and blowfish. Some of the blowfish stay in their own tank, and the remaining blowfish swim into a display tank. An equal number of clownfish join the blowfish in the display tank, but then a third of these clownfish swim back into their own tank. If the aquarium holds a combined total of 100 fish, how many clownfish are now in the display tank?

Ed has a rectangular fish tank that is 3 feet long, 2 feet wide, and 1 foot high. He decides to build a circular doghouse inside the tank with a diameter of 4 feet. If the doghouse has a height of 2 feet, how much volume of the tank is left for the fish?

The Jacksonville Walmart usually receives 120 customer complaints each day. When the store is short-staffed, the number of complaints increases by 1/3rd, and this number further increases by 25% when the self-checkout is out of order. If the store was short-staffed and the self-checkout was broken for 4 days, how many total complaints did the store receive during this period?

Loraine makes wax sculptures of animals. Large animals take four sticks of wax and small animals take two sticks. She made three times as many small animals as large animals, and she used 12 sticks of wax for small animals. If the large animals are shaped like cubes and the small animals are shaped like spheres, and each large animal has a volume of 64 cubic units while each small animal has a surface area of 12 square units, how many sticks of wax did Loraine use to make all the animals?

The owner of a Turkish restaurant wanted to prepare traditional dishes for an upcoming celebration. She ordered ground beef, in four-pound packages, from three different butchers. The following morning, the first butcher delivered 10 packages. A couple of hours later, 7 packages arrived from the second butcher. Finally, the third butcher’s delivery arrived at dusk. If all the ground beef delivered by the three butchers weighed -20 pounds, how many packages did the third butcher deliver?

Monty is planning a family reunion for 36 family members. A local restaurant offers an 8-piece fried chicken bucket with 2 sides for $12.00, which feeds 6 people. If Monty also decides to buy an additional 4-piece chicken bucket for $7.00 to ensure there's plenty of extra food, how much will it cost him to buy enough chicken and sides to feed everyone one serving, plus the extra bucket?

Liam has a box of crayons. He starts with 12 crayons and then his friend gives him some more. The next day, he finds a few more crayons on the playground. By the end of the week, Liam has twice as many crayons as he started with. How many crayons did Liam find on the playground?

Mike bought a DVD of his favorite movie for $5 at the store. His friend, Steve, also wanted to buy the same DVD but had to order it online. The online price was twice the store price, and he also had to pay shipping costs, which were 80% of the online price. Additionally, Steve had to wait for 3 weeks for the DVD to arrive and decided to buy a movie poster for $7 to pass the time. How much did Steve spend in total, including the poster?

A garden produced 237 potatoes, 60 fewer cucumbers, and twice as many peppers as the cucumbers. However, the garden also produced 10 more cucumbers than potatoes. How many vegetables did the garden produce?

May can knit 3 scarves using one yarn. She bought different types of yarns and recorded the quantities in a chart. Using the chart, determine how many scarves May will be able to make in total. (No chart provided.)

Alice and Bob decided to bake cookies for their first date. Alice initially baked 74 chocolate chip cookies and Bob baked 7 peanut butter cookies. They then baked additional cookies, with Alice baking 5 more and Bob baking 36 more. However, they also had to deal with their pets, who managed to knock some cookies off the counter. If they ended up with 93 edible cookies and there are 4 pets in the house, how many cookies did the pets knock off the counter?
In a block of flats, there are 150 apartments. 90% of them have at least 1 resident, while 55% of the apartments have at least two residents. How many apartments have only one resident?

A liter of chlorine originally costs $10 but is now on sale for 20% off. A box of soap, which originally costs $16, is now on sale for 25% off. If you decide to buy 3 liters of chlorine and 5 boxes of soap, but you also have a coupon that gives you an additional 10% off the total purchase, how much will you save in total compared to the original prices?
Ms. Thompson noticed that 35% of her Grade 4 students received a final grade below C. If she has 80 students in Grade 4, how many students received a final grade of C or above?

Carrie is wrapping four birthday presents. The first present needs 2.5 square feet of wrapping paper. The second present needs half the amount of the first. The third present needs the same amount as the first and second presents combined. The fourth present needs twice the amount of the third present. How many square feet of wrapping paper does Carrie need for all four presents?

Naomi is doing the wash. She sorts her laundry into three piles: towels, sheets, and delicate clothes. The delicate clothes take 45 minutes to wash. The towels take three times as long as the delicate clothes. The sheets take 20 minutes less than the towels. If she also adds a load of heavy blankets that take 90 minutes to wash, how many minutes in total will it take for Naomi to wash everything?

Dani brings two and a half dozen cupcakes for her 2nd-grade class. There are 27 students (including Dani), 1 teacher, and 1 teacher’s aid. If 3 students called in sick that day and Dani decides to give an extra cupcake to each of the remaining students, how many cupcakes are left after she gives them out?

Lena has 96 inches of yarn that she plans to use for her knitting project. She first cuts it into 16 equal pieces. Realizing the pieces are too short, she decides to tie four pieces together. Each knot makes the combined piece 2 inches shorter. How long are the pieces of yarn after she ties them?
If 68% of the pies in a bakery are eaten with forks, and the bakery makes 2000 pies in total, how many pies are not eaten with forks if the percentage of pies eaten with forks changes to p%?

The dinner bill for 6 friends came to $150. Silas decided to pay for half of the bill, and the remaining friends agreed to split the rest of the bill equally, including a 10% tip for the whole meal. If each of the remaining friends also adds an additional $2 to cover any unexpected charges, how many dollars will one of the friends pay?

A school has several teachers, and each teacher teaches 5 periods a day. If the school operates 24 days a month and each teacher is paid $5 per period, how much has the school spent on teacher salaries after 6 months, considering there are some part-time teachers who only work half the days?
John writes a certain number of pages every day. How long will it take him to write 3 books?

Tom's cat needs a series of treatments over a year, totaling $6000. He has had pet insurance for 24 months that costs $20 per month. The insurance covers 80% of the treatment costs, but the coverage increases by 5% every six months. How much money did Tom save by having insurance over the year?
Roger rode his bike for x miles this morning, and then 5 times that amount in the evening. If he continues this routine for y days, how many miles does Roger ride his bike in total?
Ed has 2 dogs, 3 cats, and twice as many fish as cats and dogs combined. However, Ed also claims that he has exactly 10 pets in total. How many fish does Ed have?
Arven bought five puppies for a total cost of $1200. Three puppies are on sale for $200 each. How much does each of the two other puppies cost if they cost the same?

A beadshop earns a third of its profit on Monday, a quarter of its profit on Tuesday, and during a special weekend sale, it earns an additional $300. If the shop makes a total profit of $1,500 for the week, how much profit, in dollars, was made on Wednesday?

Emilia is planning to make multiple berry cobblers for a community event. She needs 42 cartons of berries for each cobbler. She already has 2 cartons of strawberries and 7 cartons of blueberries in her cupboard. If she decides to make 3 cobblers, how many more cartons of berries should Emilia buy from the supermarket?

Krystian works in the library, which is located in a historic building that was constructed in 1895. He borrows an average of 40 books every day from Monday to Thursday. Every Friday, his number of borrowed books is about 40% higher than the daily average. The library has a total of 12,000 books, and Krystian's favorite section is the science fiction aisle, which has 1,500 books. How many books does he borrow in a week if the library is open from Monday to Friday?

Marla has a grid of squares that has 10 rows and 15 squares in each row. She colors 4.5 rows of 6 squares in the middle of the grid with red. She colors all squares on the first 2 and last 2 rows with blue. Then she colors the rest with green. How many squares does Marla color green?

A Turksh resraunt onner wanterd to mae tradishunal dishs for a celebrashun. She orded ground beef, in fore-pound packeges, form tree differnt butchers. Th follwing mornin, th firs butcher delivrd ten packeges. A coupel of ours later, seven packeges arrivd form th secund butcher. Finly, th thrid butcher’s delivry arrivd at dusk. If all th ground beef delivrd by th tree butchers weigd 100 pounds, haw many packeges did th thrid butcher delivr?

Dan owns an ice cream shop located in a bustling downtown area. Every sixth customer gets a free ice cream cone, and each cone costs $2. On a particularly sunny day, Dan also sells ice cream sandwiches for $3 each and offers a 10% discount on all purchases over $50. If he sold $100 worth of cones and the shop was visited by a group of 15 school children who each bought a cone, how many free ice cream cones did he give away?

Jackie is an avid tree climber. She started by climbing a 1,000-foot tall tree. Next, she climbed 3 trees, each of which was 200 feet shorter than the first tree. Finally, she climbed a tree that was 300 feet taller than the first tree. What was the average height of the trees that Jackie climbed?

A jar is shaped like a perfect cube and has a circular base. The height of the jar is equal to the diameter of its base. Three fourths of the jelly beans in the jar are red, and one quarter of the red jelly beans are coconut flavored. If 750 jelly beans are coconut flavored, how many jelly beans are there in the jar?

Tim's cat bit him, leading him to get both himself and the cat checked out. His doctor's visit cost $400, and his insurance covered 80%. The cat's visit cost $150, and his pet insurance covered $75. Additionally, Tim had to buy a $25 bandage for himself and a $15 cone for the cat. How much did he pay in total?

Jeanette is practicing her juggling. Each week she can juggle 2 more objects than the week before. If she starts out juggling 3 objects and practices for 5 weeks, but by the end of the 5th week, she can only juggle 8 objects, how many objects can she juggle at the end of the 5th week?

A grocery store has a special deal on fruits and vegetables. The store provides a chart showing the prices of different items and the discounts available based on the quantity purchased. Mark buys 3 apples and 2 bananas. He also has a coupon that offers an additional discount, which is detailed in the chart. If Mark pays $5.00, how much change does he receive? (No chart provided.)

Roger’s turn to provide a snack for the baseball team after the game has finally arrived, and he has decided to bring trail mix. The trail mix comes in packs of 6 individual pouches. Roger has 13 members on his baseball team, plus 3 coaches and 2 helpers. Each pack of trail mix is wrapped in a bright orange wrapper, and the company that produces the trail mix is known for its environmentally friendly packaging. Roger’s favorite trail mix flavor is a special blend of nuts and dried fruits, which he discovered during a family vacation to Hawaii last summer. How many packs of trail mix does he need to buy to ensure everyone gets a pouch?

Hans booked a room in a luxurious hotel that has 10 floors, each with 10 identical rooms. The hotel features a grand lobby with a chandelier weighing 500 pounds and a swimming pool that is 50 meters long. Due to an accident involving a leaky pipe, the last floor is unavailable for guests. Additionally, the hotel has a strict policy that no pets are allowed in the rooms. Considering there are no other guests, in how many different rooms could Hans be checked in?
In one hour, the temperature at the peak of Addison Mountain will drop to 3/5 of its current temperature. If the temperature now is 100 degrees, by how many degrees will the temperature decrease?

Sally and Bob have a rectangular garden where the length is twice the width, and the perimeter is 30 meters. They decide to plant a circular flower bed inside the garden with a diameter that is equal to the length of the garden. If the area of the circular flower bed is 50 square meters, what is the width of the garden?

Alex has 2 cakes that are each cut into 8 slices. A third of the slices are given away to his friends. A quarter of the remaining slices are given away to his family. Alex eats 2.5 slices. How many slices of the cake are left?

John is a prolific author who writes a book every 2 months. Initially, he earns $30,000 per book, but his earnings increase by $5,000 for every 5 books he writes. How much money has he made over 20 years of writing?

Apple and peach trees are planted in the orchard of the Grange Poser farm. The orchard has \( a \) apple trees that each give \( b \) kg of apples and \( p \) peach trees that each produce an average of \( q \) kg of fruit. If the farm decides to plant an additional \( c \) apple trees and \( d \) peach trees next year, what will be the total mass of fruit harvested in the orchard next year?

Jacob loves to build things. In Jacob's toy bin, there are 18 red blocks. The number of yellow blocks is 7 more than the number of red blocks, and the number of blue blocks is 14 more than the number of red blocks. Each month, Jacob adds 3 more red blocks, 2 more yellow blocks, and 4 more blue blocks to his collection. How many blocks are there in total after 6 months?
Anais has 30 more toys than Kamari, and together they have 160 toys. If Kamari receives 10 more toys every month, how many toys will Kamari have after 6 months?
Sarah buys a pack of 60 pencils. She uses 24 of them and then gives one-third of what is left to her friend. How many pencils does she have left?

John can teleport to different times to earn money. He teleported back 3 hours on Saturday and earned $18, then teleported forward 5 hours on Sunday and earned half that amount. He also teleported to the previous weekend and earned $20. If he needs $60 to buy a new pogo stick, how many more hours does he need to teleport to earn the remaining amount, assuming he earns $6 per hour of teleportation?

Lily has a basket of apples and oranges. She gives 3 fruits to her friend, and then buys 5 more fruits, without specifying the type. If Lily originally had twice as many apples as oranges and now has 12 fruits in total, how many apples and oranges does she have now?

Ron is part of a book club that meets every week. The club includes three couples, five single people, and Ron with his wife. In addition to the regular weekly picks, each member gets to choose an extra book during their birthday week. Given that each member has a unique birthday week, how many times a year does Ron get to pick a new book?
Sarah buys \( x \) balloons. Each balloon holds \( y \) liters of air. If she buys \( z \)-liter tanks of gas, how many tanks does she need to buy to fill all the balloons?

Shawn starts filling a bucket with water from a sink. The water flows at a steady rate of 2 cups per 10 minutes for the first hour. Then, the water pressure increases, and it flows at 4 cups per 10 minutes for the next 45 minutes. After that, the water pressure drops, and it flows at 1 cup per 10 minutes for the last 15 minutes before stopping. Shawn then needs to pour out 60% of the water. How much water is left in the bucket?
A two-year subscription to a magazine is offered with a 40% discount. If a subscription normally costs $120 per year, how much does the discounted two-year subscription cost?

Maddie’s mom drinks coffee every day. She makes 2 cups of coffee each morning, using 1.5 ounces of coffee beans per cup. A bag of coffee costs $8 and holds 10.5 ounces of beans. Maddie’s mom also uses 1/2 a gallon of milk weekly. A gallon of milk is priced at $4. Maddie wants to calculate how much her mom spends on coffee each week, but she’s not sure if the milk cost should be included in the total. How much does Maddie’s mom spend on her coffee per week, considering the ambiguity in whether the milk cost is part of the total?

Kendra visits the Craftee And Best store during a special sale where every wooden toy has a $5 discount and every hat has a $2 discount. If she buys three wooden toys and four hats with a $200 bill, how much change does she receive?

Isabelle works in a hotel and runs a bubble bath for each customer who enters the hotel. There are 13 rooms for couples and 14 single rooms. For each bath that is run, Isabelle needs 10ml of bubble bath. If the hotel is fully booked and each couple decides to have an additional bubble bath during their stay, how much bubble bath, in millilitres, does Isabelle need for the entire week, assuming the hotel is fully booked every day?

Oliver is curious about the water usage for his baths. He uses a bucket that holds 120 ounces to fill his bathtub, which he fills 14 times to reach the top. However, he prefers the water level to be 3 buckets lower. After adjusting the water level, he decides to measure his weekly water usage. If Oliver takes a bath every day, and on weekends he fills the bathtub one extra bucket higher than his usual level, how much water does he use each week?

A boxer, who is training for a championship in a gym located 10 miles from his home, weighs 97 kg at 4 months from the fight. He is on a strict diet that allows him to lose 3 kg per month until the day of the fight. The boxer trains 5 days a week, and his coach, who is 42 years old, monitors his diet and exercise regimen. If the boxer’s weight loss continues at the same rate, how much will he weigh on the day of the fight?

A grocery store is offering discounts on various items. The discounts are categorized into different types of products, and the savings for each category are shown in a chart. If you buy 3 gallons of whole milk and 5 boxes of cereal, how much will you save in total? (No chart provided.)

Cassy packs 12 jars of jam in 10 boxes and 10 jars of jam in 30 boxes. If she has 500 jars of jam and decides to give away 2 jars of jam for every holiday (assuming there are 12 holidays in a year), how many jars of jam will she have left after all the boxes are full and the holidays are accounted for?

Nancy, the librarian, is shelving books from the cart. She shelved 12 history books, 8 romance books, and 4 poetry books from the top section of the cart. Half the books on the bottom section of the cart were mystery books, which she quickly put back into place. Then, she shelved the remaining books from the bottom of the cart, including 5 Western novels and 6 biographies. However, the total number of books on the cart was negative 10. How many books did she have on the book cart when she started?

A family of four, including two children aged 6 and 10, decided to visit an underwater amusement park located 20,000 leagues beneath the sea. The regular ticket costs $109, but children below 12 years old have a $5 discount. If they gave the cashier $500, how much change will they receive after paying for the submarine ride to the park?

Ali and Sara set a goal to eat 120 small apples combined in a month. Ali eats 4 times as many apples as Sara. If they are halfway through the month and have already eaten 80 apples, how many more apples does Sara need to eat each day for the rest of the month to meet their goal?

Ellie has found an old bicycle in a field and thinks it just needs some oil to work well again. She needs 10ml of oil to fix each wheel and will need another 5ml of oil to fix the rest of the bike. However, she also believes that the total amount of oil needed for the bike is 20ml. How much oil does she need in total to fix the bike?

To upgrade her kitchen, Amanda is replacing 18 cabinet knobs at $2.50 each and 8 drawer pulls at $4.00 each. Additionally, for every 5 knobs she buys, she gets a 10% discount on the pulls. If she buys all the knobs and pulls at once, how much will the kitchen upgrade cost her?

At a conference, 20 out of 50 attendees arrived with pre-printed name badges. One-third of the remaining attendees made their own, hand-written name badges. How many attendees were not wearing any name badges?

Steve has decided to become a baker. On Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays, he bakes 12 apple pies. On Tuesdays and Thursdays, he bakes 12 cherry pies. However, each week, he increases the number of pies he bakes by 2, starting with 12 pies per day in the first week. How many more apple pies does he bake than cherry pies in the fourth week?

Jan buys 1000 feet of cable. She splits it up into 25-foot sections. She gives 1/4 of that to a friend, who then teleports the cable to Mars. She then puts half of the remaining cable in a time machine and sends it back to the year 1800. How much cable does she keep on hand in the present?

Jolene and Phil have four children, all sharing the same birthday. They welcomed their first child exactly 12 years ago. One year later, their second child was born. Their third child arrived on the third birthday of their second child. Finally, three years after the birth of their third child, they had their fourth child. How old, in years, is their fourth child?

Hillary sells handmade crafts at a flea market. Each craft is priced at a variable rate, which is the derivative of 12 dollars with respect to the number of crafts. Today, she sells 3 crafts and receives an additional 7 dollars as a tip. She then decides to deposit 18 dollars into her bank account, which has an annual interest rate of 5%. How many dollars is Hillary left with after making the deposit, assuming the interest is compounded continuously?

Charlotte is planning to buy a pair of boots that are originally priced at $90, but the store offers a 20% discount. Additionally, she wants to buy a pair of socks that cost $15 with no discount. How much money should Charlotte bring to the store to buy both the boots and the socks?

Uki owns a bakery. She sells cupcakes at $1.50 each, cookies at $2 per packet, and biscuits at $1 per packet. In a day, she can bake an average of twenty cupcakes, ten packets of cookies, and twenty packets of biscuits. Each week, she increases her production by 20% to meet growing demand. How much will be her total earnings for the first two weeks?

A bakery can make 12 pies in one hour, and each pie has 3 pieces. If each piece of pie is sold for $4, and the cost to make one pie is $0.5, how much money would the bakery lose if it operated continuously for 24 hours and each pie piece magically disappeared as soon as it was made, without any sales?

Richard can clean his room in 22 minutes. Cory takes 3 minutes more than Richard to clean her room, but Blake can clean his room 4 minutes more quickly than Richard. If they have to clean their rooms twice a week, and Blake also claims he can clean his room in the same time as Cory, how many minutes do all three spend cleaning their rooms each week?

During one day, there are 4 boat trips through the lake. The boat can take up to 12 people during one trip. If the boat’s capacity is measured in kilograms and each person weighs an average of 70 kg, what is the total volume of people the boat can transport in 2 days?
Paityn has 20 red hats and 24 blue hats. Her friend Zola has 4/5 times as many red hats as Paityn. If they combine all the hats together, how many hats does each get?

A rectangular swimming pool has a length of 20 feet, a width of 10 feet, and a depth that varies from 3 feet at one end to 7 feet at the other end. The pool is filled with water and then drained using a pump that can remove 50 cubic feet of water per hour. However, the pool also has a magical property where the water level rises by 1 foot every hour due to an enchanted spring. If the pool is initially full, how long will it take to completely drain the pool?
John worked \( h \) hours a day from the \( d_1 \)-th to the \( d_2 \)-th, including the \( d_1 \)-th and not including the \( d_2 \)-th. How many hours did he work in total?
Rewrite Question: Let Jacob’s current age be \( j \) years, and his brother Tony’s age be \( \frac{j}{2} \) years. If \( j = 24 \), how old will Tony be in \( t \) years?

A bulk warehouse is offering 48 cans of sparkling water for $12.00 a case. The local grocery store is offering the same sparkling water for $6.00 and it only has 12 cans. If the volume of each can is 355 milliliters, how much more expensive, per liter, is the density of the sparkling water at the grocery store compared to the warehouse?

Miriam has a budget of $150 to spend on marbles, with each marble costing $1. She gave her brother 60 marbles, her sister twice that amount, and her friend Savanna three times the amount she currently has. How many marbles did Miriam originally have, and how long can she continue buying marbles at her current rate of spending?
Winwin won $50 in a lottery. The breakdown of her expenses and the amount she took home is shown in the pie chart below. What percentage of her winnings did she pay in taxes? (No pie chart provided.)

Emery is organizing the cookie cutters in her mom’s drawer. She finds x triangle-shaped cutters, y square ones, and z hexagons. If she arranges them in a pattern where each shape is used p times, how many sides are there in total on all the cookie cutters used in the pattern?

Casey wants to decorate her toenails and fingernails. She decides to add an extra step by applying a coat of nail art on every other nail after the base coat and paint have dried. It takes 20 minutes to apply each coat (base, paint, glitter, and nail art) and 20 minutes for each coat to dry before applying the next one. If Casey has 10 fingernails and 10 toenails, and she applies nail art to 5 fingernails and 5 toenails, how many minutes will it take her to finish decorating all her nails?
James writes a 4-page letter to 3 different friends every week. Each month, he increases the number of pages in each letter by 25%. How many pages does he write in a year?

Mary has 5 green crayons and 8 blue crayons of different shades. Each week, she buys 2 more crayons of each color. If she gives out 3 green crayons and 1 blue crayon to Becky after 4 weeks, how many crayons does she have left?
On a farm, the average milk production is such that every p cows produce q liters of milk per week. Over r weeks, the cows produced s liters of milk. How many cows are on the farm?

Savannah is wrapping presents for her friends and family for Christmas. She has bought 3 rolls of wrapping paper to wrap 15 gifts. If it takes 1 roll to wrap 4 gifts and 1 roll to wrap 6 other gifts, and she uses the third roll to wrap the remaining gifts with no wrapping paper leftover, how many gifts did she wrap with the third roll of paper?

Nate went out to do his daily exercises. In 8 seconds, he ran a distance equal to four times the length of a football field. He then rested for a while and ran an additional distance which was 30% more than the initial distance he covered. If the field's length is 168 meters, how far did Nate run in total?
James buys several packs of beef. The price of beef is $5.50 per pound. How much did he pay?

A middle school teacher is planning a Valentine's Day card exchange for her class. She has 30 students, and 18 students want to give out heart-themed cards, while 12 students prefer to give out friendship-themed cards. The store sells packs of 6 heart-themed cards for $4 and packs of 4 friendship-themed cards for $3. Individual cards of each theme cost $1 each. What is the minimum amount of money the teacher can spend to ensure every student has the type of card they want?

Ali is collecting bottle caps. He has 125 bottle caps, some of which are red and some are green. If he gives away 25 caps to his friend, what percentage of the remaining caps are green? Assume the caps given away are either all red or all green, but it's not specified which.

During one day, there are 4 boat trips through the lake. The boat can take up to 12 people during one trip, but the boat has a maximum capacity of 8 people. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?

John writes 20 pages a day. He plans to write 3 books, each 400 pages long. However, he also decides to take a break every 10 days, during which he writes 50 pages. How long will it take him to complete all 3 books?

Tamia is making dinner and decides to use 5 bell peppers. She first cuts each bell pepper into 20 large slices. Then, she takes half of these slices and cuts them into 3 smaller pieces each. However, if she finds any slices that are not perfect, she discards 2 slices for each imperfect bell pepper. Assuming 2 of the bell peppers are imperfect, how many slices and pieces of bell pepper total will Tamia add to her meal?

A map shows the route between two cities, with various points of interest marked along the way. The scale of the map is given as 1/4 inch representing 8 miles. The distance between the two cities on the map is 3 3/8 inches. The map also includes a legend that categorizes the points of interest by symbols (e.g., parks, restaurants, gas stations). How many gas stations are there between the two cities? (No map or legend provided.)

Donovan Mitchell is currently averaging 26 points per game. His team has played 15 games this season. He has a goal of averaging 30 points per game for the entire 20 game season. However, his team might play additional exhibition games, and his points in these games are also counted towards his goal. How many points does he need to average per game in the remaining games, including any exhibition games, to reach his goal?
If it takes 20 minutes to paint a house, and 15 minutes to paint a shed, how many houses and sheds can you paint in 3 hours if you spend half the time on each?

Ian won $100 in the lottery. He decided to use the money to pay off debts. The amounts he paid to different people are shown in the chart below. How much money, in dollars, does he have left after paying off all the debts? (No chart provided.)

James has a rainwater collection barrel. For each inch of rain, he collects 15 gallons. On Monday, it rained 4 inches, and on Tuesday, it rained 3 inches. However, the barrel can only hold a maximum of 50 gallons. He can sell water for $1.20 per gallon. How much money did he make from selling all the water, given that he only sold 70 gallons?

If Mr. Jones has 6 shirts for every pair of pants and he decides to buy an additional 3 shirts for every holiday, how many total pieces of clothing will he own at the end of the year, given that there are 12 holidays and he initially has 40 pairs of pants?

Jake can wash his car with 1 bottle of car wash soap 4 times. Each bottle costs $4.00, and he washes his car once a week for 20 weeks. If the cost of car wash soap increases by $0.50 every 5 weeks, how much does he spend on car soap over the 20 weeks?

Lily has 6 lottery tickets to sell. She sells the first ticket for $2. Each successive ticket is sold for $1.50 more than the previous ticket. After keeping a $5 profit, she plans to give the rest of the money as the prize. How much money will the winner of the lottery receive?

Larry spends half an hour twice a day walking and playing with his dog, which is a golden retriever named Max. He also spends a fifth of an hour every day feeding his dog, who eats a special brand of dog food that costs $3.50 per pound. Larry’s dog weighs 70 pounds and lives in a house with a large backyard that has a fence painted blue. How many minutes does Larry spend on his dog each day?

John writes 20 pages a day. He decides to write 3 books, each in the shape of a perfect cube with a volume of 400 cubic pages. If each page is a square with a side length of 1 page, how many days will it take him to write all 3 books?

Gail has two fish tanks shaped like perfect cubes. The first tank is twice the size of the second tank. The first tank has a volume of 48 cubic feet. She follows the rule of one cubic foot of water per inch of fish. If she keeps two-inch fish in the second tank and three-inch fish in the first tank, and the second tank has a side length of 2 feet, how many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank if one of the first tank fish eats another?

Alice has a collection of marbles. She decides to give some to her friends. First, she gives 10% of her marbles to Bob. Then, she gives half of what is left to Carol. After that, she finds a box with more marbles and adds them to her collection, but she’s not sure how many were in the box. How many marbles does Alice have now?

The city’s bus system carries 1,200,000 people each day. The city also has a train system that carries twice as many people as the bus system on weekends. How many people do both the bus and train systems carry together over 13 weeks, assuming each week has 5 weekdays and 2 weekend days?
Alex is 7 years older than his brother Ben and twice his age. If the sum of their ages is the same as the number of years Alex has been older than Ben, how old is Ben?

James watched 2 episodes of Jeopardy and 2 episodes of Wheel of Fortune. Jeopardy is 20 minutes long, and Wheel of Fortune is twice as long. However, James only watched TV for a total of 1 hour. How many hours did he watch TV?

Lisa and Carly go shopping together. Lisa spends $50 on t-shirts, then spends 40% of this amount on jeans and three times this amount on coats. Carly spends only a third as much as Lisa on t-shirts but spends twice as much on jeans and half the amount Lisa spent on coats. In dollars, how much did Lisa and Carly spend in total?

James spends 3 hours vacuuming and 3 times as long on the rest of his chores. Additionally, every month he spends an extra 2 hours deep cleaning his home. How many hours does he spend on his chores in a year?
A rectangular garden has a length that is five times its width. If the area of the garden is 125 m², what is the perimeter of the garden?

Haley grows at the rate of 3 inches every year. She is currently 20 inches tall and lives in a house with a blue door. Her favorite color is green, and she has a pet cat named Whiskers who is 1 year old. If Haley’s birthday is in July and she celebrates it with a cake that has 5 candles, what will be her height after 10 years?
Terez has 45 cows on his farm. 50 percent of the cows are female, and 40 percent of the females are pregnant. How many pregnant female cows does Terez have?

Marly is making a large batch of soup for a community event. He adds 2 quarts of milk and three times as much chicken stock to 1 quart of pureed vegetables. After mixing, he realizes he needs to make the soup 25% larger to have enough for everyone. If he divides the final amount of soup into bags that can hold 3 quarts each, how many bags does he need?

Tammy just got her hair cut. For every 14 haircuts, she gets a free additional haircut. She has already received 5 free haircuts and is 5 haircuts away from qualifying for another free one. If she decides to get one extra haircut every month starting next month, how many total haircuts, including the free ones, will she have by the end of the year?

Jazel has 3 sticks. One stick is 3 centimeters long. The second stick is twice as long, and the third stick is 1 centimeter shorter than the second stick. If Jazel needs to create a rectangular frame using these sticks as the sides, what is the area of the rectangle she can form, and what is the total length of the sticks used?
If Pam is currently half as old as Rena, and in 10 years Rena will be 15 years older than Pam, how old is Pam now?

Mickey and Johnny are having a contest to see who can run around their block the most. One time around the block equals 200 meters. Johnny runs around the block 4 times. Mickey runs around the block half as many times as Johnny. If they decide to run an additional lap for every 500 meters they have already run, how many meters do they each run, and what is their average distance?

Agatha has $120 to spend on a new bike. She spends $30 on the frame and $45 on the front wheel. If she also buys a bike lock for $15, how much money, in dollars, does she have left to spend on a seat and handlebar tape?

In a small town, the mayor decides to celebrate the town’s founding by organizing a series of coin flips. Each flip represents a year, and the town was founded 211 years ago. During the celebration, a head represents a year of prosperity, and a tail represents a year of challenge. If the coin lands on heads 65 times, how many more years of challenge than prosperity has the town faced? Additionally, if the town’s prosperity is doubled every time a head appears, what is the total prosperity score of the town?
Riku has 25 times more stickers than Kristoff. If Kristoff has 85.2 stickers, how many stickers does Riku have?

Lisa is looking to attempt a World Record. She has decided to try and match Joey Chestnut's record of eating 75 full hotdogs, buns included, in 10 minutes. The chart below shows the number of hotdogs Lisa has eaten at various time intervals during her attempt. How many hotdogs will she have to eat per minute in the remaining time to at least tie Joey Chestnut's record? (No chart provided.)
Troy had \( s \) straws. He fed \( \frac{3}{5} \) of the straws to the adult pigs and the same number of straws to the piglets. If there were \( p \) piglets, how many straws did each piglet eat?

Alice and Emily are selling oranges at the farmer's market. Alice sold twice as many oranges as Emily, and the total number of oranges sold by both of them is represented by T. If T = 180, how many oranges did Alice sell?

Sarah has a collection of coins. She decides to give some to her friend and then buys a snack. If she initially had more than $5 and after giving away some coins and buying a snack for $1.50, she has less than $4 left, how much money did Sarah have at first?

Ferns checking ID's to get in to a R-rated movi. She deni 20% of the 120 kidz from River side High, 70% of 90 kidz from West Side Hi, an halv the 50 kidz from Mount Top High. How many kidz got in to the movi?

Janice can type 6 sentences per minute. Today at work, Janice continued working on a paper she started typing yesterday. She typed for 20 minutes, took a break, and typed 15 minutes longer. She then had to erase 40 sentences she had typed incorrectly. After a meeting, she typed for 18 minutes more. In all, the paper had 536 sentences by the end of today. However, it is known that Janice started today with 500 sentences already typed. How many sentences did she start with today?

There are 14 green papayas on the papaya tree. On Friday, 2 fruits turned yellow. On Sunday, twice as many fruits as on Friday turned yellow, and on the following Tuesday, 3 more fruits turned yellow. How many green papayas are left on the tree by the end of Tuesday?

Sam and Jeff had a skipping competition at recess. The competition was split into four rounds. Sam completed 1 more skip than Jeff in the first round. Jeff skipped 3 fewer times than Sam in the second round. Jeff skipped 4 more times than Sam in the third round. Jeff got tired and only completed half the number of skips as Sam in the last round. If Sam skipped 16 times in each round, what is the median number of skips per round completed by Jeff?

Ronald can grill 14.5 hamburgers per session on his new grill. He needs to cook 115 hamburgers in total for tonight's party. He has already cooked 40 hamburgers. How many more sessions will it take Ronald to finish cooking all 115 hamburgers?

A local bookstore has two types of notebooks: spiral-bound and hardcover. The prices of these notebooks are listed in a price chart. A customer buys 4 spiral-bound notebooks and 3 hardcover notebooks. What is the total cost of the notebooks the customer bought? (No price chart provided.)

After working out for 3 hours, three friends go out for lunch. Adam spends two-thirds as much money on lunch as Rick. Rick spends 20% more on his lunch than Jose. If Jose ate lunch worth $45, what is the total cost of lunch for all three?

Jaime saves $50 each week. Every two weeks, she spends $46 on a nice lunch with her mum. However, if it’s her mum’s birthday (which happens once a year), she spends an additional $50 on a special gift. How long will it take her to save $135, considering her mum’s birthday is in the next 10 weeks?

Rick has a collection of 400 books and decides to organize them into smaller groups by genre. He starts by dividing the books into two equally-sized groups and continues to divide each group into two smaller groups until each book is in a group with exactly 24 other books. How many times does Rick need to divide the groups to achieve this?

Philip has a farm with animals. He has 20 cows and 50% more ducks than cows. Philip also has pigs, which are one-fifth the total number of ducks and cows combined. If each animal requires 10 square meters of land and Philip has 1,000 square meters of land, how many more animals can he accommodate on his farm?
Alison bought some storage tubs for her garage. She bought 4 large ones and 8 small ones, for $64 total. If the large tubs cost $7 each, how much do the small ones cost?

Sasha can complete 15 questions an hour. If she has 60 questions to complete and she works for 2 hours, but then decides to work an extra hour on weekends, how many questions does she still need to complete after a month, assuming there are 4 weekends?

Sarah and her family picked a basket of apples from their orchard. Sarah gave a portion of the apples to her friend, and her brother used some of the apples to make juice. Their mother then used the remaining apples to bake pies, using 10 apples for each pie. If Sarah’s family picked 60 apples and Sarah gave 15 apples to her friend, how many pies can her mother bake, and how many apples are left? However, it is not clear if the apples used for juice were taken before or after Sarah gave apples to her friend.

Toby is counting goldfish in the local pond. He knows that only 25% of goldfish are at the surface and the rest are too deep below the surface to be able to see. If he counts 15 goldfish at the surface, and the total number of goldfish in the pond is 40, how many goldfish are below the surface?

Ayla has a customer care job where she talks to customers for 3 hours each call, and each call is charged at a rate of one cent per second. If she talks to 100 customers a week, what will be the total phone bill at the end of a 30-day month?
John plants a plot of 3.5 trees by 4 trees. Each tree gives 5 apples. He sells each apple for $0.5. How much money does he make, in dollars?

Angie bought 3 lbs. of coffee at the store today. Each lb. of coffee will brew about 40 cups of coffee. Angie drinks 3 cups of coffee every day, but she also has a magical coffee mug that refills itself with 10 cups of coffee every hour. How many days will this coffee last her?

John works a job that offers performance bonuses. He makes $80 a day and works for 8 hours. He has the option of working hard to earn the performance bonus of an extra $20 a day, but the extra effort results in a 2-hour longer workday. If John decides to earn the bonus, he must work inside a rectangular room where the length is twice the width, and the diagonal of the room is 10 feet shorter than the perimeter. How much does John make per hour if he decides to earn the bonus?

Mila makes $10 an hour, and Agnes makes $15 an hour. Agnes works 8 hours each week and receives a $50 bonus every month. How many hours does Mila need to work each month to earn as much as Agnes, including the bonus?

Lily plans to visit several friends and has a list of distances to travel: 10 miles to visit Alice, 15 miles to visit Bob, and 5 miles to visit Carol. She starts her day by driving to Alice's place. After dropping by Alice's, she realizes she needs to pick up a package from a store, which is located 7 miles from her current location. How many miles will Lily have driven when she is halfway through her errands, considering she might or might not have picked up the package?

Audrey was asleep for 10 hours last night and dreamed for 2/5 of the time. She also naps for 1.5 hours in the afternoon, during which she dreams for 1/3 of the time. How much total time was she not dreaming during her nighttime sleep and afternoon nap?
Alex bought four times as many cookies at the store as Jamie did. Jamie bought one-third as many cookies as Casey. If Casey bought 18 cookies, how many did Alex buy?

A boxer weighs 97 kg at 4 months from a fight. He is on a diet that allows him to lose 3 kg per month until the day of the fight. However, his weight increases by 2 kg per month due to muscle gain. How much will he weigh on the day of the fight?

Out of the 120 people who attended the party, 1/3 are men, half are women, and the rest are children. If each child brings along a pet, and there are 10 more pets than children, how many pets are at the party?

Terese decides to vary her running routine. On Monday, she runs \(a\) miles; on Tuesday, \(b\) miles; on Wednesday, \(c\) miles; and on Thursday, \(d\) miles. If the total distance she runs over these four days is \(T\) miles, express the average distance she runs each day in terms of \(a\), \(b\), \(c\), and \(d\).

In May, Alex collected 15 more Easter eggs than Jamie in their first round of egg hunt. However, Jamie gathered three times as many eggs as Alex in their second round of egg hunt, while Alex's total number of eggs in the second round was 15 less than the number he had gathered in the first round. If the total number of eggs in the pile they were collecting with 5 other people was 350 eggs, and Jamie gathered 75 eggs in the second egg hunt round, find the number of eggs that the 5 other egg hunters collected?

Ellie has found an old bicycle in a field near her grandmother’s house, which is 5 kilometers away from her home. The bicycle has been there for about 3 years, and it has a small bell that still works. She plans to fix it using oil. Each wheel of the bicycle requires 10ml of oil, and she will need an additional 5ml of oil to fix the rest of the bike. Ellie’s grandmother also has a cat named Whiskers, who is 4 years old and loves to play with the bicycle’s bell. How much oil does Ellie need in total to fix the bike?
There were sweets on the table. Jack came and took half of all the candies and 3.5 more candies. Then Paul came and took the remaining 7 sweets. How many sweets were on the table at first?

How many birds and chicks are there in total?

Valerie needs to put stamps on the envelopes she is about to mail. She has thank you cards for each of her grandmother, uncle, and aunt for the birthday presents they sent.
