In a single day, she goes up the three flights of stairs 5 times, down the three flights of stairs 3 times, and uses the elevator the remainder of the time. However, she also claims that she never uses the elevator. How many flights of stairs does Janice walk (up and down) in a single day?

Nadia was sent to the flower shop to buy 20 roses and 5/8 times as many lilies as roses. If roses cost $4 each and lilies cost three times as much each, calculate the total amount of money Nadia used to buy the flowers.

Nala found 5 seashells at the beach. The next day, she found another 7, and the following day, she found twice the number she got from the first two days. Additionally, during the summer, she finds 10 more seashells each week for 12 weeks. How many seashells does Nala have by the end of the summer?

John buys bags of popcorn for $4 each and sells them for $8 each. Each month, he increases the number of bags he sells by 5, starting with 20 bags in the first month. How much total profit does he make in a year?
Herman feeds the birds 1/2 cup in the morning and 1/2 cup in the afternoon. How many cups of food will he need for the winter months?

Carrie works for $8 an hour and 35 hours a week at her job. It’s been a month since she started working there, and she has saved up all of her money because she wants to buy a bike for $400. However, she also spends $200 each week on other expenses. How much money will she have left over after she buys her bike?

John carves a giant marble rectangular prism 8 meters tall with a 2-meter square base. It has a density of 2700 kg per cubic meter. In addition to this, he carves a smaller marble cube with a side length of 1 meter, which has the same density. How much does the combined weight of the rectangular prism and the cube weigh?

John writes 20 pages a day. He plans to write 3 books, each 400 pages long. John writes in a special notebook that has 500 pages, and he uses a blue pen that he refills every 100 pages. He writes in a cozy study room with a large window that faces a garden. The garden has 15 different types of flowers, and John often takes breaks to tend to them. How long will it take him to write all 3 books?

Padma starts with 75 cards and trades 2 of her valuable cards for 10 of Robert's cards. After a month, Padma trades 5 more of her cards for 12 of Robert's cards. Robert started with 88 cards and, after two months, trades another 8 of his cards for 15 of Padma's cards. How many cards were traded in total between Padma and Robert over the two months?
A rectangle has a length that is 30 units less than its width. If the width is 68 units, and the diagonal of the rectangle is 50 units, what is the area of the rectangle?

Toby is counting goldfish in the local pond, which is known to be 10 meters deep and covers an area of 500 square meters. He knows that only 25% of the goldfish are at the surface, while the rest are too deep below the surface to be seen. On a sunny day, with a gentle breeze blowing at 5 km/h, Toby counts 15 goldfish. If the pond is home to a variety of fish, including 10 koi and 5 catfish, how many goldfish are below the surface?

Sam and Jeff had a skipping competition at recess. The competition was split into four rounds. Sam completed 1 more skip than Jeff in the first round. Jeff skipped 3 fewer times than Sam in the second round. Jeff skipped 4 more times than Sam in the third round. Jeff got tired and only completed half the number of skips as Sam in the last round. What is the average number of skips per round completed by Jeff?

The Rotary Club is holding its annual Omelet Breakfast, with tickets sold in advance. This year, they sold 53 tickets for small children, 35 tickets for older children, 75 tickets for adults, and 37 tickets for seniors. The club estimates that small children can eat a half omelet, older children can eat a whole omelet, adults will eat two omelets, and seniors will eat one and a half omelets. To be safe, they decide to have enough eggs to make 25 extra omelets. They also plan to use 2 eggs for each omelet. However, they are unsure whether the 25 extra omelets are in addition to the estimated omelets or a buffer for any miscalculations. How many eggs will they need to buy?
John volunteers at a shelter twice a month for 3 hours each session. Every 3 months, he increases his volunteering time by 1 hour per session. How many hours does he volunteer in a year?
Baez has 25 marbles. She loses 20% of them one day. Then a friend sees her and gives her 1.5 times the amount that Baez has after she lost them. How many marbles does Baez end up with?

During a four-day trip to Italy, Keziah and her mom went mushroom picking. They sold all the mushrooms they picked on the first day for a total of $58. On the second day, they picked 12 mushrooms. On the third day, they picked double the mushrooms they had picked the previous day. On the last day, they picked 10 more mushrooms than they did on the first day. If the price per mushroom was $2, what is the total number of mushrooms they picked?

A community center organized a health fair and categorized the participants into different age groups. The pie chart below shows the distribution of participants by age group. If the total number of participants was 200, how many more participants were in the 18-30 age group compared to the 51-65 age group? (No chart provided.)

A convenience store sold 100 bags of chips in a month. In the first week, 15 bags of chips were sold. In the second week, thrice as many bags of chips were sold as in the first week. Starting from the third week, the store offered a discount, which increased the weekly sales by 10 bags each week. How many bags of chips were sold in each of the third and fourth weeks?

In a grocery store, Julia bought 2 pieces of Snickers and 3 packs of M&M's. Each Snickers costs $1.50, and each pack of M&M's costs as much as 2 Snickers. If the store has a special promotion where every 5th pack of M&M's is free, and Julia bought a total of 5 packs of M&M's, how much change does she receive if she gave the cashier 2 $10 bills?
Paddington has more goats than Washington. If Washington has 140 goats, how many goats do they have in total?

A cleaning company produces two sanitizer sprays. One spray has a frequency of 50% germ reduction, and another spray has a wavelength of 25% germ reduction. However, 5% of the germs they reduce overlap. What is the amplitude of germs left after using both sanitizer sprays together?

In a school election, John receives 150 votes. James captures 70% of the remaining votes. If the total number of votes cast is 1150, how many more votes does the third candidate, Lisa, receive compared to John?

A bakery sells pies, and the sales data for different types of pies over a week is summarized in a chart. The chart shows the number of pies sold each day for apple, cherry, and blueberry pies. If the bakery sells each piece of pie for $4 and each pie is cut into 3 pieces, how much revenue did the bakery generate from apple pies on Wednesday? (No chart provided.)

On Monday, Alex has 45 baseball cards. On Tuesday, Alex loses a third of them. On Wednesday, Alex buys 18 baseball cards. On Thursday, he buys a quarter of what he had on Tuesday. How many baseball cards does Alex have on Thursday?

Janet is considering quitting her job to freelance. Currently, she works 40 hours a week and earns $30/hour. As a freelancer, she would earn $40/hour but would have to pay an additional $25 a week in FICA taxes and $400 a month in healthcare premiums. If Janet also decides to take one week off each quarter for personal time, how much more would she make per year as a freelancer compared to her current job?

At Snowflake Plastics, each employee gets 15 sick days and 15 vacation days per year. If Mark uses 40% of his sick days and 60% of his vacation days in a year, how many hours' worth of days does he have left if each day covers a 7-hour long workday?

Mark has two pets, a hare that runs 15 feet/second and a tortoise that crawls 2 feet/second. If they're going to run a 30-foot race, how much of a head start (in seconds) does the tortoise need to finish in a tie?

Selena and Josh were running in a charity race. Together, they ran 36 miles. Josh ran half the distance that Selena ran. However, on days when it rained, Selena ran an additional 2 miles. Assuming it rained 5 times during the race, how many miles did Selena run in total?

A vacation rental was shared by 3 families, each consisting of 4 people, for a week. Each person uses 1 oversized beach towel a day before getting a new one. The washing machine, which is located in the basement of the rental and is a high-efficiency model, can hold 14 oversized beach towels per load. The families also used the washing machine to wash their regular laundry, which included 20 shirts and 15 pairs of pants, but these items are not part of the beach towel count. How many loads of laundry will it take to wash all the oversized beach towels?

Samuel swept the porch and cleared seven-eighths of the dust particles from it. As he walked across the porch afterward, his shoes left 223 dust particles behind. How many dust particles were on the porch before Samuel swept if there were 331.5 after he walked across it?

Alex plans to surprise his partner by filling their bathtub with sparkling cider for a special occasion. The bathtub can hold 50 gallons of liquid. Each bottle of sparkling cider contains 1.5 quarts. (There are 4 quarts in a gallon). If each bottle costs $30, and Alex receives a 15% discount for buying in bulk, how much does he spend in total?

Tom, Tim, and Paul are collecting photos of cars. Paul has 15 photos more than Tim. Tim has 120 photos less than the total amount of photos which is 200. Additionally, Tom has twice as many photos as the difference between Paul's and Tim's photos. How many photos does Tom have?

Loisa is considering buying a tablet that costs $450 if paid in full. The store offers an installment plan with a $100 down payment, followed by payments of $40 for the first 4 months, $35 for the next 4 months, and $30 for the final 4 months. If Loisa decides to save money each month to buy the tablet in cash after 6 months, how much less will she spend in total compared to the installment plan?

A family consisting of a mother, a father, and their two children, ages 6 and 10, decided to visit an amusement park on a sunny Saturday. The park is known for its thrilling roller coasters and delicious cotton candy. The regular ticket costs $109, but children below 12 years old receive a $5 discount. The family also bought a map of the park for $3, which they used to plan their day. If the family gave the cashier $500, how much change will they receive?

Baez has 25 marbles, which she keeps in a blue bag with a pattern of stars. One day, while playing near a park with her younger brother, who is 7 years old and loves collecting rocks, she loses 20% of her marbles. Later, her friend, who is wearing a green shirt and has a pet dog named Max, sees her and gives her double the amount that Baez has after she lost them. How many marbles does Baez end up with?

Lassie starts with a certain number of bones. On Saturday, she eats half of them. On Sunday, she receives 15 more bones and now has a total of 40 bones. How many bones did she start with before eating them on Saturday?

The Kwik-e-Tax Center charges $50 for a federal return, $30 for a state return, and $80 for quarterly business taxes. Additionally, they offer a $20 tax planning consultation service. If they sell 60 federal returns, 20 state returns, 10 quarterly returns, and 15 tax planning consultations in one day, what was their total revenue for the day?

Ali had a collection of seashells. He started with 180 seashells. He then gave away 40 seashells to his friends and 30 seashells to his brothers. If he sold 45% of the remaining seashells, how many seashells did he have left?

A local zoo had 200 visitors on Saturday. On Sunday, the number of visitors increased by 20% compared to Saturday. If the zoo decides to compile a yearly report, showing the total number of visitors every 2 months, how many visitors would be recorded in the first 2 months if the visitor trend continues as it did over the weekend?

Lily has 5 lottery tickets to sell. She sells the first ticket for $1. Each successive ticket is sold for a dollar less than the previous ticket. After selling all the tickets, she plans to use the money to buy a time machine that costs $10. How much money will she have left after purchasing the time machine?

Sarah commissions an artist to create a series of 9 by 13 drawings. She wants 3 of them in black and white, and 2 of them in color. Each black and white drawing costs $160, and each color drawing is 50% more expensive. How much does Sarah pay in total?

Ms. Watson’s class has 14 kindergartners and 24 first graders. She also has a number of second graders. If the total number of students in her class varies by 2 students each semester and currently stands at 42, how many second graders are in Ms. Watson’s class this semester?
Reggie's father gave him $48. Reggie bought 5 books, each costing $2, and also bought 3 notebooks, each costing $1.50. How much money does Reggie have left?

Quinton brought a box of cupcakes to school on his birthday. He gave a cupcake to each student in Ms. Delmont's class, which has more than 15 students. He also gave a cupcake to each student in Mrs. Donnelly's class, which has fewer students than Ms. Delmont's class. Additionally, he gave a cupcake to Ms. Delmont, Mrs. Donnelly, the school nurse, and the school principal. If he started with 40 cupcakes, how many cupcakes did he have left over?
John orders food for a massive restaurant. He orders 1000 pounds of beef for $8 per pound. He also orders twice that much chicken, but the chicken costs $-2 per pound. How much did everything cost?
Herbert is 10 years younger than Kris. If Kris is 24 years old now and both their ages increase by 25% next year due to a magical aging spell, how old will Herbert be next year?

Lily plans to create a giant sandcastle and needs 800 pounds of sand. She can purchase 40-pound bags of sand for $15 each. She also requires 20 pounds of water, which costs $0.50 per pound. Additionally, she spends $1,200 on advertising the event. She sells entry tickets for $25 each and manages to sell 600 tickets. How much profit does Lily make from her sandcastle event?

Sabrina starts with \( c \) cookies. She gives \( b \) cookies to her brother, and her mother gives her \( \frac{b}{2} \) cookies. Then, Sabrina gives \( \frac{2}{3} \) of her remaining cookies to her sister. How many cookies does Sabrina have left in terms of \( c \) and \( b \)?

A square has a side length of 10 cm and a diagonal of 15 cm. Mitchell, while studying, decided to draw this square and then inscribed a circle inside it with a radius of 8 cm. After 4 o'clock, she calculated the area of the circle and the area of the square. What is the total area of the square and the circle combined?

John works a job where he can earn a performance bonus. He makes $80 a day for 8 hours of work. If he decides to earn the bonus, his workday extends by 2 hours, but the bonus amount is a negative $20, reducing his total earnings to $60 for the day. How much does John make per hour if he decides to earn the bonus?

Yuri has been rescuing puppies for a month. In the first week, he rescued 20 puppies. Each subsequent week, he rescues a different number of puppies: in the second week, he rescues 2/5 times as many as the first week; in the third week, he rescues twice the number from the second week; and in the fourth week, he rescues 10 more puppies than he did in the first week. If Yuri plans to build a new shelter that can house 100 puppies, how many more puppies can he rescue before reaching the shelter's capacity?

During summer break, Jimmy explores various beaches on an island, changing his place of lodging frequently. For the first 3 days, he stays in a hostel and is charged $15 per night. From the fourth day onwards, he moves to a cabin and shares the expenses with 2 friends, where they are charged $45 in total per night. If Jimmy stays in the cabin for the next 7 days, how much does he spend on lodging in total?

Henry has 30 more lollipops than Alison, who has 60 lollipops, which is half the number of lollipops Diane has. If they decide to combine their lollipops and eat 45 lollipops every day, but on weekends they eat an additional 15 lollipops each day, how many days will it take for them to finish all the lollipops?

Jeanette is practicing her juggling inside a spherical room with a flat ceiling. The room has a diameter of 10 meters, and the ceiling is 3 meters above the floor. If she starts out juggling 3 objects and practices for 5 weeks, increasing the number of objects by 2 each week, how many objects can she juggle by the end of the 5th week, and what is the volume of the spherical room?

Marcy is a makeup artist and has agreed to do some makeup for her friend's wedding. The only makeup she has limited stock of is lip gloss, so she counts how many tubes she needs. Each tube of lip gloss will hold enough lip gloss for 3 people's makeup. Marcy decides to bring 6 tubs of lip gloss, each of which holds 2 tubes of lip gloss, and this will be the exact amount she needs for everyone's makeup. If Marcy's efficiency in applying makeup is measured by the derivative of the number of people she can paint per hour, and she works at a constant rate, how many people is Marcy painting with makeup?

A tractor trailer starts with a load of 50,000 pounds. At the first store, 10% of the weight is unloaded, and at the second store, 20% of the remaining load is removed. If the truck makes an additional stop at a third store where 15% of the new remaining load is unloaded, how much weight, in pounds, is left on the truck after all three deliveries?
Five months ago, Mike earned 10 times more money than Fred. If Mike's salary has increased by 40% since then, and Fred's salary at that time was $1200, calculate Mike's current salary.

Sarah can hold her breath underwater for 15 seconds. She decides to improve her time. After the first week, she increases it by 50%. After the second week, she doubles the time from the previous week. In the final week, she adds 25% more to her breath-holding time. How long can Sarah hold her breath now?

Linda starts with 2 dimes, 6 quarters, and 5 nickels. Her mother gives her 2 more dimes, 10 quarters, and twice as many nickels as she originally had. Each month, Linda saves 3 more dimes, 5 more quarters, and 2 more nickels. How many coins does she have at the end of 6 months?

Gary bought his first used car for $6,000. He borrowed the money from his dad, who said he could pay him back the full amount over 5 years. Gary decided to pay back the loan in 18 months instead. How much more is Gary spending per month to pay the loan off in 18 months instead of 5 years?
Susan has 21 cats and Bob has 3 cats. If Susan gives 4 cats to Bob, how many more cats does Susan have than Bob now?
In 3 years, Jayden will be half of Ernesto's age. If Ernesto is 11 years old now and Jayden is currently 10 years old, how old will Ernesto be in 5 years?

James, who started teaching at the age of 25 and has a collection of 150 rare coins, spends 40 years teaching. His partner, who teaches at the same school and has a dog named Max, has been teaching for 10 years less. If the school is located in a small town with a population of 5,000 and the average class size is 25 students, how long is their combined teaching experience?

Alex makes luxury dresses out of silk. Each dress needs 5 meters of silk and Alex has 600 meters of silk in storage. He decides to share some of his silk with his friends. First, he gives 20 meters of silk to each of his friends, but the number of friends is not specified. Then, he uses the remaining silk to make dresses himself. How many dresses can Alex make?
Jed is 10 years older than Matt. In 10 years, Jed will be twice as old as Matt is now. What is the sum of their present ages?

Caleb bought 10 cartons of ice cream and 4 cartons of frozen yoghurt. Each carton of ice cream costs $4 and each carton of frozen yoghurt costs $1. If the price of ice cream increases by 25% and the price of frozen yoghurt decreases by 20% the following week, how much more will Caleb spend on ice cream than on frozen yoghurt if he buys the same quantities the next week?

James buys \( t \) lotto tickets for \( d \) dollars each. Of those tickets, \( p \% \) are winners. Among the winning tickets, \( q \% \) win \( a \) dollars, 1 ticket wins the grand prize of \( g \) dollars, and the remaining winning tickets win an average of \( b \) dollars. How much did he profit?

There are 3 jars of cookies. One jar contains 24 cookies. Another jar has twice as many cookies as the first jar minus 10 cookies. The third jar has 5 more cookies than the second jar. If the first jar gives half its cookies to the second jar, how many cookies are in each jar now?

Heath’s goal is to plant 150,000 carrots in 5 days at his uncle’s farm. On the first day, he plants 400 rows with 300 plants in each row using a machine. How many additional carrots does he need to plant each day for the remaining 4 days to meet his goal?

Amanda needs 12 more marbles to have twice as many marbles as Katrina, and Mabel has 5 times as many marbles as Katrina. If Mabel has 85 marbles and each marble weighs -3 grams, how many more grams does Mabel's collection weigh compared to Amanda's collection?

Tanika is selling boxes of crackers for her scout troop's fund-raiser. On Saturday, she sold x boxes. On Sunday, she sold y% more than on Saturday. If she sells for z weekends, how many boxes does she sell in total?

Carter usually bakes 6 cheesecakes, 5 muffins, and 8 red velvet cakes regularly for a week. This week, he decided to double the number of cheesecakes and muffins, and triple the number of red velvet cakes and chocolate moist cakes. If he also added 10 more cupcakes to his baking list, how many more cakes and cupcakes did Carter bake this week compared to a regular week?

John's cow initially weighs 400 pounds. After a special diet, the cow’s weight increases to 1.5 times its starting weight, but it also loses 100 pounds. He sells the cow for $3 per pound. How much more is the cow worth after the diet, if its final weight is the same as its initial weight?

A bulk warehouse is offering 48 cans of sparkling water for $12.00 a case. The local grocery store, located in a bustling shopping district, is offering the same sparkling water for $6.00, but it only has 12 cans per pack. The grocery store is known for its frequent sales and has a loyalty program that offers discounts to members. Additionally, the store is currently running a promotion where every 10th customer receives a free reusable shopping bag. How much more expensive, per can, in cents, is this deal at the grocery store?

Hector purchased a container of gumballs. He gave 4 to Todd, then he gave the square root of the number he had given Todd to Alisha, and then he gave 5 less than four times the derivative of the number he had given to Alisha to Bobby. If Hector had 6 gumballs remaining, what is the total number of gumballs that Hector purchased?

Hazel walked 2 kilometers in the first hour. If she walked twice as far in the second hour and then walked an additional 3 kilometers in the third hour, how far did she walk in total over the three hours?

Sarah has a collection of marbles. She has 15 red marbles and twice as many blue marbles. One day, her friend gives her more marbles, but the friend doesn't specify the color. Sarah now has 60 marbles in total. How many marbles did her friend give her, and what color are they?

Wallace runs a beef jerky company. Each batch of jerky takes all night to make and produces 10 bags. Wallace received a customer order for 120 bags of jerky. If he starts with 20 bags already made and increases his production by 1 batch per week, how many days will it take him to fulfill the customer’s order?

Wendy, a fruit vendor, sells apples and oranges. She mentions that in the morning, she sells a certain number of apples and oranges, and in the afternoon, she sells more. If the total number of fruits sold in the morning is 70 and the total number of fruits sold in the afternoon is 90, and she sells apples at $1.50 each and oranges at $1 each, how much are her total sales for the day?

A local laundromat offers different wash cycles for various types of laundry. The water usage for each cycle is summarized in a chart. Additionally, the laundromat has a special rinse cycle for loads that require bleach, which is also detailed in the chart. Today, the laundromat has a schedule of washes, including the number of each type of wash and which loads need bleach. How many gallons of water will the laundromat use to complete today's schedule? (No chart provided.)

Pete starts with a bag of 10 marbles, where 40% are blue and the rest are red. His friend offers to trade him 3 blue marbles for every red marble. If Pete decides to keep 2 red marbles, how many total marbles does he have after trading with his friend?

Monika went out for the day and spent some money. She started by visiting the electronics store and spent $300 on new gadgets. Then, she went to the theater and watched 4 movies in a row, each costing $20. On her way home, she stopped at the local market and bought 15 bags of beans at $1.50 per bag. How much money did Monika spend throughout her day?

Hans booked a room in a hotel. The hotel has 10 floors with 10 identical rooms on each floor. Because of an accident, the last floor is unavailable for the guests. If Hans is equally likely to be checked into any available room, and he stays for 1.5 nights, how many different rooms could Hans be checked into per night on average?

Larry spends half an hour twice a day walking and playing with his dog. He also spends a fifth of an hour every day feeding his dog. If Larry’s walking speed is 5 km/h, what is the volume of time Larry spends on his dog each day?

One pie costs $5 for a piece, and each pie is cut into 4 pieces. The bakery can produce 15 pies in one hour. If the cost to make one pie is $0.75, how much profit would the bakery make in 3 hours if all pie pieces are sold?

Marvin and Tina were selling candy bars to help fund their class trip. The candy bars cost $2 each. Marvin sold 35 candy bars total. Tina sold three times the number of candy bars as Marvin, but each of her candy bars was priced at $-1. How much more money did Tina make for the class trip selling candy bars compared to Marvin?

Valerie needs to put stamps on the envelopes she is about to mail. She has thank you cards for each of her grandmother, uncle, and aunt for the birthday presents they sent. She also has to pay the water bill and the electric bill separately. She wants to send 2.5 times as many mail-in rebates as she does thank you cards, and she has 1.5 times as many job applications as rebates to mail. How many stamps does she need if everything needs 1 stamp except the electric bill, which needs 2?

In a small town, 40% of the mosquitos are infected with malaria, and 20% are infected with Zika virus. Jack is taking an experimental vaccine that reduces the chances of getting infected with malaria by 50% after a bite. If Jack gets bitten by a mosquito, what is the percentage chance he catches either Zika virus or malaria, considering that the effectiveness of the vaccine is only guaranteed if the mosquito is from the town's main park, where 60% of the mosquitos are found?
Jeremy listened to five and a half fewer songs yesterday than today. Yesterday, he listened to nine songs. How many songs did Jeremy listen to in two days?

A local grocery store is having a special sale. A gallon of whole milk, which usually costs $3, is now priced at $2. The store is also offering a discount of $1 on each box of cereal. If you decide to buy 3 gallons of whole milk and 5 boxes of cereal, and you notice that the store has a new layout with aisles numbered from 1 to 10, where the milk is in aisle 7 and the cereal is in aisle 3, how much will you save in total from the discounts? Additionally, the store has a loyalty program that offers a 5% cashback on all purchases, but this does not affect the discount amounts.
Carrie works at her job and saves up all of her money because she wants to buy a bike. How much money will she have left over after she buys her bike?

Bran's tuition fee is $120. He does a part-time job that pays him $20 per month and he has a scholarship that covers 40% of his tuition fee. If he needs to pay his tuition fee within 4 months, how much does Bran still need to pay?

School coaches decided to upgrade their sports equipment. Coach A started by buying ten new basketballs for $29 each. Each quarter, Coach A buys two more basketballs at a 10% discount off the original price. Coach B, on the other hand, bought 14 new baseballs for $2.50 each and a baseball bat for $18 at the beginning of the year. In addition, Coach B buys a new baseball bat every three months at a 15% discount off the original price. How much more did Coach A spend than Coach B over the year?

Ted needs to purchase enough fruit for a week, consisting of bananas and oranges. If he buys 5 bananas at $2 each and 10 oranges at $1.50 each, and he repeats this purchase every week, how much money does Ted spend on fruit over 6 months?

Evelyn’s family watched 10 hours of television last week. The week before, they watched 8 hours of television. If they plan to increase their television watching time by 2 hours each week starting next week, what will be the average number of hours of television they watch per week over the next 3 weeks?

A bus has seats arranged in 23.5 rows of 4 seats. At the start, 16.5 people climb on. At the first stop, 15.5 people board the bus and 3.5 get off. At the second stop, 17.5 people get on the bus and 10.5 get off. How many empty seats are there after the second stop?

Isabel has a certain amount of money, \( M \), in her piggy bank. She spends \( \frac{1}{3} \) of her money on a toy, then spends \( \frac{1}{4} \) of the remaining money on a book for her brother. If she has $51 left, how much money, in dollars, did she have initially?

A jar contains an infinite number of jelly beans. Three fourths of the jelly beans are red, and one quarter of the red jelly beans are coconut flavored. If 750 jelly beans are coconut flavored, how many jelly beans are there in the jar?
Cori is 4 years old today. In 6 years, she will be one-fourth the age of her aunt. How old is her aunt today?

Janice's office is located in a historic building on the third floor, which she reaches by walking up 3 flights of stairs. Each flight of stairs has 12 steps, and each step is 8 inches high. A school organized a field trip and assigned students to a minibus. The chart below shows the distribution of boys and girls who were initially assigned and those who actually joined the trip. How many girls were not able to join the field trip? (No chart provided.)
Haley grows at the rate of 3 inches every year. If she is currently 20 inches tall, what will be her height after 10 years, given that her height cannot exceed 25 inches?

Joy is winding balls of yarn for her cat to play with. The first ball is half the size of the second ball. The third ball is three times as large as the first ball. She used 27 feet of yarn for the third ball, but the second ball is also three times the size of the third ball. How many feet of yarn did she use for the second ball?

A clinic administered the covid vaccine to 650 people over the course of a year. In the first half of the year, 80% of the vaccinated people were adults. In the second half, this percentage dropped to 60%. How many children were vaccinated in the entire year?

Mary has a magical fuel tank that can hold negative gallons of fuel. This week, she used 15 gallons of fuel. Last week, she used 20% more than this week, but her tank showed a negative reading. How much fuel did she use in total for the two weeks?

Alice was preparing a batch of cookies for a bake sale. She baked 15 cookies in the first hour. In the second hour, she increased her baking rate by 50%, and in the third hour, she doubled her second hour rate. How many cookies did Alice bake in the three hours?
Alex weighs 7 more pounds than Ben. Ben is 10 pounds lighter than Carl. If Carl weighs 120 pounds and the three of them decide to weigh themselves together, what is their total weight?
Mitchell read several chapters of a book before and after 4 o'clock. She read 20 pages of the 11th chapter at 4 o'clock and then read 2 more chapters. How many pages did Mitchell read in total?

James has a rainwater collection barrel. For each inch of rain, he collects 15 gallons. On Monday it rained 4 inches and on Tuesday it rained 3 inches. He can sell water for $1.2 per gallon. If the barrel has a circumference of 10 gallons, how much money did he make from selling all the water?

Chang's Orchard has two types of apples: sweet and sour. He sells the sweet apples for $0.50 each and the sour apples for $0.10 each. 75% of the apples harvested are sweet, and the remaining 25% are sour. If Chang earns a total of $40 from selling the apples, how many apples did he harvest in total?
John buys several packs of magic cards. Each pack has a certain number of cards, and a fraction of those cards are uncommon. How many uncommon cards did he get?
A jar contains 120 candies. 70% of the candies are red, and 60% of the red candies are large. If 50% of the large candies are also green, how many candies in the jar are both large and green?

A plane takes off and flies for 3 hours, covering 900 miles. It then refuels and continues its journey. If the plane doubles its speed after refueling and flies for another 4 hours, how far has the plane traveled in total? However, it is known that the plane's initial speed was not constant, and it varied by 10% during the first part of the journey. Calculate the total distance traveled.

A cleaning company, located in a bustling city with a population of 500,000, produces two sanitizer sprays. The first spray, which has a blue label and is packaged in a 500ml bottle, kills 50% of germs. The second spray, with a red label and a 300ml bottle, kills 25% of germs. The company's CEO, who has been in the business for 15 years, recently discovered that 5% of the germs killed by both sprays are the same ones. If the company uses both sprays in a large office building that has 10 floors and 20 rooms per floor, what percentage of germs would be left after using both sanitizer sprays together?

Quinton brought \( c \) cupcakes to school on his birthday. He gave a cupcake to each of the \( s_1 \) students in Ms. Delmont's class and to each of the \( s_2 \) students in Mrs. Donnelly's class. He also gave a cupcake to Ms. Delmont, Mrs. Donnelly, the school nurse, and the school principal. If \( c = 40 \), \( s_1 = 18 \), and \( s_2 = 16 \), how many cupcakes did he have left over?

Four classmates, Jolyn, Therese, Aivo, and Leon, were comparing their ages based on their birth month. They found out that Jolyn is 2 months older than Therese, who was born in a leap year. Therese is 5 months older than Aivo, who has a pet dog named Max. Leon, who is a member of the school's chess club, is 2 months older than Aivo. Additionally, Jolyn's favorite color is blue, and she has 3 siblings. How much older in months is Jolyn than Leon?

Sarah and her two cousins are saving money to buy tickets for a theme park. Each adult ticket costs $30, and each child ticket costs $15. Sarah is an adult, and her cousins are children. They have collectively saved $25. Sarah has a part-time job that pays her $5 per week. If Sarah’s cousins also start working and together they earn an additional $5 per week, how many weeks will it take for them to have enough money to buy the tickets? Note that Sarah’s cousins might also contribute some of their savings from before.

Mary has 5 green crayons and 8 blue crayons of different shades. If she gives out 3 green crayons and 1 blue crayon to Becky, and then finds out that she actually has 10 crayons left, how many crayons did she start with?

Hillary, who is an avid crafter and often participates in local flea markets, sells handmade crafts for 12 dollars each. Today, she wears a blue apron and has set up her stall under a large, colorful umbrella. Hillary sells 3 crafts and, as a token of appreciation, a customer gives her an extra 7 dollars. She then decides to take a break and enjoys a cup of coffee from a nearby café. Later, Hillary deposits 18 dollars from today's profits into her bank account. She plans to use the remaining money to buy materials for her next batch of crafts. How many dollars is Hillary left with after making the deposit?

A farmer invests $50 in corn seeds, $35 in fertilizers and pesticides, and $15 in labor. After harvesting, the farmer collects 10 bags of corn. If the farmer wants to achieve a profit margin of p%, how much should each bag be sold for?
Today is my birthday, and I'm four times older than I was five years ago. How old am I?

Tim has 30 less apples than Martha, and Harry has half as many apples as Tim. If Martha has 68 apples and lives in a house with a blue door, how many apples does Harry have, considering that Tim’s favorite color is green and he often wears a yellow hat?

John scores 2 shots worth 2 points and 1 shot worth 3 points every 4 minutes. If he scores more than 10 points in a period, he gets a bonus of 5 points added to his total score for that game. He plays for 2 periods, each lasting 12 minutes. How many points does he score in total, including any bonuses?

Niko has bought 9 pairs of socks at $2 each and plans to resell them. For the first four pairs, he wants to gain a 25% profit, and for the next five pairs, he wants to increase his profit by $0.10 for each subsequent pair starting from a $0.20 profit on the first of these five pairs. How much will his total profit be?

Daytona Beach has 26 shark sightings a year, which is 5 more than triple the number of shark sightings in Cape May. If Cape May also has 2 fewer shark sightings than half the number of shark sightings in another beach, Sandy Hook, how many shark sightings are there in Sandy Hook?

A school has \( c \) classrooms. One-third of these classrooms have \( d_1 \) desks in each classroom, and the rest have \( d_2 \) desks in each classroom. Only one student can sit at one desk. How many students can this school accommodate so that everyone has their own desk?

Tina made a large pan of brownies and cut it into 24 pieces. She decided to have one with lunch and dinner every day, but each week she increases the number of brownies she eats by one more per day (starting with one per meal in the first week). Her husband continues to take one per day for 5 days each week to take to work. They also shared 4 with dinner guests. How many brownies were left at the end of the second week?

Jane's goal is to exercise 1 hour a day, 5 days a week. If she hits her goal every week for 8 weeks and also exercises an extra 2 hours each weekend during the summer months (June, July, and August), how many hours has Jane exercised by the end of the 8 weeks?

A family of 4 people shared a vacation rental for 7 days. Each person uses 1 oversized beach towel a day before getting a new one. The washing machine can hold 14 oversized beach towels per load, but it can only be used once every 24 hours. However, the washing machine also requires 3 hours to dry each load of towels. How many loads of laundry will it take to wash all the oversized beach towels, and how many days will it take to complete all the laundry if the family continues to use towels while the laundry is being done?

Tony has a bucket that holds 2 pounds of sand. He has a sandbox out back that is two feet deep, four feet wide, and 5 feet long. A cubic foot of sand weighs 3 pounds. Because it's hot outside, he wants to make sure he stays hydrated, so every 4 trips he takes he drinks 3 ounces of bottled water. However, on the hottest days of the year, he drinks twice as much water per trip. If there are 10 such hottest days in the year, and a 15 ounce bottle of water costs $2, how much change will he have after he buys all the water he needs, given he starts with $10?

A shady restaurant is charging customers gratuities after taxes without them being aware. If my total bill was $160, the sales tax in my city is 8%, I ordered a Ribeye steak for $100, and I ordered a bottle of wine for $20, how much did they charge me for gratuities?

On a normal day, Julia can run a mile in 10 minutes. However, today she decided to wear her new shoes, which slowed her down to 13 minutes per mile. If Julia runs 5 miles every day for a week, how much longer would it take her to run these miles in her new shoes compared to her old ones over the week?

Lance has 70 cents, Margaret has three-fourths of a dollar, Guy has two quarters and a dime, and Bill has six dimes. If each person contributes an additional p cents to their total, how many cents do they have combined after n days, assuming they each add the same amount each day?

Bingley starts with b bracelets. Kelly gives Bingley a fourth of her k bracelets. Then Bingley gives a third of his total bracelets to his little sister. How many bracelets does Bingley have left after these transactions?

A hairstylist charges $5 for a normal haircut, $6 for a special haircut, and $8 for a trendy haircut. If he cuts 5 normal haircuts, 3 special haircuts, and 2 trendy haircuts per day, but on weekends, he offers a discount of $1 on each type of haircut and sees an increase in customers by 50%, how much more money does he earn on weekends compared to weekdays?

A bulk warehous is offring 48 cans o sparklin watar for $12.00 a cas. Tha local grocerry stor is offring tha sam sparklin watar for $6.00 an it onli hav 12 cans. How much mor expensiv, per can, in cents, iz dis deal at tha grocerry stor?
Jennifer decides to visit the museum that is 5 miles away every month, and the museum that is 15 miles away every three months. How many miles will she travel in total over the year?

Léa bought one book for $16, three binders for $2 each, and six notebooks for $1 each. She also decides to buy four pens for $0.50 each. If she has a budget of $30, how much money will she have left after making all her purchases?

Nancy, the librarian, is organizing books from a cart. She first shelves 15 history books, 10 romance books, and 5 poetry books from the top section of the cart. Half of the books in the bottom section are mystery books, which she shelves immediately. She then shelves the remaining books from the bottom, including 7 Western novels and 9 biographies. How many books were on the cart when she started?

Max spends \( t \) minutes on biology homework. He takes twice as long on history and three times as long on geography as he does on history. If Max does this homework routine 5 days a week for \( w \) weeks, how much total time does he spend on homework?

Matt can write 10 words a minute with his right hand and 7 words a minute with his left hand. If he writes for 5 minutes with his right hand and then switches to his left hand for the next 5 minutes, how many more words does he write with his right hand compared to his left hand in total?

Ruby is taking dance lessons. The cost is $75 for 10 classes in one pack. She can add additional classes at the price of 1/3 more than the average price of a class in the pack. If she takes 13 total classes and also decides to take an extra class for each month of the year, how much does she pay in a year?

Stella and Twinkle are filling up a truck with a capacity of 6000 stone blocks at the rate of 250 blocks per hour per person. They work for four hours and are then joined by 6 other people who also work at the same rate. The truck is painted blue and has a logo of a mountain on its side. Stella wears a red hat, and Twinkle has a pet dog that barks every 15 minutes. How many hours did filling the truck take?

Mr. Williams bought 10 gallons of juice for a party. Each gallon has 10 cups. At the party, 5 cups of juice were left. Additionally, he had to buy 2 extra gallons of juice halfway through the party because it was more popular than expected. How many cups of juice were drunk in total?

Kantana loves chocolate. Every Saturday she goes to the candy store and buys 2.5 chocolates for herself and 1.5 for her sister. This last Saturday she picked up an additional 10 chocolates as a birthday gift for her friend Charlie. How many chocolates did Kantana end up buying for the month?
In a neighborhood of \( n \) families, \( a \) families own 2 dogs, \( b \) families own 1 dog, and the rest own 2 cats each. How many dogs and cats are there in all?

A printing press is printing brochures. The press prints 20 single-page spreads and twice as many double-page spreads. For every 4 pages printed for the spreads, the press also prints a block of 4 ads, each taking up a quarter of a page. Additionally, the press prints a special 3-page feature article once every month. The brochures can be arranged in any order as long as they are made up of 5 pages each. How many brochures, including the special feature articles, does the printing press create in a year?

James watched 3 episodes of Jeopardy and 2 episodes of Wheel of Fortune. Jeopardy is 20 minutes long, and each episode of Wheel of Fortune is 1.5 times as long. How many hours did he watch TV in a week, if he watches TV 4 days a week?

In a northwestern town, it rained 3 inches per day during the first 10 days of November. For the remainder of the month, the average daily rainfall was 1.5 times the amount observed during the first 10 days. What is the total amount of rainfall for this town in November, in inches?

A five-layer pyramid is being constructed where each layer has four times as many granite blocks as the layer above it. If the top layer consists of a single block, how many granite blocks are there in the entire pyramid?

Rene can finish reading 30 pages in 60 minutes. Lulu can read 27 pages in 60 minutes, and Cherry can read 25 pages in 60 minutes. If they decide to increase their reading speed by 20% after 120 minutes, how many pages will they have finished reading in total after 240 minutes?

A couple with two children, ages 6 and 10 years old, decided to go to an amusement park. The regular ticket costs $109, but children below 12 years old have a $5 discount. If the family received a total discount of $20 and they gave the cashier $500, how much change will they receive?

It takes 5 people to lift a car and twice as many people to lift a truck. Ali had a collection of seashells. He started with 180 seashells. He then gave away 40 seashells to his friends and 30 seashells to his brothers. After these transactions, he had 200 seashells left. If he sold half of the remaining seashells, how many seashells did he have left?

Samantha has 7 brothers. 3 of them have birthdays in March, 1 of them has a birthday in October, 1 has a birthday in November, and another 2 of them were born in December. If Samantha buys each of her brothers a birthday present and a Christmas present, how many more presents does she have to buy in the second half of the year than the first half of the year, considering that she might also buy an additional present for her brothers who have birthdays in the summer if they visit her?

Emilia is planning to make a berry cobbler and needs a certain number of cartons of berries. She has some cartons of strawberries and blueberries at home, but she isn't sure how many more she needs. She decides to go to the supermarket to buy more cartons. If Emilia needs 42 cartons in total and she already has 2 cartons of strawberries and 7 cartons of blueberries, how many more cartons should she buy? However, she also remembers that her friend promised to bring some cartons of berries, but she isn't sure how many. How many cartons should Emilia buy to ensure she has enough?

Silvia’s bakery is offering a 15% discount on advanced orders over $60.00. She orders 3 quiches for $20.00 each, 8 croissants at $3.50 each, and 10 buttermilk biscuits for $2.50 each. How much will her order be with the discount?

A boxer has a mass of 97 kg at 4 months from a fight. He is on a diet that allows him to lose 3 kg per month until the day of the fight. If his velocity of weight loss is constant, what is his acceleration on the day of the fight?

Kris is preparing for her sister’s party and decides to blow up balloons. She has 30 minutes to blow up as many balloons as possible and asks her brother to help. After 15 minutes, her brother doubles his speed, but Kris decides to take a break for an unknown amount of time. When Kris resumes, she blows up balloons at her original speed. After the 30 minutes, how many balloons, in total, did Kris and her brother blow up?

Nancy, the librarian, is shelving books from the cart. She shelved 12 history books, 8 romance books, and 4 poetry books from the top section of the cart. Half the books on the bottom section of the cart were mystery books, which she quickly put back into place. Then, she shelved the remaining books from the bottom of the cart, including 5 Western novels and 6 biographies. The cart is made of oak and has a capacity of 50 books. Nancy noticed that the cart was slightly heavier on the left side due to a small rock stuck in one of the wheels. How many books did she have on the book cart when she started?

Nancy is filling an aquarium for her fish. She fills it halfway and goes to answer the door. While she's gone, her cat knocks the aquarium over and spills half the water in it. Then Nancy comes back and triples the amount of water in the aquarium, causing the water to become a magical liquid that can float in the air. If the aquarium is 4 feet long, 6 feet wide, and 3 feet high, and the magical liquid occupies twice the volume of regular water, how many cubic feet of magical liquid are floating in the air?

Louie sells Dodge, Hyundai, and Kia vehicles, and his company has 400 vehicles for sale on the store's parking lot. Half of the vehicles on the lot are Dodge, and there are 20 more Hyundai vehicles on the lot than there are Kia vehicles. How many Kia vehicles are on the lot?

Mary has a collection of crayons organized in a chart that shows the number of crayons of each color and the number of crayons she gives to Becky. According to the chart, Mary initially has 5 green crayons and 8 blue crayons. She gives out some crayons to Becky. How many crayons does Mary have left after giving out the crayons shown in the chart? (No chart provided.)

Mark buys a loaf of bread for $4.20 and some cheese for $2.05. He gives the cashier $7.00. If the cashier only has 1 quarter, 1 dime, and 1 nickel in his till, plus a bunch of pennies, how many nickels does Mark get in his change?

Sam and Jeff had a skipping competition at recess. The competition was split into four rounds. Sam completed 1 more skip than Jeff in the first round. Jeff skipped 3 fewer times than Sam in the second round. Jeff skipped 4 more times than Sam in the third round. Jeff got tired and only completed half the number of skips as Sam in the last round. If Sam skipped 16 times in each round and Jeff skipped 20 times in the third round, what is the average number of skips per round completed by Jeff?

How many cars travel down Happy Street from Monday through Sunday?

Uncle Jude baked 300 cookies. He gave 20 cookies to Tim, 25 cookies to Mike, kept some in the fridge, and gave the rest to Anna. If he gave three times as many cookies as he gave Tim to Anna, how many cookies did he put in the fridge?

A school principal is booking hotel rooms for a class of 30 students to stay at during an overnight field trip. The square beds have a diagonal that is 10 feet long, and the room is a perfect circle with a diameter of 10 feet. How many rooms does the principal need to book to fit all of the students in the class?

Lily plans to make sandwiches for a school event. She decides to make 12 sandwiches in total, using 2 slices of bread for each sandwich. If each pack of bread contains 5 slices and she starts with no bread, how many packs of bread does she need to buy to make all the sandwiches?

Steve has a bank account that earns 10% interest every year. He starts by depositing $100 and then adds $10 at the end of each year. Additionally, he withdraws $5 at the end of the first year. How much money is in the account after two years?

Dale and Andrew had breakfast at a cafe. A slice of toast costs £1, and eggs cost £3 each. Dale had 2 slices of toast and 2 eggs. Andrew had 1 slice of toast and 2 eggs. However, the total cost of their breakfast was £10, even though the cafe offers a 20% discount on all items. How much did their breakfast cost before the discount?

Hadley enjoys volunteering at the local library. One day, she arranges 150 books on a shelf. By midday, some books are borrowed. She then adds 50 more books to the shelf. By the end of the day, 40 more books are borrowed, leaving 70 books on the shelf. How many books were borrowed by midday?
Martha has 68 apples. Tim has 30 fewer apples than Martha, and Harry has half as many apples as Tim. If each of them doubles their number of apples next week, how many apples will Harry have then?

A craft store, located in a bustling shopping mall, makes a third of its sales in the fabric section, a quarter of its sales in the jewelry section, and the rest in the stationery section. The store, which has been in business for 15 years, had a special sale day where they offered a 10% discount on all items. On this particular day, they made 36 sales, and the store manager, who has a pet parrot, was particularly excited about the day's performance. How many sales were in the stationery section?

Yvette decides to frame a series of 4 pictures. The frame she originally wanted is 20% more expensive than her budget of $60. Manny had 3 birthday cookie pies to share with his 24 classmates and his teacher, Mr. Keith. If each of the cookie pies were cut into 10 slices and each slice magically doubled in size every time someone took a bite, how many slices would be left after everyone, including Manny and Mr. Keith, had 1 piece?

How much money does Harriett find by the end of the year?

Jasper is planning a series of dinner parties.
