For each subsequent party, he increases the amount of cheddar cheese by 1 pound and adjusts the other ingredients proportionally. If he hosts 4 dinner parties, how much does he spend in total on the ingredients?
John has a derivative of five more roommates than the integral of twice as many as Bob. If Bob has 10 roommates, what is the coefficient of John’s roommates?

James has a rainwater collection barrel. For each inch of rain, he collects 15 gallons. On Monday, it rained 4 inches and on Tuesday, it rained 3 inches. He can sell water for $1.2 per gallon. However, due to a magical spell, the water in his barrel doubles in volume every hour. If he sells all the water after 24 hours, how much money did he make?

Jenna's doctor advises her to tan no more than 200 minutes a month. If she tans 30 minutes a day, two days a week for the first two weeks, and decides to reduce her tanning time by 10 minutes per day in the last two weeks, how many days can she tan in the last two weeks of the month without exceeding the doctor's recommendation?

Krystian works in the library and borrows an average of 40 books every day. Every Friday, his number of borrowed books is about 40% higher than the daily average. However, on Fridays, he also returns 20% of the books he borrowed earlier in the week. How many books does he borrow in a week if the library is open from Monday to Friday, and he never returns any books on the same day he borrows them?
James decides to upgrade his car. He sold his $25,000 car for 75% of its value and managed to negotiate a $35,000 sticker price car down to 85% of its value. How much did he spend out of pocket?

In a magical forest, if the number of fairies that join the dance circle every night increases by 5, and this increase is the same as the number of rabbits in the cage after seven more are added to the thirteen already there, then the total number of fairies in the dance circle is 1/3 the number of rabbits Jasper saw in the park today. How many rabbits did Jasper see in the park today?
At the dog park, Madison notices that half the dogs, including her own, have spots, and 1/5 of the dogs have pointy ears. If 15 dogs have spots, how many dogs, including Madison's, have pointy ears?

Toby is counting goldfish in the local pond. He knows that 125% of the goldfish are at the surface and the rest are too deep below the surface to be able to see. If he counts 15 goldfish, how many are below the surface?

Nick has 60 cans. Each can takes up 30 square inches of space before being compacted and 20% of that amount after being compacted. However, 10% of the cans are damaged and take up 50% more space even after being compacted. How much total space do all the cans take up after being compacted?
In 3 years, Jayden will be the derivative of Ernesto's age. If Ernesto is 11 years old, how many years old is Jayden now?

Nick has q quarters. \( \frac{2}{5} \) of the quarters are state quarters, and \( \frac{1}{2} \) of the state quarters are from Pennsylvania. How many Pennsylvania state quarters does Nick have in terms of q?
There are 50 students in a class. If 1/5 are absent, 2/3 of the students who are present are in the classroom, and the rest are in the library, how many students are in the library?

Marnie makes bead bracelets. She bought 5 bags of 50 beads and 2 bags of 100 beads. If 50 beads are used to make one bracelet, and Marnie decides to use some of the beads for a special project, how many bracelets will Marnie be able to make if she uses the remaining beads?
Tommy wants to buy 7.5 new books. Each book costs $5. If Tommy already has $15, how much more money does he need to save up?
Matt can buy key chains in packs of 10 for $20 or in packs of 4 for $12. If he needs to buy 50 key chains for a school event, how much money can he save by choosing the cheaper option?

Randy has 1 more baseball glove than 7 times the number of bats he has. If he also has 3 times as many baseballs as bats and a total of 29 baseball gloves, how many bats and baseballs does he have in total?

Loraine makes wax sculptures of animals. Large animals take 5 sticks of wax and small animals take 3 sticks. She made twice as many small animals as large animals, and she used 18 sticks of wax for small animals. How many sticks of wax did Loraine use to make all the animals?

Mr. Lu's computer store sold a total of 72 computers last month. Half of the sales were laptops, one-third were netbooks, and the remaining computers were desktops. However, due to a magical spell, the number of desktop computers sold was negative 12. How many laptops and netbooks were sold?
Angie bought 3.5 lbs. of coffee at the store today. Each lb. of coffee will brew about 40 cups of coffee. Angie drinks 3.2 cups of coffee every day. How many days will this coffee last her?

Jasmine has a 2-liter container of milk. She pours 200 ml for her breakfast cereal every morning. If she goes on a 5-day vacation and doesn’t use any milk, how many full 200 ml portions can she pour for the rest of the month, assuming there are 30 days in the month?

Sarah's age is three times Mark's age minus 4. Mark is four years older than Billy. Billy is half as old as Ana. If Ana is currently 12 years old and will be 15 in 3 years, how old will Sarah be in 5 years?

James attends a club that charges $20 to enter. For his 5 friends, he buys 2 rounds of drinks, and for himself, he buys 6 drinks. Each drink costs $6. He also orders fried chicken for $14 and decides to leave a 30% tip on all his orders. Additionally, the club has a special event 4 times a year where the entry fee is doubled and he buys an extra round of drinks for everyone. How much does James spend in a year for these club visits?
Every year, Mabel gets as many quarters as her age and also receives an additional 50 cents from her grandparents. How much money will she have in her piggy bank when she turns 10?

Marvin and Tina were selling custom-designed bookmarks to raise funds for their school library. Each bookmark was priced at $3. Marvin sold 40 bookmarks. Tina sold 2.5 times as many bookmarks as Marvin. How much more money did Tina raise for the library compared to Marvin?

A town is holding a special fireworks display for New Year’s Eve. They light enough fireworks to show the current year, then light enough to spell out “HAPPY NEW YEAR” in the sky. They also light an additional 50 boxes of fireworks for the main display. Each box contains 8 fireworks. If it takes 6 fireworks to display a number and 7 fireworks to display a letter, and there are 12 holidays in a year where they light an extra box of fireworks for each holiday, how many fireworks are lit during the year, including the New Year’s Eve display?

Elizabeth uses $3.00 worth of ingredients to make a bag of granola. She makes x bags and sells them for $6.00 a bag at the farmer's market. An hour before closing, she has sold y bags and marks the remaining z bags down to $4.00 and sells them soon after. What is her net profit in terms of x, y, and z?

Kyle bought 2 glass bottles that can hold 15 origami stars each. He then bought another 4 identical glass bottles. If he decides to fill only 75% of each bottle, how many stars must Kyle make to fill all the glass bottles he bought?

Marla is planning the lunch menu for an elementary school. There are \( x \) third grade classes with 30 students each, \( y \) fourth grade classes with 28 students each, and \( z \) fifth grade classes with 27 students each. Each student gets a hamburger, which costs \( a \) dollars, some carrots, which cost \( b \) dollars, and a cookie, which costs \( c \) dollars. How much does one lunch for all the students cost in terms of \( x \), \( y \), \( z \), \( a \), \( b \), and \( c \)?

Ten friends decide to get an end-of-year gift for their teacher. They plan to split the cost of the gift equally. However, 3.5 of the group drop out. The remaining friends split the cost equally among themselves. If each share is now $8 more, how much does the gift cost, in dollars?

Mason has 3 cartons of 200 blueberries each. He uses 10 blueberries to make each blueberry muffin and also makes 60 cinnamon muffins. If he wants to ensure that at least 60% of all the muffins he makes have blueberries, how many more blueberry muffins does he need to make?

Trey is planning his Sunday chores and decides to make a To Do list. He lists several tasks under 'clean the house,' 'take a shower,' and 'make dinner.' There are 7 tasks for cleaning the house, 1 task for taking a shower, and 4 tasks for making dinner. Each task on his list is supposed to take 10 minutes to complete. However, Trey also notes that some tasks, especially those under 'clean the house,' might take longer if they are particularly messy. If the total time for all tasks is calculated based on the assumption that each task takes 10 minutes, how many hours will it take to complete Trey's list, considering that some tasks might take longer but the exact duration is not specified?

A cleaning company produces two sanitizer sprays. One spray kills 75% of germs, and another spray kills 50% of germs. However, 60% of the germs they kill are the same ones. What percentage of germs would be left after using both sanitizer sprays together?

Four friends, Alex, Bella, Charlie, and Dana, participated in a weight loss challenge. Alex, who is 30 years old and loves jogging, lost 27 kilograms. Bella, who is Alex's sister and prefers yoga, lost 7 kilograms less than Alex. Charlie and Dana, who are twins and both enjoy swimming, lost the same amount of weight. The challenge was sponsored by a local gym, and the participants were given free protein shakes, which they all enjoyed. How many kilograms did each of the last two people lose?
A boat makes several trips through the lake each day. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?

There are 1250 pairs of shoes in the warehouse. 540 pairs are blue. The remaining pairs are either green or purple, and the number of green pairs is twice the number of purple pairs. How many pairs of purple shoes are in the warehouse?

Brian is making lasagna for a family gathering. The recipe requires 1/2 a cup of milk per serving. If each of the 8 family members is expected to eat 2 servings, and Brian also plans to make an additional 4 servings for leftovers, how many 1L cartons of milk does he need to buy?

Stella and Twinkle are filling up a truck with a capacity of 6000 stone blocks at the rate of 250 blocks per hour per person. They work for four hours and are then joined by 6 other people who also work at the same rate. However, the truck can only hold a maximum of 5000 stone blocks. How many hours did filling the truck take?

A florist arranged a special display of flowers for a wedding. The display included roses and lilies, with the number of lilies being 3/4 times the number of roses. The prices of the flowers are shown in the chart below. If the total cost of the flowers in the display was $350, how many roses were in the display? (No chart provided.)
Leticia, Nina, and Rosalie have a dance team with a total of \( t \) people. If \( q \) people quit and \( n \) new people join, how many people are on the team now?

Conor can chop 12 eggplants, 9 carrots, and 8 potatoes in a day. If he works 4 times a week and also chops an additional 15 vegetables for each special market day (which occurs 6 times a year), how many vegetables can he chop in a year?

Carmen needs $10 more to have three times the amount of money that Jethro has. Meanwhile, Patricia has $75, which is 5 times as much as Jethro. If Jethro saves an additional $5 every month, how much money will all three have combined after one year?

Amara had 100 pieces of clothing. She donated 5 pieces to one orphanage and triple that amount to another. After donating, she also decided to throw away 15 old clothes. If she then bought 20 new pieces of clothing, how many pieces of clothing does she have now?

Nico borrows 4 books from the library on Monday. On Monday, he reads the first book with a total of 20 pages. On Tuesday, he reads the second book with a total of 15 pages. On Wednesday, he reads the third book, and on Thursday, he reads the fourth book. If he has read a total of 82 pages from Monday to Thursday, how many pages did he read on Wednesday and Thursday combined?
Alice has 20 quarters. She exchanges them for nickels at the bank. Some of the nickels are iron nickels worth $3 each. What is the total value of her money now?

Nancy is filling an aquarium for her fish. She fills it halfway and goes to answer the door. While she's gone, her cat spills some of the water. Then Nancy comes back and triples the amount of water in the aquarium. If the aquarium is 4 feet long and 6 feet wide, how many cubic feet of water are in the aquarium?

Gail has two fish tanks. The first tank is three times the size of the second tank. There are 72 gallons of water in the first tank. She follows the rule of one gallon of water per inch of fish. If she keeps two-inch fish in the second tank and four-inch fish in the first tank, how many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank if two of the first tank fish eat each other?
Jessa needs to make cupcakes for 3 fourth-grade classes and a P.E. class. How many cupcakes does she need to make?

Henry took 9 pills a day for 14 days. Of these 9 pills, 4 pills cost $1.50 each, and the other pills each cost $5.50 more. If the total cost of the pills is represented by the hypotenuse of a right triangle with legs measuring $1.50 and $5.50, how much did he spend in total on the pills?
Tom reads 10 hours over 5 days and can read 50 pages per hour. If he decides to read an additional 2 hours each weekend day, how many pages does he read in a 7-day week?

While preparing for a conference, Bill fills Dixie cups with water from a water cooler. The water cooler starts with 5 gallons of water, and each Dixie cup holds 8 ounces of water. If Bill fills one cup of water for each meeting chair, and there are 6 rows of meeting chairs with 12 chairs in each row, and additionally, he fills an extra cup for each of the 4 speakers, how many ounces of water will be left in the cooler after all cups have been filled? (There are 128 ounces in a gallon.)

The largest frog can grow to weigh 10 times as much as the smallest frog. If the largest frog weighs 120 pounds and the smallest frog doubles its weight during the rainy season, how much more does the largest frog weigh than the smallest frog during the rainy season?

John buys 30 ducks for $10 each. Each duck weighs 4 pounds, and he sells them for $5 per pound. However, for every 5 ducks sold, he offers a discount of $2 per pound on the next duck. How much profit does he make after selling all the ducks?
There are 40 students in a class. If some are absent, and a fraction of the students who are present are in the classroom, how many students are in the canteen?
In 3 years, Jayden will be half of Ernesto's age. How old is Jayden now?

A boat can take up to 12 people during one trip. During one day, the boat makes 4 trips, but on the second day, it makes 8 trips, each trip doubling the boat's capacity. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?

Sally and Bob have made plans to go on a trip at the end of the year. They both decide to work as babysitters and save half of what they've earned for their trip. If Sally makes $6 per day and Bob makes $4 per day, what is the combined circumference of their savings after a year?

Lily had $m in her account. She spent $s on a shirt. She then went to another shop and spent 3s dollars. If she also had to pay a $5 fee for each transaction, how much money is left in Lily's account after both purchases and the fees?

Max has a magical model train that can shrink in size. Every time he receives a new train, the size of all his trains is halved. Over 5 years, he receives one train each birthday and two trains each Christmas, just like before. At the end of 5 years, his parents give him double the number of trains he already has, but the trains continue to shrink in size. If the original size of each train was 1 meter long, how long will all the trains be combined after they have been shrunk and doubled?

Sarah and Mark are planning a trip. They decide to save money together, starting with Sarah saving $50. Each week, Sarah saves an amount that is half of what Mark saves, and Mark saves an amount that is double what Sarah saved the previous week. How much will they have saved together after 4 weeks?

Lilah's family gallery has 400 photos. On a trip to the Grand Canyon, they took some photos on the first day and more photos on the second day. If they added all these photos to the family gallery, calculate the total number of photos in the gallery.

Peter goes to the store to buy a soda. The soda costs $0.25 an ounce. He brought $2 with him and leaves with $0.50. The soda bottle is a perfect cube with a volume of 100 cubic inches. How many ounces of soda did he buy, and what is the length of one side of the cube?

Dale and Andrew are sitting at a round table with a diameter of 1 meter. The table is also a perfect square with sides measuring 1 meter. Dale had 2 slices of toast and 2 eggs, while Andrew had 1 slice of toast and 2 eggs. If the cost of a slice of toast is £1 and an egg is £3, how much did their breakfast cost?

John decides to get gym memberships so he can get in shape. The gym close to his house is underwater and requires scuba gear to use, costing $10 a month with a sign-up fee of $50. The second gym is located on the moon and is 3 times more expensive, with a sign-up fee equal to 4 months of membership. How much total did he pay in the first year for gym membership?

Janice can type 6 sentences per minute. Today at work, Janice continued working on a paper she started typing yesterday. She typed for 20 minutes, took a break, and typed 15 minutes longer. She then had to erase 40 sentences she had typed incorrectly. After a meeting, she typed for 18 minutes more. In all, the paper had 536 sentences by the end of today. However, it is also known that Janice started today with 300 sentences already typed. How many sentences did she start with today?

Hans booked a room in a hotel. The hotel has 10 floors with 10 identical rooms on each floor. Because of an accident, the last floor is unavailable for the guests. However, the hotel manager insists that all 100 rooms are available for booking. Considering there are no other guests, in how many different rooms could Hans be checked in?

Daniela goes shopping during a sale. The store offers a 30% discount on shoes and a 25% discount on dresses. If Daniela buys 3 pairs of shoes originally priced at $60 each and 2 dresses originally priced at $120 each, how much money does she spend?

A parking garage near Nora's house has \( s \) stories, with \( p \) parking spots per level. On the first level, there are \( o_1 \) open spots. Each subsequent level has \( d \) more open spots than the previous level, except the last level, which has \( o_s \) open spots. If the first level has 58 open spots, the second level has 2 more open spots than the first, the third level has 5 more open spots than the second, and the fourth level has 31 open spots, how many full parking spots are there in all for \( s \) stories?

Thomas owns 200 books. He decides to sell them and use the money to buy records. Each book sells for $1.50, and a record costs $3. If he buys 75 records, but also decides to save 10% of his total earnings, how much money does he have left over after buying the records and saving?

James and his partner decide to build a rectangular garden. The length of the garden is 10 meters more than its width. They also want to include a circular pond inside the garden, which has a diameter equal to the width of the garden. However, the area of the pond is somehow greater than the area of the garden. What is the width of the garden?
Suraya picked 15.5 apples more than Caleb, and Caleb picked 4.5 apples less than Kayla. If Kayla picked 22.5 apples, how many more apples did Suraya pick than Kayla?

A clothing store sells \( s \) shirts and \( j \) pairs of jeans. Each shirt costs \( p \) dollars, and each pair of jeans costs \( 2p \) dollars. If the store sells all shirts and jeans, how much will the store earn in \( w \) weeks, assuming the sales rate remains constant?

Sarah plans to save a certain number of coins to buy a special gift. In the first week, she saves 20 coins. In the second week, she saves twice as many coins as she did in the first week. In the third week, she saves 10 coins less than what she saved in the second week. For the remaining weeks of the month, she saves an equal number of coins each week. If Sarah saves a total of 120 coins by the end of the month, how many coins did she save each week for the rest of the month?

Marvin and Tina were selling candy bars to help fund their class trip. The candy bars cost $2 each. Marvin sold 35 candy bars total. Tina sold three times the number of candy bars as Marvin. They decided to arrange the candy bars they sold into a rectangular prism where the length is 7 candy bars, the width is 5 candy bars, and the height is 3 candy bars. If the volume of this rectangular prism is 105 cubic candy bars, how much more money did Tina make for the class trip selling candy bars compared to Marvin?

Sandy orders drinks for a group at the café. She buys c cappuccinos at $2 each, t iced teas at $3 each, l cafe lattes at $1.5 each, and e espressos at $1 each. If Sandy pays with a $20 bill, how much change does she receive in terms of c, t, l, and e?

Max has 8 children. Six of his children each have the same number of children as Max has, while the other two have 5 children each. How many grandchildren does Max have in total after 3 years, if each of his grandchildren has one additional child every year?

Nancy is filling an aquarium for her fish. She fills it halfway and goes to answer the door. While she's gone, her cat, who is wearing a blue collar, knocks the aquarium over and spills half the water in it. Then Nancy comes back and triples the amount of water in the aquarium. The aquarium is 4 feet long, 6 feet wide, and 3 feet high, and it is made of glass that is 0.5 inches thick. If the aquarium is placed on a wooden stand that is 2 feet long, 3 feet wide, and 1 foot high, how many cubic feet of water are in the aquarium?

Christian and Sue are planning to buy a $50.00 bottle of perfume for their mom's birthday. Initially, Christian has $5.00 and Sue has $7.00. Christian decides to mow 4 lawns, charging $5.00 per lawn, and Sue decides to walk 6 dogs, charging $2.00 per dog. After these jobs, they also plan to do additional chores: Christian will wash 3 cars for $3.00 each, and Sue will babysit for 2 hours at $4.00 per hour. How much more money will they need to make in order to buy the bottle of perfume for their mom?
Emma takes 50 more than five times as many chocolate chip cookies as oatmeal cookies. If she has 120 oatmeal cookies, how many cookies does she have in total?

A circular lake has a diameter of 10 meters. A boat, which is shaped like a square with a side length of 15 meters, makes 4 trips across the lake each day. The boat can carry up to 12 people per trip. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?

Martin owns a farm with hens. Initially, 10 hens lay 80 eggs in 10 days. Martin decides to buy 15 more hens, and each hen's egg-laying rate increases by 10% due to better feeding conditions. How many eggs will all the hens lay in 15 days?

Katie and her family love to dunk donuts in coffee. They find that for every 4 donuts, they need 3 ounces of coffee. Each pot of coffee they make contains 15 ounces and costs $4 to prepare. If Katie’s family eats 5 dozen donuts in a week, how much will they spend on coffee over 4 weeks?

Four classmates were comparing their ages based on their birth month. They found out that Jolyn is 2.5 months older than Therese while Therese is 5.2 months older than Aivo. Then, Leon is 2.3 months older than Aivo. How much older in months is Jolyn than Leon?

James watched 2 episodes of Jeopardy and 2 episodes of Wheel of Fortune. Each episode of Jeopardy is 20 minutes long, and each episode of Wheel of Fortune is twice as long. James watched these shows while eating popcorn, which he prepared in a large red bowl that can hold up to 10 cups. He also drank a 16-ounce soda, which he finished halfway through the second episode of Wheel of Fortune. How many hours did he spend watching TV?

In a conference room, chairs were arranged in rows for a board meeting. If 2/5 of the chairs were not occupied, and the rest each had two people, calculate the number of board members who did attend the meeting.

Baez has a rectangular box that can hold exactly 25 marbles. One day, she loses 20% of her marbles. Her friend then gives her double the amount she has left. She tries to fit all her marbles back into the box, but the box has magically transformed into a circle with a circumference of 25 marbles. How many marbles does Baez have, and can she fit them all into the circular box?

In a conference room, 40 chairs with a capacity of 2 people each were arranged in rows in preparation for the board meeting of a company, whose number of members was the same as the chairs' capacity. The conference room was located on the 10th floor of a skyscraper, and the meeting was scheduled to start at 10:00 AM. The company's CEO, who was known for his punctuality, arrived 15 minutes early. If 2/5 of the chairs were not occupied, and the rest each had two people, calculate the number of board members who did attend the meeting.

Texas Integrated School initially has 15 classes with 20 students per class. After adding five more classes, they also decided to increase the number of students per class by 5. How many students will the school have now?
In ten years, I'll be twice my sister's age, and the product of our ages at that time will be 270. How old am I now?
Winwin win 50 dollor, she pai 20% tax an 5 dollor procesing. How much she take home, got left?

Austin and Jake start descending from the 12th floor of a building at the same time. Austin uses the elevator, which takes 1.5 minutes to reach the ground level. Jake uses the stairs, descending 4 steps every second. If each floor has 35 steps, how many seconds later will Jake reach the ground floor compared to Austin?

Ruth prepared a batch of sandwiches. She ate 1 sandwich, gave 2 sandwiches to her brother, and her first cousin arrived and ate 2 sandwiches. Then, her two other cousins arrived and ate 1 sandwich each. After that, her aunt visited and ate 2 more sandwiches. If there were 5 sandwiches left, how many sandwiches did Ruth prepare?

A bag of pistachios has 120 pistachios in it. 85 percent have shells, and 70 percent of those have shells that are opened. Additionally, 10 percent of the pistachios without shells are actually wrapped in a thin, edible coating. How many pistachios in the bag have shells and have an opened shell?

A baker has 10 cheesecakes on the display and 15 more are still in the fridge. If the baker has sold 7 cheesecakes from the display and then moved some cheesecakes from the fridge to the display, how many cheesecakes are left to be sold?

Henry took 9 pills a day for 14 days. Of these 9 pills, 4 pills cost $1.50 each, and the other pills each cost $5.50 more. Henry’s doctor, Dr. Smith, who has been practicing for 25 years, prescribed these pills after a thorough check-up that lasted 45 minutes. Henry’s pharmacy, located 3 miles from his house, is open from 9 AM to 6 PM, and the pharmacist, Ms. Johnson, has a cat named Whiskers. How much did Henry spend in total on the pills?

Missy had a giant piggy bank in her bedroom. Every day she would search the house for change to put in her bank. After 5 years, the bank was opened and it contained $600 in change. If the second, third, fourth, and fifth year she doubled the amount of money she put in the bank from the amount she had put in the previous year, how much money, in dollars, did she put in the bank the first year?

A magical tree produces candies at a rate of 50 candies per second. Jack came and took half of all the candies produced in the last 10 seconds and 4 more candies. Then, in the next instant, Paul came and took the remaining 7 sweets, which included 3 candies that spontaneously turned into gold coins. How many candies were on the table at first?

Trevor recorded the number of carnations in each bouquet he bought over several weeks. The chart below shows the number of carnations in each bouquet for each week. What is the average number of carnations in the bouquets for Week 3? (No chart provided.)

During one day, there are 4 boat trips through the lake. The boat, which is painted blue and has a capacity of 12 people per trip, is operated by a captain named John who has been working for 10 years. The boat also has a small deck where passengers can enjoy the view, and it takes 15 minutes to complete each trip. How many people can the boat transport in 2 days?

Emerson and his friends are avid rowers who never skip a weekend. One weekend, Emerson started his rowing trip and reached 6 miles away from his starting point. He then rowed another 15 miles at a constant speed, took a short break, and finally covered the last 18 miles. If Emerson also rows an additional 10 miles during each of the 8 major rowing festivals in a year, what is the total distance he rows in a year, considering he rows the same distance every weekend?

Sarah went to the market and bought some fruits. She bought apples, bananas, and oranges. She also bought some vegetables, including carrots, tomatoes, and potatoes. Each apple costs $2, each banana costs $1, and each orange costs $3. The carrots cost $1.50 each, tomatoes cost $2 each, and potatoes cost $1 each. Sarah bought twice as many apples as bananas and the same number of oranges as carrots. She also bought more tomatoes than potatoes. How much did Sarah spend in total?

Harper drinks 1/2 a bottle of mineral water per day. She buys the mineral water by the case at a big box store, where each case contains 24 bottles and is on sale for $12.00. If she wants to buy enough cases to last her 365 days, and she also buys an additional case for every 10 cases to stock up for unexpected guests, how much will she spend in total?
4.5 gallons of coffee were divided among 18 thermoses. Genevieve drank 3 thermoses, and her friend Leo drank 2 thermoses. How many more pints of coffee did Genevieve drink compared to Leo?

After shearing her 200 sheep, Azalea paid the shearer who had come to help her with the work $2000 for his job. Each of the sheared sheep produced 10 pounds of wool. If Ms. Azalea sold a pound of wool at $20 and the cost of maintaining each sheep for the year was $50, how much profit did she make from the produce of her sheep farm after accounting for maintenance costs?

Brandon's gecko sales can be modeled by the function \( f(x) = 2x \), where \( x \) is the number of geckos sold in the current year. If Brandon sold 86 geckos last year, what is the derivative of the function representing the total number of geckos sold over the last two years?

In Alaska, the commercial Cod fishing season runs from January 1 - August 1, lasting exactly 7 months, or 213 days on a non-leap year. Two fishermen are competing to see who can earn more profit. The first fisherman plans to catch fish at a steady rate of 3 per day for the entire season. The second fisherman, who is a novice, starts more slowly, catching 1 fish per day during the first 30 days, 2 fish per day during the next 60 days, and then increases his rate by 1 fish per day every 30 days for the remainder of the season. At the end of the season, how many more fish will be caught by the fisherman who catches the higher number of fish?

Billy has 8 hours of free time each day on the weekend. He decides to spend 75% of his free time playing video games and the remaining time reading. If he reads at a rate of 60 pages per hour and each book he reads is 80 pages long, how many books can he finish reading over the course of a month, assuming there are 4 weekends in a month?

This year, the school library not only purchased 3 times as many books as the 50 new books it bought last year but also received a donation of 20 books from a local author. If the library had 100 books before any purchases or donations last year, how many books are in the library now?

Mr. Montero is planning a road trip and needs to calculate his fuel requirements. The trip involves traveling to a destination 600 miles away and then returning home. The fuel efficiency of his car is shown in the table below, which indicates how many miles he can travel per gallon of gas at different speeds. Mr. Montero currently has 8 gallons of gas in his car. How many more gallons of gas does he need to complete his round trip? (No table provided.)

Grayson drives his motorboat for 1 hour at 25 mph and then 0.5 hours at 20 mph. If the weather conditions worsen, reducing his speed by 10% for the last 0.5 hours, how far does he travel? Rudy rows in his rowboat for 3 hours at 10 mph, but if the current helps him, increasing his speed by 2 mph for the last hour, how much farther, in miles, does Grayson go compared to Rudy?

Mckenna's daily schedule is illustrated in a timeline chart that shows her activities and the duration of each activity. Using the chart, determine how many hours Mckenna spends in meetings with her team of developers. (No chart provided.)

Jeanette is practicing her juggling. Each week she can juggle 2 more objects than the week before. If she starts out juggling 3 objects and practices for 5 weeks, but by the end of the third week, she can only juggle 5 objects, how many objects can she juggle by the end of the fifth week?

At the beginning of the month, there were $21 in the cookie jar. Doris spent $6, and Martha spent half as much as Doris. Each week, an additional $5 is added to the cookie jar. How much money, in dollars, is in the cookie jar at the end of the month?

Ann is baking cookies in a zero-gravity space station. She bakes three dozen oatmeal raisin cookies, two dozen sugar cookies, and four dozen chocolate chip cookies. Due to the lack of gravity, each cookie expands to the size of a basketball. Ann gives away two dozen oatmeal raisin cookies, 1.5 dozen sugar cookies, and 2.5 dozen chocolate chip cookies. How many total basketball-sized cookies does she keep?

Celine buys two laptops and four smartphones for her children. If there is a 10% chance that any device might be defective and need to be exchanged for a new one, which costs the shop an additional $50 for each exchange, how much does she actually spend in total if she initially has $3000 and receives the correct change?
Alyssa, Keely, and Kendall ordered 100 chicken nuggets from a fast-food restaurant. Keely and Kendall each ate twice the derivative of Alyssa’s nuggets. How many nuggets did Alyssa eat?

Napoleon has 17 jelly beans, and Sedrich has 4 more jelly beans than Napoleon. If the total number of jelly beans that Napoleon and Sedrich have together is increased by 10 and then divided by 3, the result is equal to the number of jelly beans that Mikey has. How many jelly beans does Mikey have?

Richard can clean his room in 22 minutes. Cory takes 3 minutes more than Richard to clean her room, while Blake can clean his room 4 minutes more quickly than Cory. If they have to clean their rooms twice a week, what is the combined frequency of their cleaning efforts each week?

Stella and Twinkle are filling up a truck with a capacity of 6000 stone blocks at the rate of 250 blocks per hour per person. They work for four hours and are then joined by 6 other people who also work at the same rate. The truck is shaped like a perfect cube with a side length of 10 meters, but it can only hold 6000 stone blocks. How many hours did filling the truck take?
Tim has fewer apples than Martha, and Harry has half as many apples as Tim. If Martha has 68 apples, how many apples does Harry have?

A coffee shop brews \( c \) coffee cups per hour on weekdays and \( w \) coffee cups in total over the weekend. If the coffee shop is open \( h \) hours a day every single day, how many coffee cups are brewed in \( d \) days?

Janice can type 6 sentences per minute. Today at work, Janice continued working on a paper she started typing yesterday. She typed for 20 minutes, took a break to have a cup of tea, and typed 15 minutes longer. During her break, she checked her emails and replied to 5 messages. She then had to erase 40 sentences she had typed incorrectly because her cat walked across the keyboard. After a meeting that lasted 45 minutes, during which she took 10 pages of notes, she typed for 18 minutes more. In all, the paper had 536 sentences by the end of today. How many sentences did she start with today?

Utopia National Park hosted 35,000 elephants on Friday night. The next morning, there was a 5-hour elephant exodus out of the park, at a constant rate of 3,000 elephants/hour. Over the next 8-hour period, new elephants entered the park at a constant rate. If the final number of elephants in the park was 32,000, at what rate did the new elephants enter the park?

John decides to update his shoe collection by buying a $150 pair of Nikes, a $120 pair of work boots, and a $90 pair of casual sandals. Tax is 10%, and he also has a 15% off coupon that can be applied to the shoes before tax. How much did he pay for everything?

Max has a chart that tracks the number of model trains he receives each year. The chart shows the number of trains he gets for his birthday and Christmas over 5 years. At the end of the 5 years, his parents give him double the number of trains he already has. How many trains does Max have now? (No chart provided.)

Phil has a coin collection that began with 50 state quarters his parents gave him. In the first year, he doubled his collection. The following year, he added 3 quarters each month. The next year, he added 1 quarter every third month. In the fourth year, he decided to give away 10% of his collection to his younger sister. How many quarters did Phil have left after giving some away?

John orders food for a massive restaurant. He orders 1000 pounds of beef for $8 per pound. He also orders twice that much chicken at $3 per pound, but the total cost of the chicken is $1500. How much did everything cost?

A book has 8 chapters. Beth has read 2 chapters in 3 hours. She decides to read more each day, increasing her reading time by 30 minutes every day. If she continues this pattern, how many days will it take her to finish reading the book?

The owner of a Turkish restaurant wanted to prepare traditional dishes for an upcoming celebration. She ordered ground beef, in four-pound packages, from three different butchers. The following morning, the first butcher delivered 10 packages. A couple of hours later, 7 packages arrived from the second butcher. Finally, the third butcher’s delivery arrived at dusk. If all the ground beef delivered by the three butchers weighed 100 pounds, and the third butcher delivered only 5 packages, how many pounds of ground beef did the first butcher actually deliver?

Manny had 3 birthday cookie pies to share with his 24 classmates and his teacher, Mr. Keith. Each of the cookie pies was cut into 10 slices. Manny, his classmates, and Mr. Keith all had 1 piece each. The classroom was decorated with balloons and streamers, and the party lasted for 2 hours. Manny's favorite color is blue, and he wore a red shirt to the party. How many slices of cookie pie are left after the party?
James spends 40 years teaching. His partner has been teaching for 10 years less, but together they claim to have 95 years of combined teaching experience. How long has his partner been teaching?
Toby is counting goldfish in the local pond. He counts 15 goldfish at the surface. How many goldfish are in the pond?

Ann, Becky, and Julia work at a pharmacy. Each works for 8 hours a day and serves 7 customers per hour. One day, Julia had to leave early and only worked for 6 hours. If Ann and Becky each worked their full shift, how many customers did they serve in total that day?

During a quiet week on Happy Street, the fewest cars pass by on Sunday, with only 5 cars. On Monday, 20% more cars are seen compared to Sunday. Tuesday sees a 50% increase over Monday. Wednesday has 3 fewer cars than Tuesday. Thursday and Friday each have 10 cars. How many cars travel down Happy Street from Sunday through Friday?

Irene is designing a rectangular garden where the length is 10 feet more than the width. She decides to add a triangular section to one corner of the garden, where the triangle has three right angles. If the area of the rectangular part of the garden is 120 square feet, and Irene worked 50 hours last week earning her usual rate plus overtime, calculate her total income and the dimensions of the garden.

Loraine makes wax sculptures of animals. Large animals take four sticks of wax and small animals take two sticks. She made three times as many small animals as large animals. How many sticks of wax did Loraine use to make all the animals?

Prudence is launching her cupcake business. Each cupcake costs her $0.75 to produce. On her first try, she burnt the first 2 dozen cupcakes and had to discard them. Her next batch of 2 dozen came out perfect, but she couldn't resist and ate 5 right away. Later, she made another 2 dozen cupcakes and ate 4 more. If she sells the remaining cupcakes at $2.00 each, and she also offers a special deal of 10% off on weekends, how much is her net profit over a month, assuming there are 4 weekends?
Josh built his little brother a rectangular sandbox. The perimeter of the sandbox is 48 feet and the length is three times the width. What is the width of the sandbox?

A school organized a field trip, and the students were divided into three groups: Group A, Group B, and Group C. The distribution of students across these groups is shown in the pie chart below. If the total number of students is 120, how many students are in Group B? (No chart provided.)
Winwin won some money in a lottery. She paid a certain percentage for tax and a fixed amount for the processing fee. How much did she take home?
In a box of 72 pieces of fruit, one-third of the box contains oranges. There are twice as many peaches as oranges, and there are three times as many apples as peaches. How many apples are in the box?

Kevin has been for a run and wants to calculate how far he traveled. He started running at 10 miles per hour for half an hour, then increased his speed to 20 miles per hour for another half an hour. After that, he slowed down to 8 miles per hour, but it’s not clear if he continued running for another 15 minutes or if he ran for a total of 45 minutes. How many miles has Kevin run?

It takes Camilla 45 minutes to prepare a batch of pizza dough, which can make 4 pizzas, and another 30 minutes to cook 2 pizzas at a time in the oven. How many hours would it take her to finish making 16 pizzas?
Brady will make $450 more in a year than Dwayne. If Dwayne's annual earnings increase by $100 every three months starting from $1,200, how much will Brady and Dwayne make combined in a year?
In a jar that initially contains 50 ants, the number of ants doubles every h hours. How many ants will be in the jar after t hours?

Marcy is a makeup artist and has agreed to do some makeup for her friend's wedding. She decides to bring 6 tubs of lip gloss, each of which holds 2 tubes of lip gloss. Each tube of lip gloss will hold enough lip gloss for 3 people's makeup. Marcy also plans to set up her makeup station in a circular room with a square ceiling that has a side length of 10 feet. If the circular room has a diameter of 15 feet, how many people is Marcy painting with makeup?

A soccer team had 24 players prepared for a soccer game. The first half saw 11 players start the game with 2 substitutions made. In the second half, the team made twice as many substitutions as in the first half, and additionally, 1 player was sent off and could not be replaced. How many players on the team did not play that day?

Thre kat sat oan a fense, meowin at da moon. Da firs kat meow 3 timez per minit. Da secnd kat meowd twise az frquent az da firs kat. An da thrid kat meowd won-thre th frqncy ov da secnd kat. Wat iz da combind totl numbr ov meowz da thre kat make in 5 minits?
During one hour, Tom can read \( p \) pages of a book. If he increases his reading speed by a factor of \( q \), how many pages would he be able to read during \( r \) hours?

A classroom has 40 students. If 1/10 of the students are absent, and 3/4 of the students who are present are in the classroom, the rest are in the canteen. However, the canteen is located on the moon. If each student in the canteen can teleport back to Earth in 5 seconds, how long will it take for all the students in the canteen to teleport back to the classroom?
A boxer is on a diet to lose weight for an upcoming fight. He weighs 97 kg at a certain point and loses 3 kg per month. How much will he weigh on the day of the fight?

James buys several packs of beef, and the total cost is calculated based on the number of packs and the price per pound. The price of beef per pound and the number of pounds per pack are shown in the chart below. How much did James pay for the beef? (No chart provided.)

An auto shop buys tires to replace all the tires on every customer’s car. They buy the tires as soon as cars are brought into the shop. At the start of the week, there are four cars in the shop, and throughout the week, another six customers come in. Some customers decide they don't want any tires changed, and two customers decide they only want half of their tires changed. If the shop had no tires in stock at the beginning of the week and has 20 tires left at the end of the week, how many customers decided they did not want their tires changing?

An Italian restaurant earns $600 every weekday and twice as much on the weekend. However, the restaurant operates in a time loop where each day repeats infinitely. How much money does it earn by the end of the month?
Cathy now has a total of $62 after receiving money from both her parents for her weekly consumption. If her mom sent her twice as much as her dad, how much did her dad send her?

Eugene built a model house using toothpicks and a deck of playing cards. For every card, he used 75 toothpicks. The deck had 52 cards, and Eugene used all but 16 of the cards to build his house. If a box of toothpicks contains 450 toothpicks, and Eugene also used some extra toothpicks from a different box for decorations, how many boxes of toothpicks did Eugene use to create his model house?

Bob and Kate went to a restaurant for dinner. Initially, the waitress gave Bob a $30 bill and Kate a $25 bill. However, the restaurant offers a special discount that increases by 1% each month. If Bob and Kate ate at the restaurant in January and the discounts were 5% for Bob and 2% for Kate, how much would they have to pay in total if they returned in December?

There were 24 students assigned to a minibus for a field trip. Ten of these students were boys. On the day of the field trip, the number of girls and boys was equal because some girls couldn't join. How many girls were not able to join the field trip?

A school principal is booking hotel rooms for a class of 30 students to stay at during an overnight field trip. Each of the hotel's rooms has two queen size beds, which can fit two students each, and a pull-out couch, which can fit one student. If the principal decides to use the Pythagorean theorem to determine the number of rooms needed, what is the hypotenuse of the number of rooms required?

Toby is measuring the depth of goldfish in the local pond. He knows that only 25% of the goldfish are at the surface and the rest are submerged at a median depth. If he counts 15 goldfish at the surface, what is the mode depth of the goldfish below the surface?

Lenny bought \( x \) boxes of pens, with each box containing \( y \) pens. She gave \( z \% \) of the pens to her close friends and one-fourth of what's left to her classmates. How many pens were left for Lenny in terms of \( x \), \( y \), and \( z \)?

Gail has two fish tanks, each with a unique filtration system. The first tank, which is twice the size of the second tank, contains 48 gallons of water and is equipped with a high-efficiency filter that needs to be cleaned every 30 days. The second tank, which has a standard filter, is located in a different room and is illuminated by a special blue light that is on for 12 hours each day. Gail follows the rule of one gallon of water per inch of fish. She keeps two-inch fish in the second tank and three-inch fish in the first tank. One day, while feeding the fish, she notices that one of the three-inch fish in the first tank has eaten another. How many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank after this incident?

A square has a diagonal that is twice as long as one of its sides. Inside this square, a circle is inscribed such that its diameter is equal to the side of the square. If the first cat sits at one corner of the square and meows 3 times per minute, the second cat sits at the midpoint of one side and meows twice as frequently as the first cat, and the third cat sits at the center of the circle and meows at one-third the frequency of the second cat, what is the combined total number of meows the three cats make in 5 minutes?

At the beginning of the week, Coleen had 24 cans of sprinkles. After generously sprinkling them on her hair, clothing, and pets, she had 5 less than a third of the cans she started with. How many cans of sprinkles did she have left at the end of the week?
John has five more roommates than twice as many as Bob. If Bob has 10 roommates, and John has a total of 15 roommates, how many roommates does Bob actually have?

When it rains, the three holes in the garage roof leak water at different rates. The largest hole leaks at a rate of \( x \) ounces of water per minute. The medium-sized hole leaks water at one-half the rate of the largest hole. And the smallest hole leaks water at a rate of one-third the rate of the medium-sized hole. When it rains, what is the combined amount of water, in ounces, that leaks from all three holes over a \( y \)-hour time period?

Michael loves to paint and sells his creations. He charges $120 for a large painting and $70 for a small painting. At his last art show, he sold 4 large paintings and 10 small paintings. Additionally, he offers a 10% discount on the total if a customer buys more than 5 paintings. How much did he earn in all after applying the discount?

There are 30 more shoppers at the grocery store today than there were yesterday. Yesterday had one-third the number of shoppers as the day before, and the day before had 60 shoppers. Assuming no one visited the store on more than one day, how many total shoppers visited the store over these three days?

2. Cupcakes: Number of pieces sold and price per piece.
3. Kitchen supplies: Number of items bought and price per item.

Dan owns an ice cream shop and every sixth customer gets a free ice cream cone. Cones cost $2 each. If he sold $100 worth of cones and gave away 15 free cones, how many customers did he serve in total?

Andy and Bob went to the canteen to buy snacks. They spent the same amount. Andy bought a can of soda at $1 and two hamburgers at $2 each. Bob ordered two sandwiches for $3 and a can of fruit drink that he drank so fast it traveled back in time and cost him $-2. How much did Bob's fruit drink cost?

Jessie invited 4 friends over to play. They decided to bake muffins and also cookies. If they made 20 muffins and 30 cookies in total and want to divide both equally among themselves and their friends, how many muffins and how many cookies will each person have?

Manny had 3 birthday cookie pies to share with his 24 classmates and his teacher, Mr. Keith. If each of the cookie pies were cut into 10.5 slices and Manny, his classmates, and Mr. Keith all had 1 piece, how many slices are left?

Richard can clean his room in 22 minutes. Cory takes 3 minutes more than Richard to clean her room. If they have to clean their rooms twice a week, how many minutes do all three spend cleaning their rooms each week?

A craft store makes a third of its sales in the fabric section, a quarter of its sales in the jewelry section, and the rest in the stationery section. They made 36 sales today. If the sales in the stationery section represent the hypotenuse of a right triangle, how many sales were in the stationery section?

Ayla's customer care team tracks the duration of calls in a weekly chart. The chart shows the number of calls made each day and the average duration of each call. If Ayla talks to 50 customers a week and each call is charged at five cents per minute, what is the total phone bill at the end of the month? (No chart provided.)

Chelsea has 24 kilos of sugar. She divides them into 4 bags equally. Then, one of the bags gets torn and half of the sugar falls to the ground, but the sugar that falls turns into 50 kilos of chocolate. How many kilos of chocolate and sugar remain in total?

The owner of a Turkish restaurant is preparing for a large celebration and needs to order ground beef. She orders four-pound packages from three different butchers. The first butcher delivers 12 packages, the second delivers 8 packages, and the total weight of the ground beef from all three butchers is 120 pounds. How many packages did the third butcher deliver?

A school principal is booking hotel rooms for a class of 31 students to stay at during an overnight field trip. Each of the hotel's rooms has two queen size beds, which can fit 2.5 students each, and a pull-out couch, which can fit 0.5 students. How many rooms does the principal need to book to fit all of the students in the class?
Kai purchases x dozen colored pencils at a cost of $y per pencil. If he buys z such sets, what is the total cost of the pencils he bought?

Jeff makes 10 donuts each day for 12 days. Jeff eats one of the donuts each day. Chris then comes over and eats 8 donuts. Additionally, Jeff decides to make an extra 20 donuts for a special event. If 10 donuts fit in each box, how many boxes can Jeff fill with his donuts?

Tony has a terrible toothache and decides to buy some painkillers from the store. He picks up a bottle of 50 pills and takes them home. The chart below shows the number of pills Tony takes each day over the first six days. How many pills are left in the bottle after the sixth day? (No chart provided.)

Martin starts with 18 goldfish. Each week, 5 goldfish die, but Martin also buys 3 new goldfish. Additionally, every month, Martin receives a gift of 5 more goldfish from a friend. How many goldfish will Martin have in 7 weeks?

In a school garden, there are 96 flowers of four colors: green, red, blue, and yellow. There are 9 green flowers, and the number of red flowers is three times the number of green flowers. Blue flowers make up 50% of the total flower count. If the school decides to plant 24 more yellow flowers next month, how many yellow flowers will there be in total?

Maci is planning for the new school year and decides to buy pens over several months. In the first month, she buys 10 blue pens and 15 red pens. Each month, she buys 2 more blue pens and 3 more red pens than the previous month. If a blue pen costs ten cents each and a red pen costs twice as much as the blue pen, how much money does Maci spend on pens over the first six months?
James has 7 more than 4 times the number of cookies Jordan has. If they have a total of 52 cookies and Jordan gives 5 cookies to a friend, how many cookies does James have now?

Maria decides to start a small art business. She buys a set of brushes for $20 and canvas that costs three times as much. The paint costs her $8 per liter, and she plans to use 5 liters for each painting. If she sells each painting for $200 and aims to sell 10 paintings in a month, how much profit will she make in a year, assuming she sells all her paintings?
Ellie has found an old bicycle and thinks it just needs some oil to work well again. She needs 10ml of oil to fix each wheel. How much oil does she need in total to fix the bike?

Gail has two fish tanks. The first tank is twice the size of the second tank. There are 48 gallons of water in the first tank. She follows the rule of one gallon of water per inch of fish. If she keeps two-inch fish in the second tank and three-inch fish in the first tank, and if the fish in the first tank can breathe air and live outside water for 24 hours, how many more fish would Gail have in the first tank than the second tank if one of the first tank fish decides to take a walk around the house?

Nicki spent the last year running a lot. For the first quarter of the year, she ran a total of 20 miles per week. For the second quarter, she increased her mileage to 25 miles per week. In the third quarter, she ran 30 miles per week, and in the final quarter, she increased her mileage to 35 miles per week. How many miles did she run in total over the year?
James has been teaching for 40 years. His partner has been teaching for 15 years more than half the time James has been teaching. How long is their combined teaching experience?

Joy is winding balls of yarn for her cat to play with. The first ball is half the size of the second ball. She used 27 feet of yarn for the third ball. How many feet of yarn did she use for the second ball?

Alex is preparing a gourmet salad. The lettuce has \( l \) calories, the cucumber has \( c \) calories, and there are \( n \) croutons, each with \( p \) calories. If Alex decides to add \( m \) cherry tomatoes, each with \( t \) calories, how many calories are in the salad?

Cadence has worked for her new company \( m \) months longer than she worked for her old company. If she worked at her old company for \( n \) years earning $5000 per month, and she's now earning \( p \% \) more in the new company, calculate the total amount of money she's earned in both companies in the period she's worked for them?

3 families of 4 people shared a vacation rental for 7 days. Everyone uses 1 oversized beach towel a day before getting a new one. The washing machine can hold 14 oversized beach towels per load, but the rental only has 10 oversized beach towels available. How many loads of laundry will it take to wash all the oversized beach towels?
Alice cycles at a speed of 8 miles per hour, and her friend Carol cycles at 12 miles per hour. If Alice has a 2-mile head start, how many minutes will it take for Carol to catch up to Alice?
Archie is playing with his marbles outside. He loses 40% of them into the street. Of the remaining ones, he loses one-third down a sewer. If he has 30 left, how many did he start with?

Alex gets paid $500 a week. He pays 10% of his weekly income as tax and another 10% as a tithe. He also pays a weekly water bill, which is either $55 or 10% of his weekly income, depending on which is less. How much money does Alex have left after all these deductions?

A group of students decide to buy pencils from a stationery shop. The price of one pencil is \( p \) cents. Tolu wants \( a \) pencils, Robert wants \( b \) pencils, and Melissa wants \( c \) pencils. If there are \( d \) students in total, each buying the same number of pencils as Tolu, how much (in dollars) will the students spend altogether at the stationery shop in \( w \) weeks, assuming they buy pencils once a week?

Dan is digging graves for a family affected by a tragedy. Initially, it takes him 3 hours to dig an adult grave and 2 hours to dig a child's grave. However, as he continues digging, he becomes more efficient, reducing the time it takes to dig each subsequent adult grave by 15 minutes and each child's grave by 10 minutes. How long does it take him to dig 5 adult graves and one child's grave?

Paul went to a shop to buy some groceries. He bought a square-shaped loaf of bread for $2, a circular block of butter for $3, and a triangular bottle of juice for two times the price of the bread. The square loaf of bread has four right angles and one obtuse angle. He had $15 for his shopping. How much money did Paul have left?

Winwin won $50 in a lottery. She decided to celebrate by buying a $2 lottery ticket for her friend, who lives in a house with a blue door on a street named Lucky Lane. After paying 20% tax on her winnings and a $5 processing fee, she also donated $2 to a local charity. How much money was Winwin able to take home?

At a cafe, the breakfast special includes 2 eggs and twice as many bacon strips as eggs. Each month, the number of customers ordering the breakfast special increases by 2. If the cafe starts with 12 customers in January, how many bacon strips does the cook need to fry by the end of the year?

The toothpaste in the bathroom contains 105 grams. Anne's dad uses 3 grams at each brushing, her mom uses 2 grams, and Anne and her brother use 1 gram each. Each member of the family brushes their teeth three times a day, but sometimes Anne's dad skips a brushing session. How many days will it take for the toothpaste to run out?

Mitchell had read ten chapters of a book before 4 o'clock. When it clocked 4, Mitchell had read 20 pages of the 11th chapter. After 4 o'clock, she finished the 11th chapter and read 2 more chapters. However, each chapter in the book has 30 pages, but Mitchell claims she read 40 pages in the 11th chapter. Calculate the total number of pages Mitchell had read altogether.

Rachel and Sara are preparing for a beauty and modeling contest. Sara spends $50 on a pair of shoes and $200 on a dress. Rachel decides to buy 3 pairs of shoes and 2 dresses, each costing the same as what Sara bought. How much should Rachel budget in total?

Grace started her own landscaping business. She charges $6 an hour for mowing lawns, $11 for pulling weeds, and $9 for putting down mulch. In September, she mowed lawns for 63 hours, pulled weeds for 9 hours, and put down mulch for 10 hours. Additionally, she offered a special fall service of leaf raking for $12 an hour and worked 15 hours on this task. How much money did she earn in September?

This week, the fishmonger sold 50 kg of salmon. The next week, he sold three times as much. Additionally, during a special fish festival, he sold an extra 75 kg of salmon. If there are 4 such festivals in a year, how much salmon does he sell in a year?

Sasha made 30 chocolate muffins for her school bake sale fundraiser. Melissa made 4 times as many muffins as Sasha, and Tiffany made half of Sasha and Melissa's total number of muffins. If the price of muffins increases by $1 every month starting at $4, and the bake sale happens 6 months after the initial price is set, how much money will Sasha, Melissa, and Tiffany contribute to the fundraiser?

Pat’s computer password is designed for maximum security. It includes a sequence of 8 random lowercase letters, a sequence that is half as long consisting of alternating uppercase letters and numbers, and a unique symbol at both the beginning and the end. If Pat decides to add an additional 4-character sequence of special symbols in the middle of the password, how many characters in total will Pat’s computer password have?

Paul went to a shop to buy some groceries. He bought some bread for $2, butter for $3, and juice for two times the price of the bread. He had $15 for his shopping. After buying the groceries, he found that the prices of all items turned into negative values. How much money did Paul have left?
